var P_HTM = [];
P_HTM[1]="*Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa* **";
P_HTM[2]="*Saṃyuttanikāyo* **";
P_HTM[3]="*Mahāvaggo* **";
P_HTM[4]="*45. Maggasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[5]="*1. Avijjāvaggo**Ignorance*";
P_HTM[6]="*1. Avijjāsuttaṃ**Ignorance*";
P_HTM[7]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[9]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[10]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[11]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[12]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[13]="*“Avijjā, bhikkhave, pubbaṅgamā akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samāpattiyā, anvadeva ahirikaṃ anottappaṃ.**“Mendicants, ignorance precedes the attainment of unskillful qualities, with lack of conscience and prudence following along.*";
P_HTM[14]="*Avijjāgatassa, bhikkhave, aviddasuno micchādiṭṭhi pahoti;**An ignoramus, sunk in ignorance, gives rise to wrong view.*";
P_HTM[15]="*micchādiṭṭhissa micchāsaṅkappo pahoti;**Wrong view gives rise to wrong thought.*";
P_HTM[16]="*micchāsaṅkappassa micchāvācā pahoti;**Wrong thought gives rise to wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[17]="*micchāvācassa micchākammanto pahoti;**Wrong speech gives rise to wrong action.*";
P_HTM[18]="*micchākammantassa micchāājīvo pahoti;**Wrong action gives rise to wrong livelihood.*";
P_HTM[19]="*micchāājīvassa micchāvāyāmo pahoti;**Wrong livelihood gives rise to wrong effort.*";
P_HTM[20]="*micchāvāyāmassa micchāsati pahoti;**Wrong effort gives rise to wrong mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[21]="*micchāsatissa micchāsamādhi pahoti.**Wrong mindfulness gives rise to wrong immersion.*";
P_HTM[22]="*Vijjā ca kho, bhikkhave, pubbaṅgamā kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samāpattiyā, anvadeva hirottappaṃ.**Knowledge precedes the attainment of skillful qualities, with conscience and prudence following along.*";
P_HTM[23]="*Vijjāgatassa, bhikkhave, viddasuno sammādiṭṭhi pahoti;**A sage, firm in knowledge, gives rise to right view.*";
P_HTM[24]="*sammādiṭṭhissa sammāsaṅkappo pahoti;**Right view gives rise to right thought.*";
P_HTM[25]="*sammāsaṅkappassa sammāvācā pahoti;**Right thought gives rise to right speech.*";
P_HTM[26]="*sammāvācassa sammākammanto pahoti;**Right speech gives rise to right action.*";
P_HTM[27]="*sammākammantassa sammāājīvo pahoti;**Right action gives rise to right livelihood.*";
P_HTM[28]="*sammāājīvassa sammāvāyāmo pahoti;**Right livelihood gives rise to right effort.*";
P_HTM[29]="*sammāvāyāmassa sammāsati pahoti;**Right effort gives rise to right mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[30]="*sammāsatissa sammāsamādhi pahotī”ti.**Right mindfulness gives rise to right immersion.”*";
P_HTM[31]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[32]="*2. Upaḍḍhasuttaṃ**Half the Spiritual Life*";
P_HTM[33]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[34]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakyesu viharati nagarakaṃ nāma sakyānaṃ nigamo.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, where they have a town named Nagaraka.*";
P_HTM[35]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[36]="*“upaḍḍhamidaṃ, bhante, brahmacariyaṃ, yadidaṃ—kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā”ti.**“Sir, good friends, companions, and associates are half the spiritual life.”*";
P_HTM[37]="*“Mā hevaṃ, ānanda, mā hevaṃ, ānanda.**“Not so, Ānanda! Not so, Ānanda!*";
P_HTM[38]="*Sakalamevidaṃ, ānanda, brahmacariyaṃ, yadidaṃ—kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā.**Good friends, companions, and associates are the whole of the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[39]="*Kalyāṇamittassetaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ kalyāṇasahāyassa kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa—ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvessati, ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarissati.**A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[40]="*Kathañcānanda, bhikkhu kalyāṇamitto kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti, ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti?**And how does a mendicant with good friends develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path?*";
P_HTM[41]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ;**It’s when a mendicant develops right view, which relies on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripens as letting go.*";
P_HTM[42]="*sammāsaṅkappaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ … pe …**They develop right thought …*";
P_HTM[43]="*sammāvācaṃ bhāveti … pe …**right speech …*";
P_HTM[44]="*sammākammantaṃ bhāveti … pe …**right action …*";
P_HTM[45]="*sammāājīvaṃ bhāveti … pe …**right livelihood …*";
P_HTM[46]="*sammāvāyāmaṃ bhāveti … pe …**right effort …*";
P_HTM[47]="*sammāsatiṃ bhāveti … pe …**right mindfulness …*";
P_HTM[48]="*sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ.**right immersion, which relies on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripens as letting go.*";
P_HTM[49]="*Evaṃ kho, ānanda, bhikkhu kalyāṇamitto kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti, ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti.**That’s how a mendicant with good friends develops and cultivates the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[50]="*Tadamināpetaṃ, ānanda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā sakalamevidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, yadidaṃ—kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā.**And here’s another way to understand how good friends are the whole of the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[51]="*Mamañhi, ānanda, kalyāṇamittaṃ āgamma jātidhammā sattā jātiyā parimuccanti; jarādhammā sattā jarāya parimuccanti; maraṇadhammā sattā maraṇena parimuccanti; sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammā sattā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsehi parimuccanti.**For, by relying on me as a good friend, sentient beings who are liable to rebirth, old age, and death, to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress are freed from all these things.*";
P_HTM[52]="*Iminā kho etaṃ, ānanda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā sakalamevidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, yadidaṃ—kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā”ti.**This is another way to understand how good friends are the whole of the spiritual life.”*";
P_HTM[53]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[54]="*3. Sāriputtasuttaṃ**Sāriputta*";
P_HTM[55]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[56]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Sāriputta went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[57]="*“sakalamidaṃ, bhante, brahmacariyaṃ, yadidaṃ—kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā”ti.**“Sir, good friends, companions, and associates are the whole of the spiritual life.”*";
P_HTM[58]="*“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta.**“Good, good, Sāriputta!*";
P_HTM[59]="*Sakalamidaṃ, sāriputta, brahmacariyaṃ, yadidaṃ—kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā.**Good friends, companions, and associates are the whole of the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[60]="*Kalyāṇamittassetaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ kalyāṇasahāyassa kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa—ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvessati, ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarissati.**A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[61]="*Kathañca, sāriputta, bhikkhu kalyāṇamitto kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti, ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti?**And how does a mendicant with good friends develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path?*";
P_HTM[62]="*Idha, sāriputta, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ … pe … sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ.**It’s when a mendicant develops right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go.*";
P_HTM[63]="*Evaṃ kho, sāriputta, bhikkhu kalyāṇamitto kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti, ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti.**That’s how a mendicant with good friends develops and cultivates the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[64]="*Tadamināpetaṃ, sāriputta, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā sakalamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, yadidaṃ—kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā.**And here’s another way to understand how good friends are the whole of the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[65]="*Mamañhi, sāriputta, kalyāṇamittaṃ āgamma jātidhammā sattā jātiyā parimuccanti; jarādhammā sattā jarāya parimuccanti; maraṇadhammā sattā maraṇena parimuccanti; sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammā sattā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsehi parimuccanti.**For, by relying on me as a good friend, sentient beings who are liable to rebirth, old age, and death, to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress are freed from all these things.*";
P_HTM[66]="*Iminā kho etaṃ, sāriputta, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā sakalamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, yadidaṃ—kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā”ti.**This is another way to understand how good friends are the whole of the spiritual life.”*";
P_HTM[67]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[68]="*4. Jāṇussoṇibrāhmaṇasuttaṃ**Regarding the Brahmin Jāṇussoṇi*";
P_HTM[69]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[70]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then Venerable Ānanda robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms.*";
P_HTM[71]="*Addasā kho āyasmā ānando jāṇussoṇiṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sabbasetena vaḷavābhirathena sāvatthiyā niyyāyantaṃ.**He saw the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi driving out of Sāvatthī in a splendid all-white chariot drawn by mares.*";
P_HTM[72]="*Setā sudaṃ assā yuttā honti setālaṅkārā, seto ratho, setaparivāro, setā rasmiyo, setā patodalaṭṭhi, setaṃ chattaṃ, setaṃ uṇhīsaṃ, setāni vatthāni, setā upāhanā, setāya sudaṃ vālabījaniyā bījīyati.**The yoked horses were pure white, as were the ornaments, chariot, upholstery, reins, goad, and canopy. And his turban, robes, sandals were white, as was the chowry fanning him.*";
P_HTM[73]="*Tamenaṃ jano disvā evamāha:**When people saw it they exclaimed,*";
P_HTM[74]="*“brahmaṃ vata, bho, yānaṃ.**“Wow! That’s a Brahmā vehicle!*";
P_HTM[75]="*Brahmayānarūpaṃ vata, bho”ti.**It’s a vehicle fit for Brahmā!”*";
P_HTM[76]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Ānanda wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened, adding,*";
P_HTM[77]="*“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[78]="*Addasaṃ khvāhaṃ, bhante, jāṇussoṇiṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sabbasetena vaḷavābhirathena sāvatthiyā niyyāyantaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[79]="*Setā sudaṃ assā yuttā honti setālaṅkārā, seto ratho, setaparivāro, setā rasmiyo, setā patodalaṭṭhi, setaṃ chattaṃ, setaṃ uṇhīsaṃ, setāni vatthāni, setā upāhanā, setāya sudaṃ vālabījaniyā bījīyati.* **";
P_HTM[80]="*Tamenaṃ jano disvā evamāha:* **";
P_HTM[81]="*‘brahmaṃ vata, bho, yānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[82]="*Brahmayānarūpaṃ vata, bho’ti.* **";
P_HTM[83]="*Sakkā nu kho, bhante, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmayānaṃ paññāpetun”ti?**“Sir, can you point out a Brahmā vehicle in this teaching and training?”*";
P_HTM[84]="*“Sakkā, ānandā”ti bhagavā avoca:**“I can, Ānanda,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[85]="*“imasseva kho etaṃ, ānanda, ariyassa aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa adhivacanaṃ:**“These are all terms for the noble eightfold path:*";
P_HTM[86]="*‘brahmayānaṃ’ itipi, ‘dhammayānaṃ’ itipi, ‘anuttaro saṅgāmavijayo’ itipīti.**‘vehicle of Brahmā’, or else ‘vehicle of truth’, or else ‘supreme victory in battle’.*";
P_HTM[87]="*Sammādiṭṭhi, ānanda, bhāvitā bahulīkatā rāgavinayapariyosānā hoti, dosavinayapariyosānā hoti, mohavinayapariyosānā hoti.**When right view is developed and cultivated it culminates with the removal of greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[88]="*Sammāsaṅkappo, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosavinayapariyosāno hoti, mohavinayapariyosāno hoti.**When right thought …*";
P_HTM[89]="*Sammāvācā, ānanda, bhāvitā bahulīkatā rāgavinayapariyosānā hoti, dosa … pe … mohavinayapariyosānā hoti.**right speech …*";
P_HTM[90]="*Sammākammanto, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosa … pe … mohavinayapariyosāno hoti.**right action …*";
P_HTM[91]="*Sammāājīvo, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosa … pe … mohavinayapariyosāno hoti.**right livelihood …*";
P_HTM[92]="*Sammāvāyāmo, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosa … pe … mohavinayapariyosāno hoti.**right effort …*";
P_HTM[93]="*Sammāsati, ānanda, bhāvitā bahulīkatā rāgavinayapariyosānā hoti, dosa … pe … mohavinayapariyosānā hoti.**right mindfulness …*";
P_HTM[94]="*Sammāsamādhi, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosa … pe … mohavinayapariyosāno hoti.**right immersion is developed and cultivated it culminates with the removal of greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[95]="*Iminā kho etaṃ, ānanda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā imassevetaṃ ariyassa aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa adhivacanaṃ:**This is a way to understand how these are all terms for the noble eightfold path:*";
P_HTM[96]="*‘brahmayānaṃ’ itipi, ‘dhammayānaṃ’ itipi, ‘anuttaro saṅgāmavijayo’ itipī”ti.**‘vehicle of Brahmā’, or else ‘vehicle of truth’, or else ‘supreme victory in battle’.”*";
P_HTM[97]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[98]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[99]="*“Yassa saddhā ca paññā ca,**“Its qualities of faith and wisdom*";
P_HTM[100]="*Dhammā yuttā sadā dhuraṃ;**are always yoked to the shaft.*";
P_HTM[101]="*Hirī īsā mano yottaṃ,**Conscience is its pole, mind its strap,*";
P_HTM[102]="*Sati ārakkhasārathi.**and mindfulness its careful driver.*";
P_HTM[103]="*Ratho sīlaparikkhāro,**The chariot’s equipped with ethics,*";
P_HTM[104]="*jhānakkho cakkavīriyo;**its axle is absorption, and energy its wheel.*";
P_HTM[105]="*Upekkhā dhurasamādhi,**Equanimity and immersion are the carriage-shaft,*";
P_HTM[106]="*anicchā parivāraṇaṃ.**and it’s upholstered with desirelessness.*";
P_HTM[107]="*Abyāpādo avihiṃsā,**Good will, harmlessness, and seclusion*";
P_HTM[108]="*viveko yassa āvudhaṃ;**are its weapons,*";
P_HTM[109]="*Titikkhā cammasannāho,**patience its shield and armor,*";
P_HTM[110]="*yogakkhemāya vattati.**as it rolls on to sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[111]="*Etadattani sambhūtaṃ,**This supreme Brahmā vehicle*";
P_HTM[112]="*brahmayānaṃ anuttaraṃ;**arises in oneself.*";
P_HTM[113]="*Niyyanti dhīrā lokamhā,**The wise leave the world in it,*";
P_HTM[114]="*aññadatthu jayaṃ jayan”ti.**sure of winning the victory.”*";
P_HTM[115]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[116]="*5. Kimatthiyasuttaṃ**What’s the Purpose*";
P_HTM[117]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[118]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu … pe … ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha … and said to him:*";
P_HTM[119]="*“Idha no, bhante, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā amhe evaṃ pucchanti:**“Sir, sometimes wanderers who follow other paths ask us:*";
P_HTM[120]="*‘kimatthiyaṃ, āvuso, samaṇe gotame brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti?**‘Reverends, what’s the purpose of living the spiritual life with the ascetic Gotama?’*";
P_HTM[121]="*Evaṃ puṭṭhā mayaṃ, bhante, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākaroma:**We answer them like this:*";
P_HTM[122]="*‘dukkhassa kho, āvuso, pariññatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti.**‘The purpose of living the spiritual life under the Buddha is to completely understand suffering.’*";
P_HTM[123]="*Kacci mayaṃ, bhante, evaṃ puṭṭhā evaṃ byākaramānā vuttavādino ceva bhagavato homa, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhāma, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākaroma, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchatī”ti?**Answering this way, we trust that we repeat what the Buddha has said, and don’t misrepresent him with an untruth. We trust our explanation is in line with the teaching, and that there are no legitimate grounds for rebuke or criticism.”*";
P_HTM[124]="*“Taggha tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ puṭṭhā evaṃ byākaramānā vuttavādino ceva me hotha, na ca maṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhatha, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākarotha, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchati.**“Indeed, in answering this way you repeat what I’ve said, and don’t misrepresent me with an untruth. Your explanation is in line with the teaching, and there are no legitimate grounds for rebuke or criticism.*";
P_HTM[125]="*Dukkhassa hi pariññatthaṃ mayi brahmacariyaṃ vussati.**For the purpose of living the spiritual life with me is to completely understand suffering.*";
P_HTM[126]="*Sace vo, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**If wanderers who follow other paths were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[127]="*‘atthi panāvuso, maggo, atthi paṭipadā etassa dukkhassa pariññāyā’ti, evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha:**‘Is there a path and a practice for completely understanding that suffering?’ You should answer them like this:*";
P_HTM[128]="*‘atthi kho, āvuso, maggo, atthi paṭipadā etassa dukkhassa pariññāyā’ti.**‘There is.’*";
P_HTM[129]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, maggo, katamā paṭipadā etassa dukkhassa pariññāyāti?**And what is that path?*";
P_HTM[130]="*Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—**It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[131]="*sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[132]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo, ayaṃ paṭipadā etassa dukkhassa pariññāyāti.**This is the path and the practice for completely understanding suffering.*";
P_HTM[133]="*Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyāthā”ti.**When questioned by wanderers who follow other paths, that’s how you should answer them.”*";
P_HTM[134]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[135]="*6. Paṭhamaaññatarabhikkhusuttaṃ**A Mendicant (1st)*";
P_HTM[136]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[137]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and asked him,*";
P_HTM[138]="*“‘brahmacariyaṃ, brahmacariyan’ti, bhante, vuccati.**“Sir, they speak of this thing called the ‘spiritual path’.*";
P_HTM[139]="*Katamaṃ nu kho, bhante, brahmacariyaṃ, katamaṃ brahmacariyapariyosānan”ti?**What is the spiritual path? And what is the culmination of the spiritual path?”*";
P_HTM[140]="*“Ayameva kho, bhikkhu, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo brahmacariyaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**“Mendicant, the spiritual path is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[141]="*sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[142]="*Yo kho, bhikkhu, rāgakkhayo dosakkhayo mohakkhayo—**The ending of greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[143]="*idaṃ brahmacariyapariyosānan”ti.**This is the culmination of the spiritual path.”*";
P_HTM[144]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[145]="*7. Dutiyaaññatarabhikkhusuttaṃ**A Mendicant (2nd)*";
P_HTM[146]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[147]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and said to him:*";
P_HTM[148]="*“‘Rāgavinayo dosavinayo mohavinayo’ti, bhante, vuccati.**“Sir, they speak of ‘the removal of greed, hate, and delusion’.*";
P_HTM[149]="*Kissa nu kho etaṃ, bhante, adhivacanaṃ:**What is this a term for?”*";
P_HTM[150]="*‘rāgavinayo dosavinayo mohavinayo’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[151]="*“Nibbānadhātuyā kho etaṃ, bhikkhu, adhivacanaṃ:**“Mendicant, the removal of greed, hate, and delusion is a term for the natural principle of extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[152]="*‘rāgavinayo dosavinayo mohavinayo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[153]="*Āsavānaṃ khayo tena vuccatī”ti.**It’s used to speak of the ending of defilements.”*";
P_HTM[154]="*Evaṃ vutte, so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, the mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[155]="*“‘amataṃ, amatan’ti, bhante, vuccati.**“Sir, they speak of ‘the deathless’.*";
P_HTM[156]="*Katamaṃ nu kho, bhante, amataṃ, katamo amatagāmimaggo”ti?**What is the deathless? And what is the path that leads to the deathless?”*";
P_HTM[157]="*“Yo kho, bhikkhu, rāgakkhayo dosakkhayo mohakkhayo—**“The ending of greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[158]="*idaṃ vuccati amataṃ.**This is called the deathless.*";
P_HTM[159]="*Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo amatagāmimaggo, seyyathidaṃ—**The path that leads to the deathless is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[160]="*sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhī”ti.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.”*";
P_HTM[161]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[162]="*8. Vibhaṅgasuttaṃ**Analysis*";
P_HTM[163]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[164]="*“Ariyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ desessāmi vibhajissāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach and analyze for you the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[165]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[166]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[167]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[168]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo?**“And what is the noble eightfold path?*";
P_HTM[169]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**It is right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[170]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sammādiṭṭhi?**And what is right view?*";
P_HTM[171]="*Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dukkhe ñāṇaṃ, dukkhasamudaye ñāṇaṃ, dukkhanirodhe ñāṇaṃ, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ñāṇaṃ—**Knowing about suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.*";
P_HTM[172]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammādiṭṭhi.**This is called right view.*";
P_HTM[173]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāsaṅkappo?**And what is right thought?*";
P_HTM[174]="*Yo kho, bhikkhave, nekkhammasaṅkappo, abyāpādasaṅkappo, avihiṃsāsaṅkappo—**It is the thought of renunciation, good will, and harmlessness.*";
P_HTM[175]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāsaṅkappo.**This is called right thought.*";
P_HTM[176]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sammāvācā?**And what is right speech?*";
P_HTM[177]="*Yā kho, bhikkhave, musāvādā veramaṇī, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī, samphappalāpā veramaṇī—**Avoiding speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical.*";
P_HTM[178]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāvācā.**This is called right speech.*";
P_HTM[179]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammākammanto?**And what is right action?*";
P_HTM[180]="*Yā kho, bhikkhave, pāṇātipātā veramaṇī, adinnādānā veramaṇī, abrahmacariyā veramaṇī—**Avoiding killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual activity.*";
P_HTM[181]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammākammanto.**This is called right action.*";
P_HTM[182]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāājīvo?**And what is right livelihood?*";
P_HTM[183]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako micchāājīvaṃ pahāya sammāājīvena jīvitaṃ kappeti—**It’s when a noble disciple gives up wrong livelihood and earns a living by right livelihood.*";
P_HTM[184]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāājīvo.**This is called right livelihood.*";
P_HTM[185]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāvāyāmo?**And what is right effort?*";
P_HTM[186]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ anuppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati,**It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise.*";
P_HTM[187]="*uppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya chandaṃ janeti … pe …**They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen are given up.*";
P_HTM[188]="*anuppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ uppādāya chandaṃ janeti … pe …**They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that skillful qualities that have not arisen do arise.*";
P_HTM[189]="*uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati—**They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are fulfilled by development.*";
P_HTM[190]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāvāyāmo.**This is called right effort.*";
P_HTM[191]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sammāsati?**And what is right mindfulness?*";
P_HTM[192]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[193]="*vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**They meditate observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[194]="*citte cittānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**They meditate observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[195]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ—**They meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[196]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāsati.**This is called right mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[197]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāsamādhi?**And what is right immersion?*";
P_HTM[198]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[199]="*Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[200]="*Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[201]="*Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati—**Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[202]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāsamādhī”ti.**This is called right immersion.”*";
P_HTM[203]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[204]="*9. Sūkasuttaṃ**A Spike*";
P_HTM[205]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[206]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, sālisūkaṃ vā yavasūkaṃ vā micchāpaṇihitaṃ hatthena vā pādena vā akkantaṃ hatthaṃ vā pādaṃ vā bhindissati, lohitaṃ vā uppādessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**“Mendicants, suppose a spike of rice or barley was pointing the wrong way. If you trod on it with hand or foot, there’s no way it could break the skin and produce blood.*";
P_HTM[207]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[208]="*Micchāpaṇihitattā, bhikkhave, sūkassa.**Because the spike is pointing the wrong way.*";
P_HTM[209]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, so vata bhikkhu micchāpaṇihitāya diṭṭhiyā micchāpaṇihitāya maggabhāvanāya avijjaṃ bhindissati, vijjaṃ uppādessati, nibbānaṃ sacchikarissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**In the same way, a mendicant whose view and development of the path is pointing the wrong way cannot break ignorance, produce knowledge, and realize extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[210]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[211]="*Micchāpaṇihitattā, bhikkhave, diṭṭhiyā.**Because their view is pointing the wrong way.*";
P_HTM[212]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, sālisūkaṃ vā yavasūkaṃ vā sammāpaṇihitaṃ hatthena vā pādena vā akkantaṃ hatthaṃ vā pādaṃ vā bhindissati, lohitaṃ vā uppādessatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**Suppose a spike of rice or barley was pointing the right way. If you trod on it with hand or foot, it may well break the skin and produce blood.*";
P_HTM[213]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[214]="*Sammāpaṇihitattā, bhikkhave, sūkassa.**Because the spike is pointing the right way.*";
P_HTM[215]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, so vata bhikkhu sammāpaṇihitāya diṭṭhiyā sammāpaṇihitāya maggabhāvanāya avijjaṃ bhindissati, vijjaṃ uppādessati, nibbānaṃ sacchikarissatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**In the same way, a mendicant whose view and development of the path is pointing the right way may well break ignorance, produce knowledge, and realize extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[216]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[217]="*Sammāpaṇihitattā, bhikkhave, diṭṭhiyā.**Because their view is pointing the right way.*";
P_HTM[218]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammāpaṇihitāya diṭṭhiyā sammāpaṇihitāya maggabhāvanāya avijjaṃ bhindati, vijjaṃ uppādeti, nibbānaṃ sacchikarotīti?**And how does a mendicant whose view and development of the path is pointing the right way break ignorance, give rise to knowledge, and realize extinguishment?*";
P_HTM[219]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ … pe … sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ.**It’s when a mendicant develops right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go.*";
P_HTM[220]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammāpaṇihitāya diṭṭhiyā sammāpaṇihitāya maggabhāvanāya avijjaṃ bhindati, vijjaṃ uppādeti, nibbānaṃ sacchikarotī”ti.**That’s how a mendicant whose view and development of the path is pointing the right way breaks ignorance, gives rise to knowledge, and realizes extinguishment.”*";
P_HTM[221]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[222]="*10. Nandiyasuttaṃ**With Nandiya*";
P_HTM[223]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[224]="*Atha kho nandiyo paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the wanderer Nandiya went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[225]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho nandiyo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[226]="*“kati nu kho, bho gotama, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā nibbānaṅgamā honti nibbānaparāyanā nibbānapariyosānā”ti?**“Master Gotama, how many things, when developed and cultivated, have extinguishment as their culmination, destination, and end?”*";
P_HTM[227]="*“Aṭṭhime kho, nandiya, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā nibbānaṅgamā honti nibbānaparāyanā nibbānapariyosānā.**“These eight things, when developed and cultivated, have extinguishment as their culmination, destination, and end.*";
P_HTM[228]="*Katame aṭṭha?**What eight?*";
P_HTM[229]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**They are: right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[230]="*Ime kho, nandiya, aṭṭha dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā nibbānaṅgamā honti nibbānaparāyanā nibbānapariyosānā”ti.**These eight things, when developed and cultivated, have extinguishment as their culmination, destination, and end.”*";
P_HTM[231]="*Evaṃ vutte, nandiyo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, the wanderer Nandiya said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[232]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! …*";
P_HTM[233]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[234]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[235]="*Avijjāvaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[236]="*Avijjañca upaḍḍhañca,* **";
P_HTM[237]="*sāriputto ca brāhmaṇo;* **";
P_HTM[238]="*Kimatthiyo ca dve bhikkhū,* **";
P_HTM[239]="*vibhaṅgo sūkanandiyāti.* **";
P_HTM[240]="*2. Vihāravaggo**Meditation*";
P_HTM[241]="*1. Paṭhamavihārasuttaṃ**Meditation (1st)*";
P_HTM[242]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[243]="*“Icchāmahaṃ, bhikkhave, aḍḍhamāsaṃ paṭisallīyituṃ.**“Mendicants, I wish to go on retreat for a fortnight.*";
P_HTM[244]="*Namhi kenaci upasaṅkamitabbo, aññatra ekena piṇḍapātanīhārakenā”ti.**No-one should approach me, except for the one who brings my alms-food.”*";
P_HTM[245]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissutvā nāssudha koci bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamati, aññatra ekena piṇḍapātanīhārakena.**“Yes, sir,” replied those mendicants. And no-one approached him, except for the one who brought the alms-food.*";
P_HTM[246]="*Atha kho bhagavā tassa aḍḍhamāsassa accayena paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then after a fortnight had passed, the Buddha came out of retreat and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[247]="*“yena svāhaṃ, bhikkhave, vihārena paṭhamābhisambuddho viharāmi, tassa padesena vihāsiṃ.**“Mendicants, I’ve been practicing part of the meditation I practiced when I was first awakened.*";
P_HTM[248]="*So evaṃ pajānāmi:**I understand that*";
P_HTM[249]="*‘micchādiṭṭhipaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**there’s feeling conditioned by wrong view*";
P_HTM[250]="*sammādiṭṭhipaccayāpi vedayitaṃ … pe …**and feeling conditioned by right view. …*";
P_HTM[251]="*micchāsamādhipaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**There’s feeling conditioned by wrong immersion,*";
P_HTM[252]="*sammāsamādhipaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**and feeling conditioned by right immersion.*";
P_HTM[253]="*chandapaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**There’s feeling conditioned by desire,*";
P_HTM[254]="*vitakkapaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**by thought,*";
P_HTM[255]="*saññāpaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**and by perception.*";
P_HTM[256]="*chando ca avūpasanto hoti, vitakko ca avūpasanto hoti, saññā ca avūpasantā hoti, tappaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**As long as desire, thought, and perception are not stilled, there is feeling conditioned by that.*";
P_HTM[257]="*chando ca vūpasanto hoti, vitakko ca vūpasanto hoti, saññā ca vūpasantā hoti, tappaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**When desire, thought, and perception are stilled, there is feeling conditioned by that.*";
P_HTM[258]="*appattassa pattiyā atthi āyāmaṃ, tasmimpi ṭhāne anuppatte tappaccayāpi vedayitan’”ti.**There is effort to attain the unattained. When that state has been attained, there is also feeling conditioned by that.”*";
P_HTM[259]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[260]="*2. Dutiyavihārasuttaṃ**Meditation (2nd)*";
P_HTM[261]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[262]="*“Icchāmahaṃ, bhikkhave, temāsaṃ paṭisallīyituṃ.**“Mendicants, I wish to go on retreat for three months.*";
P_HTM[263]="*Namhi kenaci upasaṅkamitabbo, aññatra ekena piṇḍapātanīhārakenā”ti.**No-one should approach me, except for the one who brings my alms-food.”*";
P_HTM[264]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissutvā nāssudha koci bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamati, aññatra ekena piṇḍapātanīhārakena.**“Yes, sir,” replied those mendicants. And no-one approached him, except for the one who brought the alms-food.*";
P_HTM[265]="*Atha kho bhagavā tassa temāsassa accayena paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then after three months had passed, the Buddha came out of retreat and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[266]="*“yena svāhaṃ, bhikkhave, vihārena paṭhamābhisambuddho viharāmi, tassa padesena vihāsiṃ.**“Mendicants, I’ve been practicing part of the meditation I practiced when I was first awakened.*";
P_HTM[267]="*So evaṃ pajānāmi:**I understand that*";
P_HTM[268]="*‘micchādiṭṭhipaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**there’s feeling conditioned by wrong view*";
P_HTM[269]="*micchādiṭṭhivūpasamapaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**and by the stilling of wrong view,*";
P_HTM[270]="*sammādiṭṭhipaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**by right view*";
P_HTM[271]="*sammādiṭṭhivūpasamapaccayāpi vedayitaṃ … pe …**and by the stilling of right view. …*";
P_HTM[272]="*micchāsamādhipaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**There’s feeling conditioned by wrong immersion*";
P_HTM[273]="*micchāsamādhivūpasamapaccayāpi vedayitaṃ, sammāsamādhipaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**and by the stilling of wrong immersion, by right immersion*";
P_HTM[274]="*sammāsamādhivūpasamapaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**and by the stilling of right immersion.*";
P_HTM[275]="*chandapaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**There’s feeling conditioned by desire*";
P_HTM[276]="*chandavūpasamapaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**and by the stilling of desire,*";
P_HTM[277]="*vitakkapaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**by thought*";
P_HTM[278]="*vitakkavūpasamapaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**and by the stilling of thought,*";
P_HTM[279]="*saññāpaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**by perception*";
P_HTM[280]="*saññāvūpasamapaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**and by the stilling of perception.*";
P_HTM[281]="*chando ca avūpasanto hoti, vitakko ca avūpasanto hoti, saññā ca avūpasantā hoti, tappaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**As long as desire, thought, and perception are not stilled, there is feeling conditioned by that.*";
P_HTM[282]="*chando ca vūpasanto hoti, vitakko ca vūpasanto hoti, saññā ca vūpasantā hoti, tappaccayāpi vedayitaṃ;**When desire, thought, and perception are stilled, there is feeling conditioned by that.*";
P_HTM[283]="*appattassa pattiyā atthi āyāmaṃ, tasmimpi ṭhāne anuppatte tappaccayāpi vedayitan’”ti.**There is effort to attain the unattained. When that state has been attained, there is also feeling conditioned by that.”*";
P_HTM[284]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[285]="*3. Sekkhasuttaṃ**A Trainee*";
P_HTM[286]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[287]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and asked him,*";
P_HTM[288]="*“‘sekkho, sekkho’ti, bhante, vuccati.**“Sir, they speak of this person called ‘a trainee’.*";
P_HTM[289]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, sekkho hotī”ti?**How is a trainee defined?”*";
P_HTM[290]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, sekkhāya sammādiṭṭhiyā samannāgato hoti … pe … sekkhena sammāsamādhinā samannāgato hoti.**“Mendicant, it’s someone who has a trainee’s right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[291]="*Ettāvatā kho, bhikkhu, sekkho hotī”ti.**That’s how a trainee is defined.”*";
P_HTM[292]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[293]="*4. Paṭhamauppādasuttaṃ**Arising (1st)*";
P_HTM[294]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[295]="*“Aṭṭhime, bhikkhave, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā anuppannā uppajjanti, nāññatra tathāgatassa pātubhāvā arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**“Mendicants, these eight things don’t arise to be developed and cultivated except when a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha has appeared.*";
P_HTM[296]="*Katame aṭṭha?**What eight?*";
P_HTM[297]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**They are: right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[298]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭha dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā anuppannā uppajjanti, nāññatra tathāgatassa pātubhāvā arahato sammāsambuddhassā”ti.**These eight things don’t arise to be developed and cultivated except when a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha has appeared.”*";
P_HTM[299]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[300]="*5. Dutiyauppādasuttaṃ**Arising (2nd)*";
P_HTM[301]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[302]="*“Aṭṭhime, bhikkhave, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā anuppannā uppajjanti, nāññatra sugatavinayā.**“Mendicants, these eight things don’t arise to be developed and cultivated apart from the Holy One’s training.*";
P_HTM[303]="*Katame aṭṭha?**What eight?*";
P_HTM[304]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**They are: right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[305]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭha dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā anuppannā uppajjanti, nāññatra sugatavinayā”ti.**These are the eight things that don’t arise to be developed and cultivated apart from the Holy One’s training.”*";
P_HTM[306]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[307]="*6. Paṭhamaparisuddhasuttaṃ**Purified (1st)*";
P_HTM[308]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[309]="*“Aṭṭhime, bhikkhave, dhammā parisuddhā pariyodātā anaṅgaṇā vigatūpakkilesā anuppannā uppajjanti, nāññatra tathāgatassa pātubhāvā arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**“Mendicants, these eight things don’t arise to be purified, bright, flawless, and rid of corruptions except when a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha has appeared.*";
P_HTM[310]="*Katame aṭṭha?**What eight?*";
P_HTM[311]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**They are: right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[312]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭha dhammā parisuddhā pariyodātā anaṅgaṇā vigatūpakkilesā anuppannā uppajjanti, nāññatra tathāgatassa pātubhāvā arahato sammāsambuddhassā”ti.**These eight things don’t arise to be purified, bright, flawless, and rid of corruptions except when a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha has appeared.”*";
P_HTM[313]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[314]="*7. Dutiyaparisuddhasuttaṃ**Purified (2nd)*";
P_HTM[315]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[316]="*“Aṭṭhime, bhikkhave, dhammā parisuddhā pariyodātā anaṅgaṇā vigatūpakkilesā anuppannā uppajjanti, nāññatra sugatavinayā.**“Mendicants, these eight things don’t arise to be purified, bright, flawless, and rid of corruptions apart from the Holy One’s training.*";
P_HTM[317]="*Katame aṭṭha?**What eight?*";
P_HTM[318]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**They are: right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[319]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭha dhammā parisuddhā pariyodātā anaṅgaṇā vigatūpakkilesā anuppannā uppajjanti, nāññatra sugatavinayā”ti.**These eight things don’t arise to be purified, bright, flawless, and rid of corruptions apart from the Holy One’s training.”*";
P_HTM[320]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[321]="*8. Paṭhamakukkuṭārāmasuttaṃ**At the Chicken Monastery (1st)*";
P_HTM[322]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[323]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca ānando āyasmā ca bhaddo pāṭaliputte viharanti kukkuṭārāme.**At one time the venerables Ānanda and Bhadda were staying at Pāṭaliputta, in the Chicken Monastery.*";
P_HTM[324]="*Atha kho āyasmā bhaddo sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Bhadda came out of retreat, went to Venerable Ānanda, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[325]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā bhaddo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to Ānanda:*";
P_HTM[326]="*“‘Abrahmacariyaṃ, abrahmacariyan’ti, āvuso ānanda, vuccati.**“Reverend, they speak of this thing called ‘not the spiritual path’.*";
P_HTM[327]="*Katamaṃ nu kho, āvuso, abrahmacariyan”ti?**What is not the spiritual path?”*";
P_HTM[328]="*“Sādhu sādhu, āvuso bhadda.**“Good, good, Reverend Bhadda!*";
P_HTM[329]="*Bhaddako kho te, āvuso bhadda, ummaṅgo, bhaddakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ, kalyāṇī paripucchā.**Your approach and articulation are excellent, and it’s a good question.*";
P_HTM[330]="*Evañhi tvaṃ, āvuso bhadda, pucchasi:**For you asked:*";
P_HTM[331]="*‘abrahmacariyaṃ, abrahmacariyanti, āvuso ānanda, vuccati.**‘They speak of this thing called “not the spiritual path”.*";
P_HTM[332]="*Katamaṃ nu kho, āvuso, abrahmacariyan’”ti?**What is not the spiritual path?’”*";
P_HTM[333]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[334]="*“Ayameva kho, āvuso, aṭṭhaṅgiko micchāmaggo abrahmacariyaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**“What is not the spiritual path is simply the wrong eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[335]="*micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāsamādhī”ti.**wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion.”*";
P_HTM[336]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[337]="*9. Dutiyakukkuṭārāmasuttaṃ**At the Chicken Monastery (2nd)*";
P_HTM[338]="*Pāṭaliputtanidānaṃ.**At Pāṭaliputta.*";
P_HTM[339]="*“‘Brahmacariyaṃ, brahmacariyan’ti, āvuso ānanda, vuccati.**“Reverend, they speak of this thing called the ‘spiritual path’.*";
P_HTM[340]="*Katamaṃ nu kho, āvuso, brahmacariyaṃ, katamaṃ brahmacariyapariyosānan”ti?**What is the spiritual path? And what is the culmination of the spiritual path?”*";
P_HTM[341]="*“Sādhu sādhu, āvuso bhadda.**“Good, good, Reverend Bhadda!*";
P_HTM[342]="*Bhaddako kho te, āvuso bhadda, ummaṅgo, bhaddakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ, kalyāṇī paripucchā.**Your approach and articulation are excellent, and it’s a good question.*";
P_HTM[343]="*Evañhi tvaṃ, āvuso bhadda, pucchasi:**For you asked:*";
P_HTM[344]="*‘brahmacariyaṃ, brahmacariyanti, āvuso ānanda, vuccati.**‘They speak of this thing called “the spiritual path”.*";
P_HTM[345]="*Katamaṃ nu kho, āvuso, brahmacariyaṃ, katamaṃ brahmacariyapariyosānan’”ti?**What is the spiritual path? And what is the culmination of the spiritual path?’”*";
P_HTM[346]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[347]="*“Ayameva kho, āvuso, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo brahmacariyaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**“The spiritual path is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[348]="*sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[349]="*Yo kho, āvuso, rāgakkhayo dosakkhayo mohakkhayo—**The ending of greed, hate, and delusion:*";
P_HTM[350]="*idaṃ brahmacariyapariyosānan”ti.**this is the culmination of the spiritual path.”*";
P_HTM[351]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[352]="*10. Tatiyakukkuṭārāmasuttaṃ**At the Chicken Monastery (3rd)*";
P_HTM[353]="*Pāṭaliputtanidānaṃ.**At Pāṭaliputta.*";
P_HTM[354]="*“‘Brahmacariyaṃ, brahmacariyan’ti, āvuso ānanda, vuccati.**“Reverend, they speak of this thing called the ‘spiritual path’.*";
P_HTM[355]="*Katamaṃ nu kho, āvuso, brahmacariyaṃ, katamo brahmacārī, katamaṃ brahmacariyapariyosānan”ti?**What is the spiritual path? Who is someone on the spiritual path? And what is the culmination of the spiritual path?”*";
P_HTM[356]="*“Sādhu sādhu, āvuso bhadda.**“Good, good, Reverend Bhadda!*";
P_HTM[357]="*Bhaddako kho te, āvuso bhadda, ummaṅgo, bhaddakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ, kalyāṇī paripucchā.**Your approach and articulation are excellent, and it’s a good question. …*";
P_HTM[358]="*Evañhi tvaṃ, āvuso bhadda, pucchasi:* **";
P_HTM[359]="*‘brahmacariyaṃ, brahmacariyanti, āvuso ānanda, vuccati.* **";
P_HTM[360]="*Katamaṃ nu kho, āvuso, brahmacariyaṃ, katamo brahmacārī, katamaṃ brahmacariyapariyosānan’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[361]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.* **";
P_HTM[362]="*“Ayameva kho, āvuso, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo brahmacariyaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**The spiritual path is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[363]="*sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[364]="*Yo kho, āvuso, iminā ariyena aṭṭhaṅgikena maggena samannāgato—**Someone who possesses this noble eightfold path*";
P_HTM[365]="*ayaṃ vuccati brahmacārī.**is called someone on the spiritual path.*";
P_HTM[366]="*Yo kho, āvuso, rāgakkhayo dosakkhayo mohakkhayo—**The ending of greed, hate, and delusion:*";
P_HTM[367]="*idaṃ brahmacariyapariyosānan”ti.**this is the culmination of the spiritual path.”*";
P_HTM[368]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[369]="*Tīṇi suttantāni ekanidānāni.* **";
P_HTM[370]="*Vihāravaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[371]="*Dve vihārā ca sekkho ca,* **";
P_HTM[372]="*uppādā apare duve;* **";
P_HTM[373]="*Parisuddhena dve vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[374]="*kukkuṭārāmena tayoti.* **";
P_HTM[375]="*3. Micchattavaggo**The Wrong Way*";
P_HTM[376]="*1. Micchattasuttaṃ**The Wrong Way*";
P_HTM[377]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[378]="*“Micchattañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, sammattañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the wrong way and the right way.*";
P_HTM[379]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[380]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, micchattaṃ?**And what is the wrong way?*";
P_HTM[381]="*Seyyathidaṃ—micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāsamādhi.**It is wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion.*";
P_HTM[382]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, micchattaṃ.**This is called the wrong way.*";
P_HTM[383]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, sammattaṃ?**And what is the right way?*";
P_HTM[384]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**It is right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[385]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammattan”ti.**This is called the right way.”*";
P_HTM[386]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[387]="*2. Akusaladhammasuttaṃ**Unskillful Qualities*";
P_HTM[388]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[389]="*“Akusale ca kho, bhikkhave, dhamme desessāmi, kusale ca dhamme.**“Mendicants, I will teach you skillful and unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[390]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[391]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, akusalā dhammā?**And what are unskillful qualities?*";
P_HTM[392]="*Seyyathidaṃ—micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāsamādhi.**They are wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion.*";
P_HTM[393]="*Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, akusalā dhammā.**These are called unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[394]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, kusalā dhammā?**And what are skillful qualities?*";
P_HTM[395]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**They are right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[396]="*Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, kusalā dhammā”ti.**These are called skillful qualities.”*";
P_HTM[397]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[398]="*3. Paṭhamapaṭipadāsuttaṃ**Practice (1st)*";
P_HTM[399]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[400]="*“Micchāpaṭipadañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, sammāpaṭipadañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the wrong practice and the right practice.*";
P_HTM[401]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[402]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, micchāpaṭipadā?**And what’s the wrong practice?*";
P_HTM[403]="*Seyyathidaṃ—micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāsamādhi.**It is wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion.*";
P_HTM[404]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, micchāpaṭipadā.**This is called the wrong practice.*";
P_HTM[405]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sammāpaṭipadā?**And what’s the right practice?*";
P_HTM[406]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**It is right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[407]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāpaṭipadā”ti.**This is called the right practice.”*";
P_HTM[408]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[409]="*4. Dutiyapaṭipadāsuttaṃ**Practice (2nd)*";
P_HTM[410]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[411]="*“Gihino vāhaṃ, bhikkhave, pabbajitassa vā micchāpaṭipadaṃ na vaṇṇemi.**“Mendicants, I don’t praise wrong practice for laypeople or renunciates.*";
P_HTM[412]="*Gihi vā, bhikkhave, pabbajito vā micchāpaṭipanno micchāpaṭipattādhikaraṇahetu nārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**Because of wrong practice, neither laypeople nor renunciates succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.*";
P_HTM[413]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, micchāpaṭipadā?**And what’s the wrong practice?*";
P_HTM[414]="*Seyyathidaṃ—micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāsamādhi.**It is wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion.*";
P_HTM[415]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, micchāpaṭipadā.**This is called the wrong practice.*";
P_HTM[416]="*Gihino vāhaṃ, bhikkhave, pabbajitassa vā micchāpaṭipadaṃ na vaṇṇemi.**I don’t praise wrong practice for lay people or renunciates.*";
P_HTM[417]="*Gihi vā, bhikkhave, pabbajito vā micchāpaṭipanno micchāpaṭipattādhikaraṇahetu nārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**Because of wrong practice, neither laypeople nor renunciates succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.*";
P_HTM[418]="*Gihino vāhaṃ, bhikkhave, pabbajitassa vā sammāpaṭipadaṃ vaṇṇemi.**I praise right practice for laypeople and renunciates.*";
P_HTM[419]="*Gihi vā, bhikkhave, pabbajito vā sammāpaṭipanno sammāpaṭipattādhikaraṇahetu ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**Because of right practice, both laypeople and renunciates succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.*";
P_HTM[420]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sammāpaṭipadā?**And what’s the right practice?*";
P_HTM[421]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**It is right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[422]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāpaṭipadā.**This is called the right practice.*";
P_HTM[423]="*Gihino vāhaṃ, bhikkhave, pabbajitassa vā sammāpaṭipadaṃ vaṇṇemi.**I praise right practice for laypeople and renunciates.*";
P_HTM[424]="*Gihi vā, bhikkhave, pabbajito vā sammāpaṭipanno sammāpaṭipattādhikaraṇahetu ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan”ti.**Because of right practice, both laypeople and renunciates succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.”*";
P_HTM[425]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[426]="*5. Paṭhamaasappurisasuttaṃ**A Good Person (1st)*";
P_HTM[427]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[428]="*“Asappurisañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, sappurisañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you a bad person and a good person.*";
P_HTM[429]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[430]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappuriso?**And what is a bad person?*";
P_HTM[431]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, micchāsaṅkappo, micchāvāco, micchākammanto, micchāājīvo, micchāvāyāmo, micchāsati, micchāsamādhi—**It’s someone who has wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion.*";
P_HTM[432]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappuriso.**This is called a bad person.*";
P_HTM[433]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappuriso?**And what is a good person?*";
P_HTM[434]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvāco, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi—**It’s someone who has right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[435]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappuriso”ti.**This is called a good person.”*";
P_HTM[436]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[437]="*6. Dutiyaasappurisasuttaṃ**A Good Person (2nd)*";
P_HTM[438]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[439]="*“Asappurisañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, asappurisena asappurisatarañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you a bad person and a worse person,*";
P_HTM[440]="*Sappurisañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi sappurisena sappurisatarañca.**a good person and a better person.*";
P_HTM[441]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[442]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappuriso?**And what is a bad person?*";
P_HTM[443]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco micchādiṭṭhiko hoti … pe … micchāsamādhi—**It’s someone who has wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion.*";
P_HTM[444]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappuriso.**This is called a bad person.*";
P_HTM[445]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro?**And what is a worse person?*";
P_HTM[446]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco micchādiṭṭhiko hoti … pe … micchāsamādhi, micchāñāṇī, micchāvimutti—**It’s someone who has wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[447]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappurisena asappurisataro.**This is called a worse person.*";
P_HTM[448]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappuriso?**And what is a good person?*";
P_HTM[449]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sammādiṭṭhiko hoti … pe … sammāsamādhi—**It’s someone who has right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[450]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappuriso.**This is called a good person.*";
P_HTM[451]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappurisena sappurisataro?**And what is a better person?*";
P_HTM[452]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sammādiṭṭhiko hoti … pe … sammāsamādhi, sammāñāṇī, sammāvimutti—**It’s someone who has right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[453]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappurisena sappurisataro”ti.**This is called a better person.”*";
P_HTM[454]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[455]="*7. Kumbhasuttaṃ**Pots*";
P_HTM[456]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[457]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kumbho anādhāro suppavattiyo hoti, sādhāro duppavattiyo hoti;**“A pot without a stand is easy to overturn, but if it has a stand it’s hard to overturn.*";
P_HTM[458]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, cittaṃ anādhāraṃ suppavattiyaṃ hoti, sādhāraṃ duppavattiyaṃ hoti.**In the same way, a mind without a stand is easy to overturn, but if it has a stand it’s hard to overturn.*";
P_HTM[459]="*Ko ca, bhikkhave, cittassa ādhāro?**And what’s the stand for the mind?*";
P_HTM[460]="*Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—**It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[461]="*sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[462]="*Ayaṃ cittassa ādhāro.**This is the stand for the mind.*";
P_HTM[463]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kumbho anādhāro suppavattiyo hoti, sādhāro duppavattiyo hoti;**A pot without a stand is easy to overturn, but if it has a stand it’s hard to overturn.*";
P_HTM[464]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, cittaṃ anādhāraṃ suppavattiyaṃ hoti, sādhāraṃ duppavattiyaṃ hotī”ti.**In the same way, a mind without a stand is easy to overturn, but if it has a stand it’s hard to overturn.”*";
P_HTM[465]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[466]="*8. Samādhisuttaṃ**Immersion*";
P_HTM[467]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[468]="*“Ariyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, sammāsamādhiṃ desessāmi saupanisaṃ saparikkhāraṃ.**“Mendicants, I will teach you noble right immersion with its vital conditions and its prerequisites.*";
P_HTM[469]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[470]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ariyo sammāsamādhi saupaniso saparikkhāro?**And what is noble right immersion with its vital conditions and its prerequisites?*";
P_HTM[471]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsati.**There are right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, and right mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[472]="*Yā kho, bhikkhave, imehi sattahaṅgehi cittassa ekaggatā saparikkhāratā—**Unification of mind with these seven factors as prerequisites is called noble right immersion ‘with its vital conditions’ and ‘with its prerequisites’.”*";
P_HTM[473]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyo sammāsamādhi saupaniso itipi saparikkhāro itipī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[474]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[475]="*9. Vedanāsuttaṃ**Feeling*";
P_HTM[476]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[477]="*“Tisso imā, bhikkhave, vedanā.**“Mendicants, there are these three feelings.*";
P_HTM[478]="*Katamā tisso?**What three?*";
P_HTM[479]="*Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—**Pleasant, painful, and neutral feeling.*";
P_HTM[480]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, tisso vedanā.**These are the three feelings.*";
P_HTM[481]="*Imāsaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tissannaṃ vedanānaṃ pariññāya ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo bhāvetabbo.**The noble eightfold path should be developed to completely understand these three feelings.*";
P_HTM[482]="*Katamo ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo?**What is the noble eightfold path?*";
P_HTM[483]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**It is right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[484]="*Imāsaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tissannaṃ vedanānaṃ pariññāya ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo bhāvetabbo”ti.**This noble eightfold path should be developed to completely understand these three feelings.”*";
P_HTM[485]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[486]="*10. Uttiyasuttaṃ**With Uttiya*";
P_HTM[487]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[488]="*Atha kho āyasmā uttiyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā uttiyo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Uttiya went up to the Buddha … and asked him,*";
P_HTM[489]="*“idha mayhaṃ, bhante, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi:**“Just now, sir, as I was in private retreat this thought came to mind.*";
P_HTM[490]="*‘pañca kāmaguṇā vuttā bhagavatā.**‘The Buddha has spoken of the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[491]="*Katame nu kho pañca kāmaguṇā vuttā bhagavatā’”ti?**What are they?’”*";
P_HTM[492]="*“Sādhu sādhu, uttiya.**“Good, good, Uttiya!*";
P_HTM[493]="*Pañcime kho, uttiya, kāmaguṇā vuttā mayā.**I have spoken of these five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[494]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[495]="*Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā,**Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[496]="*sotaviññeyyā saddā … pe …**Sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[497]="*ghānaviññeyyā gandhā … pe …**Smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[498]="*jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …**Tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[499]="*kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā—**Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[500]="*ime kho, uttiya, pañca kāmaguṇā vuttā mayā.**These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation that I’ve spoken of.*";
P_HTM[501]="*Imesaṃ kho, uttiya, pañcannaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ pahānāya ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo bhāvetabbo.**The noble eightfold path should be developed to give up these five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[502]="*Katamo ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo?**What is the noble eightfold path?*";
P_HTM[503]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**It is right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[504]="*Imesaṃ kho, uttiya, pañcannaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ pahānāya ayaṃ ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo bhāvetabbo”ti.**This is the noble eightfold path that should be developed to give up these five kinds of sensual stimulation.”*";
P_HTM[505]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[506]="*Micchattavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[507]="*Micchattaṃ akusalaṃ dhammaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[508]="*Duve paṭipadāpi ca;* **";
P_HTM[509]="*Asappurisena dve kumbho,* **";
P_HTM[510]="*Samādhi vedanuttiyenāti.* **";
P_HTM[511]="*4. Paṭipattivaggo**Practice*";
P_HTM[512]="*1. Paṭhamapaṭipattisuttaṃ**Practice (1st)*";
P_HTM[513]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[514]="*“Micchāpaṭipattiñca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, sammāpaṭipattiñca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the wrong practice and the right practice.*";
P_HTM[515]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[516]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, micchāpaṭipatti?**And what’s the wrong practice?*";
P_HTM[517]="*Seyyathidaṃ—micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāsamādhi.**It is wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion.*";
P_HTM[518]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, micchāpaṭipatti.**This is called the wrong practice.*";
P_HTM[519]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sammāpaṭipatti?**And what’s the right practice?*";
P_HTM[520]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**It is right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[521]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāpaṭipattī”ti.**This is called the right practice.”*";
P_HTM[522]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[523]="*2. Dutiyapaṭipattisuttaṃ**Practice (2nd)*";
P_HTM[524]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[525]="*“Micchāpaṭipannañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, sammāpaṭipannañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you one practicing wrongly and one practicing rightly.*";
P_HTM[526]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[527]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, micchāpaṭipanno?**And who is practicing wrongly?*";
P_HTM[528]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco micchādiṭṭhiko hoti … pe … micchāsamādhi—**It’s someone who has wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion.*";
P_HTM[529]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, micchāpaṭipanno.**This is called one practicing wrongly.*";
P_HTM[530]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāpaṭipanno?**And who is practicing rightly?*";
P_HTM[531]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sammādiṭṭhiko hoti … pe … sammāsamādhi—**It’s someone who has right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[532]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāpaṭipanno”ti.**This is called one practicing rightly.”*";
P_HTM[533]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[534]="*3. Viraddhasuttaṃ**Missed Out*";
P_HTM[535]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[536]="*“Yesaṃ kesañci, bhikkhave, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo viraddho, viraddho tesaṃ ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo sammā dukkhakkhayagāmī.**“Mendicants, whoever has missed out on the noble eightfold path has missed out on the noble path to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[537]="*Yesaṃ kesañci, bhikkhave, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo āraddho, āraddho tesaṃ ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo sammā dukkhakkhayagāmī.**Whoever has undertaken the noble eightfold path has undertaken the noble path to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[538]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo?**And what is the noble eightfold path?*";
P_HTM[539]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**It is right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[540]="*Yesaṃ kesañci, bhikkhave, ayaṃ ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo viraddho, viraddho tesaṃ ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo sammā dukkhakkhayagāmī.**Whoever has missed out on the noble eightfold path has missed out on the noble path to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[541]="*Yesaṃ kesañci, bhikkhave, ayaṃ ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo āraddho, āraddho tesaṃ ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo sammā dukkhakkhayagāmī”ti.**Whoever has undertaken the noble eightfold path has undertaken the noble path to the complete ending of suffering.”*";
P_HTM[542]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[543]="*4. Pāraṅgamasuttaṃ**Going to the Far Shore*";
P_HTM[544]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[545]="*“Aṭṭhime, bhikkhave, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā apārā pāraṃ gamanāya saṃvattanti.**“Mendicants, when these eight things are developed and cultivated they lead to going from the near shore to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[546]="*Katame aṭṭha?**What eight?*";
P_HTM[547]="*Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**They are right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[548]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭha dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā apārā pāraṃ gamanāya saṃvattantī”ti.**When these eight things are developed and cultivated they lead to going from the near shore to the far shore.”*";
P_HTM[549]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[550]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[551]="*“Appakā te manussesu,**“Few are those among humans*";
P_HTM[552]="*ye janā pāragāmino;**who cross to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[553]="*Athāyaṃ itarā pajā,**The rest just run*";
P_HTM[554]="*tīramevānudhāvati.**around on the near shore.*";
P_HTM[555]="*Ye ca kho sammadakkhāte,**When the teaching is well explained,*";
P_HTM[556]="*dhamme dhammānuvattino;**those who practice accordingly*";
P_HTM[557]="*Te janā pāramessanti,**are the ones who will cross over*";
P_HTM[558]="*maccudheyyaṃ suduttaraṃ.**Death’s domain so hard to pass.*";
P_HTM[559]="*Kaṇhaṃ dhammaṃ vippahāya,**Rid of dark qualities,*";
P_HTM[560]="*sukkaṃ bhāvetha paṇḍito;**an astute person should develop the bright.*";
P_HTM[561]="*Okā anokamāgamma,**Leaving home behind*";
P_HTM[562]="*viveke yattha dūramaṃ.**for the seclusion so hard to enjoy,*";
P_HTM[563]="*Tatrābhiratimiccheyya,**you should try to find delight there,*";
P_HTM[564]="*hitvā kāme akiñcano;**having left behind sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[565]="*Pariyodapeyya attānaṃ,**With no possessions, an astute person*";
P_HTM[566]="*cittaklesehi paṇḍito.**should cleanse themselves of mental corruptions.*";
P_HTM[567]="*Yesaṃ sambodhiyaṅgesu,**And those whose minds are rightly developed*";
P_HTM[568]="*sammā cittaṃ subhāvitaṃ;**in the awakening factors;*";
P_HTM[569]="*Ādānapaṭinissagge,**letting go of attachments,*";
P_HTM[570]="*anupādāya ye ratā;**they delight in not grasping.*";
P_HTM[571]="*Khīṇāsavā jutimanto,**With defilements ended, brilliant,*";
P_HTM[572]="*te loke parinibbutā”ti.**they are extinguished in this world.”*";
P_HTM[573]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[574]="*5. Paṭhamasāmaññasuttaṃ**The Ascetic Life (1st)*";
P_HTM[575]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[576]="*“Sāmaññañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, sāmaññaphalāni ca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the ascetic life and the fruits of the ascetic life.*";
P_HTM[577]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[578]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, sāmaññaṃ?**And what is the ascetic life?*";
P_HTM[579]="*Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—**It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[580]="*sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[581]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sāmaññaṃ.**This is called the ascetic life.*";
P_HTM[582]="*Katamāni ca, bhikkhave, sāmaññaphalāni?**And what are the fruits of the ascetic life?*";
P_HTM[583]="*Sotāpattiphalaṃ, sakadāgāmiphalaṃ, anāgāmiphalaṃ, arahattaphalaṃ—**The fruits of stream-entry, once-return, non-return, and perfection.*";
P_HTM[584]="*imāni vuccanti, bhikkhave, sāmaññaphalānī”ti.**These are called the fruits of the ascetic life.”*";
P_HTM[585]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[586]="*6. Dutiyasāmaññasuttaṃ**The Ascetic Life (2nd)*";
P_HTM[587]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[588]="*“Sāmaññañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, sāmaññatthañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the ascetic life and the goal of the ascetic life.*";
P_HTM[589]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[590]="*Katamañca kho, bhikkhave, sāmaññaṃ?**And what is the ascetic life?*";
P_HTM[591]="*Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—**It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[592]="*sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[593]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sāmaññaṃ.**This is called the ascetic life.*";
P_HTM[594]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sāmaññattho?**And what is the goal of the ascetic life?*";
P_HTM[595]="*Yo kho, bhikkhave, rāgakkhayo dosakkhayo mohakkhayo—**The ending of greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[596]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sāmaññattho”ti.**This is called the goal of the ascetic life.”*";
P_HTM[597]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[598]="*7. Paṭhamabrahmaññasuttaṃ**The Brahmin Life (1st)*";
P_HTM[599]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[600]="*“Brahmaññañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, brahmaññaphalāni ca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you life as a brahmin and the fruits of life as a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[601]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[602]="*Katamañca kho, bhikkhave, brahmaññaṃ?**And what is life as a brahmin?*";
P_HTM[603]="*Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—**It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[604]="*sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[605]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, brahmaññaṃ.**This is called life as a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[606]="*Katamāni ca, bhikkhave, brahmaññaphalāni?**And what are the fruits of life as a brahmin?*";
P_HTM[607]="*Sotāpattiphalaṃ, sakadāgāmiphalaṃ, anāgāmiphalaṃ, arahattaphalaṃ—**The fruits of stream-entry, once-return, non-return, and perfection.*";
P_HTM[608]="*imāni vuccanti, bhikkhave, brahmaññaphalānī”ti.**These are called the fruits of life as a brahmin.”*";
P_HTM[609]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
