P_HTM[653]="*5. Aññatitthiyapeyyālavaggo**Abbreviated Texts on Followers of Other Paths*";
P_HTM[654]="*1. Rāgavirāgasuttaṃ**The Fading Away of Greed*";
P_HTM[655]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[656]="*“Sace vo, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**“Mendicants, if wanderers who follow another path were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[657]="*‘kimatthiyaṃ, āvuso, samaṇe gotame brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti, evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha:**‘Reverends, what’s the purpose of living the spiritual life with the ascetic Gotama?’ You should answer them like this:*";
P_HTM[658]="*‘rāgavirāgatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti.**‘The purpose of living the spiritual life under the Buddha is the fading away of greed.’*";
P_HTM[659]="*Sace pana vo, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**If wanderers who follow other paths were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[660]="*‘atthi panāvuso, maggo, atthi paṭipadā rāgavirāgāyā’ti, evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha:**‘Is there a path and a practice for the fading away of greed?’ You should answer them like this:*";
P_HTM[661]="*‘atthi kho, āvuso, maggo, atthi paṭipadā rāgavirāgāyā’ti.**‘There is a path and a practice for the fading away of greed.’*";
P_HTM[662]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, maggo, katamā ca paṭipadā rāgavirāgāya?**And what is that path, what is that practice for the fading away of greed?*";
P_HTM[663]="*Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—**It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[664]="*sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[665]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo, ayaṃ paṭipadā rāgavirāgāyāti.**This is the path, this is the practice for the fading away of greed.*";
P_HTM[666]="*Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyāthā”ti.**When questioned by wanderers who follow other paths, that’s how you should answer them.”*";
P_HTM[667]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[668]="*2-7. Saṃyojanappahānādisuttachakkaṃ**42–47. Saṃyojanappahānādisuttachakka*";
P_HTM[669]="*“Sace vo, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**“Mendicants, if wanderers who follow another path were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[670]="*‘kimatthiyaṃ, āvuso, samaṇe gotame brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti, evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha:**‘Reverends, what’s the purpose of living the spiritual life with the ascetic Gotama?’ You should answer them like this:*";
P_HTM[671]="*‘saṃyojanappahānatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti … pe …**‘The purpose of living the spiritual life under the Buddha is to give up the fetters.’ …*";
P_HTM[672]="*‘anusayasamugghātanatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti … pe …**‘… to uproot the underlying tendencies.’ …*";
P_HTM[673]="*‘addhānapariññatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti … pe …**‘… to completely understand the course of time.’ …*";
P_HTM[674]="*‘āsavānaṃ khayatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti … pe …**‘… to end the defilements.’ …*";
P_HTM[675]="*‘vijjāvimuttiphalasacchikiriyatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti … pe …**‘… to realize the fruit of knowledge and freedom.’ …*";
P_HTM[676]="*‘ñāṇadassanatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti … pe ….**‘… for knowledge and vision.’ …”*";
P_HTM[677]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[678]="*8. Anupādāparinibbānasuttaṃ**Extinguishment by Not Grasping*";
P_HTM[679]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[680]="*“Sace vo, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**“Mendicants, if wanderers who follow another path were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[681]="*‘kimatthiyaṃ, āvuso, samaṇe gotame brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti, evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha:**‘Reverends, what’s the purpose of living the spiritual life with the ascetic Gotama?’ You should answer them like this:*";
P_HTM[682]="*‘anupādāparinibbānatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti.**‘The purpose of living the spiritual life under the Buddha is extinguishment by not grasping.’*";
P_HTM[683]="*Sace pana vo, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**If wanderers who follow other paths were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[684]="*‘atthi panāvuso, maggo, atthi paṭipadā anupādāparinibbānāyā’ti, evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha:**‘Is there a path and a practice for extinguishment by not grasping?’ You should answer them like this:*";
P_HTM[685]="*‘atthi kho, āvuso, maggo, atthi paṭipadā anupādāparinibbānāyā’ti.**‘There is a path and a practice for extinguishment by not grasping.’*";
P_HTM[686]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, maggo, katamā ca paṭipadā anupādāparinibbānāya?**And what is that path, what is that practice for extinguishment by not grasping?*";
P_HTM[687]="*Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—**It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[688]="*sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[689]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo, ayaṃ paṭipadā anupādāparinibbānāyāti.**This is the path, this is the practice for extinguishment by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[690]="*Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyāthā”ti.**When questioned by wanderers who follow other paths, that’s how you should answer them.”*";
P_HTM[691]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[692]="*Aññatitthiyapeyyālaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[693]="*Virāgasaṃyojanaṃ anusayaṃ,* **";
