P_HTM[880]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[881]="*6. Chaṭṭhapācīnaninnasuttaṃ**Sixth Discourse on Slanting East*";
P_HTM[882]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yā kācimā mahānadiyo, seyyathidaṃ—**“Mendicants, all the great rivers—that is,*";
P_HTM[883]="*gaṅgā, yamunā, aciravatī, sarabhū, mahī, sabbā tā pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā;**the Ganges, Yamunā, Aciravatī, Sarabhū, and Mahī—slant, slope, and incline towards the east.*";
P_HTM[884]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvento ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro.**In the same way, a mendicant who develops and cultivates the noble eightfold path slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[885]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvento ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro?**And how does a mendicant who develops the noble eightfold path slant, slope, and incline to extinguishment?*";
P_HTM[886]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ … pe … sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ.**It’s when a mendicant develops right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go.*";
P_HTM[887]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvento ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro”ti.**That’s how a mendicant who develops and cultivates the noble eightfold path slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment.”*";
P_HTM[888]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
