P_HTM[1096]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye keci kusalā dhammā, sabbe te appamādamūlakā appamādasamosaraṇā; appamādo tesaṃ dhammānaṃ aggamakkhāyati.**In the same way, all skillful qualities are rooted in diligence and meet at diligence, and diligence is said to be the best of them.*";
P_HTM[1097]="*Appamattassetaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvessati ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarissati.**A mendicant who is diligent can expect to develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[1098]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appamatto ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti?**And how does a mendicant who is diligent develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path?*";
P_HTM[1099]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti amatogadhaṃ amataparāyanaṃ amatapariyosānaṃ … pe … sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti amatogadhaṃ amataparāyanaṃ amatapariyosānaṃ.**It’s when a mendicant develops right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion, which culminate, finish, and end in the deathless.*";
P_HTM[1100]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appamatto ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarotīti.**That’s how a mendicant who is diligent develops and cultivates the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[1101]="*Yāvatā, bhikkhave, sattā apadā vā dvipadā vā catuppadā vā bahuppadā vā rūpino vā arūpino vā saññino vā asaññino vā nevasaññīnāsaññino vā, tathāgato tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho;**Mendicants, the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, is said to be the best of all sentient beings—be they footless, with two feet, four feet, or many feet; with form or formless; with perception or without perception or with neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[1102]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye keci kusalā dhammā, sabbe te appamādamūlakā appamādasamosaraṇā;**In the same way, all skillful qualities are rooted in diligence and meet at diligence,*";
P_HTM[1103]="*appamādo tesaṃ dhammānaṃ aggamakkhāyati.**and diligence is said to be the best of them.*";
P_HTM[1104]="*Appamattassetaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvessati ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarissati.**A mendicant who is diligent can expect to develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[1105]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appamatto ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti?**And how does a mendicant who is diligent develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path?*";
P_HTM[1106]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti nibbānaninnaṃ nibbānapoṇaṃ nibbānapabbhāraṃ … pe … sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti nibbānaninnaṃ nibbānapoṇaṃ nibbānapabbhāraṃ.**It’s when a mendicant develops right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion, which slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[1107]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appamatto ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarotī”ti.**That’s how a mendicant who is diligent develops and cultivates the noble eightfold path.”*";
P_HTM[1108]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1109]="*2. Padasuttaṃ**Footprints*";
P_HTM[1110]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yāni kānici jaṅgalānaṃ pāṇānaṃ padajātāni, sabbāni tāni hatthipade samodhānaṃ gacchanti;**“The footprints of all creatures that walk can fit inside an elephant’s footprint.*";
P_HTM[1111]="*hatthipadaṃ tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati, yadidaṃ—mahantattena;**So an elephant’s footprint is said to be the biggest of them all.*";
P_HTM[1112]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye keci kusalā dhammā, sabbe te appamādamūlakā appamādasamosaraṇā; appamādo tesaṃ dhammānaṃ aggamakkhāyati.**In the same way, all skillful qualities are rooted in diligence and meet at diligence, and diligence is said to be the best of them.*";
P_HTM[1113]="*Appamattassetaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvessati ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarissati.**A mendicant who is diligent can expect to develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[1114]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appamatto ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti?**And how does a mendicant who is diligent develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path?*";
P_HTM[1115]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ … pe … sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ …**It’s when a mendicant develops right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go. …*";
P_HTM[1116]="*evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appamatto ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarotī”ti.**That’s how a mendicant who is diligent develops and cultivates the noble eightfold path.”*";
P_HTM[1117]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1118]="*3-7. Kūṭādisuttapañcakaṃ**141–145. Kūṭādisutta*";
P_HTM[1119]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kūṭāgārassa yā kāci gopānasiyo sabbā tā kūṭaṅgamā kūṭaninnā kūṭasamosaraṇā; kūṭaṃ tāsaṃ aggamakkhāyati;**“Mendicants, the rafters of a bungalow all lean to the peak, slope to the peak, and meet at the peak, so the peak is said to be the topmost of them all.*";
P_HTM[1120]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …**In the same way …”*";
P_HTM[1121]="*(yathā heṭṭhimasuttantaṃ, evaṃ vitthāretabbaṃ.)**(This should be told in full as in the previous discourse.)*";
P_HTM[1122]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1123]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci mūlagandhā, kāḷānusāriyaṃ tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati;**“Of all kinds of fragrant root, spikenard is said to be the best. …”*";
P_HTM[1124]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1125]="*catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1126]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci sāragandhā, lohitacandanaṃ tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati;**“Of all kinds of fragrant heartwood, red sandalwood is said to be the best. …”*";
P_HTM[1127]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1128]="*pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1129]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci pupphagandhā, vassikaṃ tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati;**“Of all kinds of fragrant flower, jasmine is said to be the best. …”*";
P_HTM[1130]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1131]="*chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1132]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci kuṭṭarājāno, sabbe te rañño cakkavattissa anuyantā bhavanti, rājā tesaṃ cakkavatti aggamakkhāyati;**“All lesser kings are vassals of a wheel-turning monarch, so the wheel-turning monarch is said to be the foremost of them all. …”*";
P_HTM[1133]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1134]="*sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1135]="*8-10. Candimādisuttatatiyakaṃ**146–148. Candimādisutta*";
P_HTM[1136]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yā kāci tārakarūpānaṃ pabhā, sabbā tā candimappabhāya kalaṃ nāgghanti soḷasiṃ, candappabhā tāsaṃ aggamakkhāyati;**“The radiance of all the stars is not worth a sixteenth part of the moon’s radiance, so the moon’s radiance is said to be the best of them all. …”*";
P_HTM[1137]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1138]="*aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1139]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, saradasamaye viddhe vigatavalāhake deve ādicco nabhaṃ abbhussakkamāno sabbaṃ ākāsagataṃ tamagataṃ abhivihacca bhāsate ca tapate ca virocati ca;**“After the rainy season the sky is clear and cloudless. And when the sun rises, it dispels all the darkness from the sky as it shines and glows and radiates. …”*";
P_HTM[1140]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1141]="*navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1142]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yāni kānici tantāvutānaṃ vatthānaṃ, kāsikavatthaṃ tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati;**“Mendicants, cloth from Kāsī is said to be the best kind of woven cloth. …”*";
P_HTM[1143]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye keci kusalā dhammā, sabbe te appamādamūlakā appamādasamosaraṇā;* **";
P_HTM[1144]="*appamādo tesaṃ dhammānaṃ aggamakkhāyati.* **";
P_HTM[1145]="*Appamattassetaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvessati ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarissati.* **";
P_HTM[1146]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appamatto ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti?* **";
P_HTM[1147]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ … pe … sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1148]="*evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appamatto ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarotī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1149]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1150]="*(Yadapi tathāgataṃ, tadapi vitthāretabbaṃ.)**(These should all be expanded as in the section on the Realized One.)*";
P_HTM[1151]="*Appamādavaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[1152]="*Tathāgataṃ padaṃ kūṭaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[1153]="*mūlaṃ sāro ca vassikaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[1154]="*Rājā candimasūriyā ca,* **";
P_HTM[1155]="*vatthena dasamaṃ padaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1156]="*7. Ānāpānavaggo**Hard Work*";
P_HTM[1157]="*1. Balasuttaṃ**Hard Work*";
P_HTM[1158]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[1159]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci balakaraṇīyā kammantā karīyanti, sabbe te pathaviṃ nissāya pathaviyaṃ patiṭṭhāya evamete balakaraṇīyā kammantā karīyanti;**“Mendicants, all the hard work that gets done depends on the earth and is grounded on the earth.*";
P_HTM[1160]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti.**In the same way, a mendicant develops and cultivates the noble eightfold path depending on and grounded on ethics.*";
P_HTM[1161]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti?**And how does a mendicant grounded on ethics develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path?*";
P_HTM[1162]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ … pe …**It’s when a mendicant develops right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go.*";
P_HTM[1163]="*evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarotīti.**That’s how a mendicant grounded on ethics develops and cultivates the noble eightfold path.”*";
P_HTM[1164]="*(Paragaṅgāpeyyālīvaṇṇiyato paripuṇṇasuttanti vitthāramaggī.)* **";
P_HTM[1165]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci balakaraṇīyā kammantā karīyanti, sabbe te pathaviṃ nissāya pathaviyaṃ patiṭṭhāya evamete balakaraṇīyā kammantā karīyanti;* **";
P_HTM[1166]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti.* **";
P_HTM[1167]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti?* **";
