P_HTM[1997]="*Katame satta?**What seven?*";
P_HTM[1998]="*Satisambojjhaṅgo … pe … upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo.**The awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity.*";
P_HTM[1999]="*Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā kathaṃ bahulīkatā taṇhānirodhāya saṃvattanti?**And how are the seven awakening factors developed and cultivated so as to lead to the cessation of craving?*";
P_HTM[2000]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ … pe … upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ.**It’s when a mendicant develops the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go.*";
P_HTM[2001]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā evaṃ bahulīkatā taṇhānirodhāya saṃvattantī”ti.**This is how the seven awakening factors are developed and cultivated so as to lead to the cessation of craving.”*";
P_HTM[2002]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2003]="*7. Taṇhānirodhasuttaṃ**Helping Penetration*";
P_HTM[2004]="*“Nibbedhabhāgiyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, maggaṃ desessāmi;**“Mendicants, I will teach you a path that helps penetration.*";
P_HTM[2005]="*taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
