P_HTM[2701]="*Aññataraphalasuttaṃ**Livid*";
P_HTM[2702]="*“Vinīlakasaññā, bhikkhave … pe …**“Mendicants, when the perception of a livid corpse is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2703]="*tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2704]="*Mahatthasuttaṃ**Split Open*";
P_HTM[2705]="*“Vicchiddakasaññā, bhikkhave … pe …**“Mendicants, when the perception of a split open corpse is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2706]="*catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2707]="*Yogakkhemasuttaṃ**Bloated*";
P_HTM[2708]="*“Uddhumātakasaññā, bhikkhave … pe …**“Mendicants, when the perception of a bloated corpse is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2709]="*pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2710]="*Saṃvegasuttaṃ**Love*";
P_HTM[2711]="*“Mettā, bhikkhave, bhāvitā … pe …**“Mendicants, when love is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2712]="*chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2713]="*Phāsuvihārasuttaṃ**Compassion*";
P_HTM[2714]="*“Karuṇā, bhikkhave, bhāvitā … pe …**“Mendicants, when compassion is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2715]="*sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2716]="*2. Puḷavakasuttaṃ**Rejoicing*";
P_HTM[2717]="*“Muditā, bhikkhave, bhāvitā … pe …**“Mendicants, when rejoicing is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2718]="*aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2719]="*3. Vinīlakasuttaṃ**Equanimity*";
P_HTM[2720]="*“Upekkhā, bhikkhave, bhāvitā … pe …**“Mendicants, when equanimity is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2721]="*navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2722]="*4. Vicchiddakasuttaṃ**Breathing*";
P_HTM[2723]="*“Ānāpānassati, bhikkhave, bhāvitā … pe …**“Mendicants, when mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2724]="*dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2725]="*Ānāpānavaggo sattamo.* **";
P_HTM[2726]="*Aṭṭhikapuḷavakaṃ vinīlakaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2727]="*Vicchiddakaṃ uddhumātena pañcamaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2728]="*Mettā karuṇā muditā,* **";
P_HTM[2729]="*Upekkhā ānāpānena te dasāti.* **";
P_HTM[2730]="*5. Uddhumātakasuttaṃ**Ugliness*";
P_HTM[2731]="*“Asubhasaññā, bhikkhave … pe …**“Mendicants, when the perception of ugliness is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2732]="*paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2733]="*6. Mettāsuttaṃ**Death*";
P_HTM[2734]="*“Maraṇasaññā, bhikkhave … pe …**“Mendicants, when the perception of death is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2735]="*dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2736]="*7. Karuṇāsuttaṃ**Repulsiveness of Food*";
P_HTM[2737]="*“Āhāre paṭikūlasaññā, bhikkhave … pe …**“Mendicants, when the perception of repulsiveness of food is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2738]="*tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2739]="*8. Muditāsuttaṃ**Dissatisfaction*";
P_HTM[2740]="*“Sabbaloke anabhiratisaññā, bhikkhave … pe …**“Mendicants, when the perception of dissatisfaction with the whole world is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2741]="*catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2742]="*9. Upekkhāsuttaṃ**Impermanence*";
P_HTM[2743]="*“Aniccasaññā, bhikkhave … pe …**“Mendicants, when the perception of impermanence is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
P_HTM[2744]="*pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2745]="*10. Ānāpānasuttaṃ**Suffering in Impermanence*";
P_HTM[2746]="*“Anicce dukkhasaññā, bhikkhave … pe …**“Mendicants, when the perception of suffering in impermanence is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial. …”*";
