P_HTM[5179]="*6. Gaṅgāpeyyālavaggo**Esanāvagga*";
P_HTM[5180]="*1-10. Oghādisuttadasakaṃ**35–44. Esanādisuttadasaka*";
P_HTM[5181]="*“Tisso imā, bhikkhave, esanā.**“Mendicants, there are these three searches.*";
P_HTM[5182]="*Katamā tisso?**What three?*";
P_HTM[5183]="*Kāmesanā, bhavesanā, brahmacariyesanā—**The search for sensual pleasures, the search for continued existence, and the search for a spiritual path.*";
P_HTM[5184]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, tisso esanā.**These are the three searches.*";
P_HTM[5185]="*Imāsaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tissannaṃ esanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya cattāro sammappadhānā bhāvetabbā.**The four right efforts should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these three searches.*";
P_HTM[5186]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5187]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ … pe …**It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise. …*";
P_HTM[5188]="*uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati.**so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are completed by development.*";
P_HTM[5189]="*Imāsaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tissannaṃ esanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya ime cattāro sammappadhānā bhāvetabbā”ti.**These four right efforts should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these three searches.”*";
P_HTM[5190]="*(Vitthāretabbaṃ.)**(To be expanded as in SN 45.161–170.)*";
P_HTM[5191]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
