P_HTM[5197]="*9. Esanāvaggo**Oghavagga*";
P_HTM[5198]="*1-12. Balādisuttadvādasakaṃ**45–54. Oghādisutta*";
P_HTM[5199]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, uddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni.**“Mendicants, there are five higher fetters.*";
P_HTM[5200]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5201]="*Rūparāgo, arūparāgo, māno, uddhaccaṃ, avijjā—**Desire for rebirth in the realm of luminous form, desire for rebirth in the formless realm, conceit, restlessness, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[5202]="*imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañcuddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni.**These are the five higher fetters.*";
P_HTM[5203]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya cattāro sammappadhānā bhāvetabbā.**The four right efforts should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters.*";
P_HTM[5204]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5205]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ … pe …**It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise. …*";
P_HTM[5206]="*uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati.**so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are completed by development.*";
P_HTM[5207]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya ime cattāro sammappadhānā bhāvetabbā”ti.**These four right efforts should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters.”*";
