P_HTM[5217]="*10. Oghavaggo**Gaṅgāpeyyālavagga*";
P_HTM[5218]="*1-10. Oghādisuttadasakaṃ**1–12. Balādisutta*";
P_HTM[5219]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, balāni.**“Mendicants, there are these five powers.*";
P_HTM[5220]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5221]="*Saddhābalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, satibalaṃ, samādhibalaṃ, paññābalaṃ—**The powers of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[5222]="*imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca balānīti.**These are the five powers.*";
P_HTM[5223]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gaṅgā nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā;**The Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines to the east.*";
P_HTM[5224]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañca balāni bhāvento pañca balāni bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro.**In the same way, a mendicant who develops and cultivates the five powers slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[5225]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañca balāni bhāvento pañca balāni bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro?**And how does a mendicant who develops the five powers slant, slope, and incline to extinguishment?*";
P_HTM[5226]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhābalaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ,**It’s when a mendicant develops the powers of faith,*";
P_HTM[5227]="*vīriyabalaṃ … pe …**energy,*";
P_HTM[5228]="*satibalaṃ …**mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[5229]="*samādhibalaṃ …**immersion,*";
P_HTM[5230]="*paññābalaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ.**and wisdom, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go.*";
P_HTM[5231]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañca balāni bhāvento pañca balāni bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro”ti.**That’s how a mendicant who develops and cultivates the five powers slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment.”*";
