P_HTM[5314]="*51. Iddhipādasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[5315]="*7. Bhikkhusuttaṃ**From the Near Shore*";
P_HTM[5316]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā apārā pāraṃ gamanāya saṃvattanti.**“Mendicants, when these four bases of psychic power are developed and cultivated they lead to going from the near shore to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5317]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5318]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[5319]="*vīriyasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to energy, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[5320]="*cittasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to mental development, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[5321]="*vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti.**They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to inquiry, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[5322]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā apārā pāraṃ gamanāya saṃvattantī”ti.**When these four bases of psychic power are developed and cultivated they lead to going from the near shore to the far shore.”*";
P_HTM[5323]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5324]="*8. Buddhasuttaṃ**Missed Out*";
P_HTM[5325]="*“Yesaṃ kesañci, bhikkhave, cattāro iddhipādā viraddhā, viraddho tesaṃ ariyo maggo sammā dukkhakkhayagāmī.**“Mendicants, whoever has missed out on the four bases of psychic power has missed out on the noble path to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[5326]="*Yesaṃ kesañci, bhikkhave, cattāro iddhipādā āraddhā, āraddho tesaṃ ariyo maggo sammā dukkhakkhayagāmī.**Whoever has undertaken the four bases of psychic power has undertaken the noble path to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[5327]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5328]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm …*";
P_HTM[5329]="*vīriyasamādhi … pe …**energy …*";
P_HTM[5330]="*cittasamādhi … pe …**mental development …*";
P_HTM[5331]="*vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti.**inquiry, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[5332]="*Yesaṃ kesañci, bhikkhave, ime cattāro iddhipādā viraddhā, viraddho tesaṃ ariyo maggo sammā dukkhakkhayagāmī.**Whoever has missed out on these four bases of psychic power has missed out on the noble path to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[5333]="*Yesaṃ kesañci, bhikkhave, ime cattāro iddhipādā āraddhā, āraddho tesaṃ ariyo maggo sammā dukkhakkhayagāmī”ti.**Whoever has undertaken these four bases of psychic power has undertaken the noble path to the complete ending of suffering.”*";
P_HTM[5334]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5335]="*9. Ñāṇasuttaṃ**A Noble One*";
P_HTM[5336]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ariyā niyyānikā niyyanti takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāya.**“Mendicants, when these four bases of psychic power are developed and cultivated they are noble and emancipating, and bring one who practices them to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[5337]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5338]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm …*";
P_HTM[5339]="*vīriyasamādhi … pe …**energy …*";
P_HTM[5340]="*cittasamādhi … pe …**mental development …*";
P_HTM[5341]="*vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti.**inquiry, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[5342]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ariyā niyyānikā niyyanti takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāyā”ti.**When these four bases of psychic power are developed and cultivated they are noble and emancipating, and bring one who practices them to the complete ending of suffering.”*";
P_HTM[5343]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5344]="*10. Cetiyasuttaṃ**Disillusionment*";
P_HTM[5345]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattanti.**“Mendicants, these four bases of psychic power, when developed and cultivated, lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[5346]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5347]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm …*";
P_HTM[5348]="*vīriyasamādhi … pe …**energy …*";
P_HTM[5349]="*cittasamādhi … pe …**mental development …*";
P_HTM[5350]="*vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti.**inquiry, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[5351]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattantī”ti.**These four bases of psychic power, when developed and cultivated, lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.”*";
P_HTM[5352]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5353]="*8. Oghavaggo**At the Cāpāla Shrine*";
P_HTM[5354]="*1. Pubbasuttaṃ**Partly*";
P_HTM[5355]="*“Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā iddhipadesaṃ abhinipphādesuṃ sabbe te catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā.**“Mendicants, all the ascetics and brahmins in the past who have partly manifested psychic powers have done so by developing and cultivating the four bases of psychic power.*";
P_HTM[5356]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā iddhipadesaṃ abhinipphādessanti sabbe te catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā.**All the ascetics and brahmins in the future who will partly manifest psychic powers will do so by developing and cultivating the four bases of psychic power.*";
P_HTM[5357]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā iddhipadesaṃ abhinipphādenti sabbe te catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā.**All the ascetics and brahmins in the present who are partly manifesting psychic powers do so by developing and cultivating the four bases of psychic power.*";
P_HTM[5358]="*Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5359]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm …*";
P_HTM[5360]="*vīriyasamādhi … pe …**energy …*";
P_HTM[5361]="*cittasamādhi … pe …**mental development …*";
P_HTM[5362]="*vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti.**inquiry, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[5363]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā iddhipadesaṃ abhinipphādesuṃ, sabbe te imesaṃyeva catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā.**All the ascetics and brahmins in the past who have partly manifested psychic powers have done so by developing and cultivating these four bases of psychic power.*";
P_HTM[5364]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā iddhipadesaṃ abhinipphādessanti, sabbe te imesaṃyeva catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā.**All the ascetics and brahmins in the future who will partly manifest psychic powers will do so by developing and cultivating these four bases of psychic power.*";
P_HTM[5365]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā iddhipadesaṃ abhinipphādenti, sabbe te imesaṃyeva catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā”ti.**All the ascetics and brahmins in the present who are partly manifesting psychic powers do so by developing and cultivating these four bases of psychic power.”*";
P_HTM[5366]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5367]="*2. Mahapphalasuttaṃ**Completely*";
P_HTM[5368]="*“Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā samattaṃ iddhiṃ abhinipphādesuṃ, sabbe te catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā.**“Mendicants, all the ascetics and brahmins in the past who have completely manifested psychic powers have done so by developing and cultivating the four bases of psychic power.*";
P_HTM[5369]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā samattaṃ iddhiṃ abhinipphādessanti, sabbe te catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā.**All the ascetics and brahmins in the future who will completely manifest psychic powers will do so by developing and cultivating the four bases of psychic power.*";
P_HTM[5370]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā samattaṃ iddhiṃ abhinipphādenti, sabbe te catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā.**All the ascetics and brahmins in the present who are completely manifesting psychic powers do so by developing and cultivating the four bases of psychic power.*";
P_HTM[5371]="*Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5372]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm …*";
