P_HTM[6190]="*“Asekhenāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā cattāro satipaṭṭhānā upasampajja vihātabbā.**“Reverend Sāriputta, a mendicant who is an adept should enter and remain in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[6191]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6192]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6193]="*vedanāsu … pe …**They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …*";
P_HTM[6194]="*citte … pe …**mind …*";
P_HTM[6195]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ—**principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6196]="*asekhenāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā ime cattāro satipaṭṭhānā upasampajja vihātabbā”ti.**A mendicant who is an adept should enter and remain in these four kinds of mindfulness meditation.”*";
P_HTM[6197]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6198]="*5. Ṭhānasuttaṃ**At Thorny Wood (3rd)*";
P_HTM[6199]="*Sāketanidānaṃ.**At Sāketa.*";
P_HTM[6200]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca:**Sāriputta said to Anuruddha:*";
P_HTM[6201]="*“katamesaṃ āyasmā anuruddho dhammānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā mahābhiññataṃ patto”ti?**“What things has Venerable Anuruddha developed and cultivated to attain great direct knowledge?”*";
P_HTM[6202]="*“Catunnaṃ khvāhaṃ, āvuso, satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā mahābhiññataṃ patto.**“Reverend, I attained great direct knowledge by developing and cultivating the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[6203]="*Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6204]="*Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, kāye kāyānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**I meditate observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6205]="*vedanāsu … pe …**I meditate observing an aspect of feelings …*";
P_HTM[6206]="*citte … pe …**mind …*";
P_HTM[6207]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ—**principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6208]="*imesaṃ khvāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā mahābhiññataṃ patto.**I attained great direct knowledge by developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[6209]="*Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā sahassaṃ lokaṃ abhijānāmī”ti.**And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I directly know the entire galaxy.”*";
P_HTM[6210]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6211]="*6. Kammasamādānasuttaṃ**The Ending of Craving*";
P_HTM[6212]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6213]="*Tatra kho āyasmā anuruddho bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Venerable Anuruddha addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6214]="*“āvuso bhikkhavo”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[6215]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato anuruddhassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[6216]="*Āyasmā anuruddho etadavoca:**Anuruddha said this:*";
P_HTM[6217]="*“Cattārome, āvuso, satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā taṇhākkhayāya saṃvattanti.**“Reverends, when these four kinds of mindfulness meditation are developed and cultivated they lead to the ending of craving.*";
P_HTM[6218]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6219]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati … pe …**It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body …*";
P_HTM[6220]="*vedanāsu … pe …**feelings …*";
P_HTM[6221]="*citte … pe …**mind …*";
P_HTM[6222]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ—**principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6223]="*ime kho, āvuso, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā taṇhākkhayāya saṃvattantī”ti.**When these four kinds of mindfulness meditation are developed and cultivated they lead to the ending of craving.”*";
P_HTM[6224]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6225]="*7. Sabbatthagāminisuttaṃ**The Frankincense*";
P_HTM[6226]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā anuruddho sāvatthiyaṃ viharati salaḷāgāre.**At one time Venerable Anuruddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the frankincense-tree hut.*";
P_HTM[6227]="*Tatra kho āyasmā anuruddho bhikkhū āmantesi … pe … etadavoca:**There Venerable Anuruddha addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6228]="*“seyyathāpi, āvuso, gaṅgā nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā.**“Reverends, suppose that, although the Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines to the east,*";
P_HTM[6229]="*Atha mahājanakāyo āgaccheyya kudālapiṭakaṃ ādāya:**a large crowd were to come along with a spade and basket, saying:*";
P_HTM[6230]="*‘mayaṃ imaṃ gaṅgānadiṃ pacchāninnaṃ karissāma pacchāpoṇaṃ pacchāpabbhāran’ti.**‘We’ll make this Ganges river slant, slope, and incline to the west!’*";
P_HTM[6231]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññathāvuso, api nu so mahājanakāyo gaṅgānadiṃ pacchāninnaṃ kareyya pacchāpoṇaṃ pacchāpabbhāran”ti?**What do you think, reverends? Would they succeed?”*";
P_HTM[6232]="*“No hetaṃ, āvuso”.**“No, reverend.*";
P_HTM[6233]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6234]="*“Gaṅgā, āvuso, nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā.**The Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines to the east.*";
P_HTM[6235]="*Sā na sukarā pacchāninnaṃ kātuṃ pacchāpoṇaṃ pacchāpabbhāraṃ.**It’s not easy to make it slant, slope, and incline to the west.*";
P_HTM[6236]="*Yāvadeva ca pana so mahājanakāyo kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**That large crowd will eventually get weary and frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[6237]="*“Evameva kho, āvuso, bhikkhuṃ cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bhāventaṃ cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bahulīkarontaṃ rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā mittā vā amaccā vā ñātī vā sālohitā vā bhogehi abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyyuṃ:**“In the same way, while a mendicant develops and cultivates the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, if rulers or their ministers, friends or colleagues, relatives or family should invite them to accept wealth, saying:*";
P_HTM[6238]="*‘ehambho purisa, kiṃ te ime kāsāvā anudahanti?**‘Please, mister, why let these ocher robes torment you?*";
P_HTM[6239]="*Kiṃ muṇḍo kapālamanusañcarasi?**Why follow the practice of shaving your head and carrying an alms bowl?*";
P_HTM[6240]="*Ehi hīnāyāvattitvā bhoge ca bhuñjassu puññāni ca karohī’ti.**Come, return to a lesser life, enjoy wealth, and make merit!’*";
P_HTM[6241]="*So vata, āvuso, bhikkhu cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bhāvento cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bahulīkaronto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**It’s simply impossible for a mendicant who is developing and cultivating the four kinds of mindfulness meditation to reject the training and return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[6242]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6243]="*Yañhi taṃ, āvuso, cittaṃ dīgharattaṃ vivekaninnaṃ vivekapoṇaṃ vivekapabbhāraṃ taṃ vata hīnāyāvattissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**Because for a long time that mendicant’s mind has slanted, sloped, and inclined to seclusion. So it’s impossible for them to return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[6244]="*Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bhāveti, cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bahulīkarotīti?**And how does a mendicant develop the four kinds of mindfulness meditation?*";
P_HTM[6245]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati … pe …**It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body …*";
P_HTM[6246]="*vedanāsu … pe …**feelings …*";
P_HTM[6247]="*citte … pe …**mind …*";
P_HTM[6248]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6249]="*Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bhāveti, cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bahulīkarotī”ti.**That’s how a mendicant develops and cultivates the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.”*";
P_HTM[6250]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6251]="*8. Nānādhātusuttaṃ**In Ambapālī’s Wood*";
P_HTM[6252]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca anuruddho āyasmā ca sāriputto vesāliyaṃ viharanti ambapālivane.**At one time the venerables Anuruddha and Sāriputta were staying near Vesālī, in Ambapālī’s Wood.*";
P_HTM[6253]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca:**Then in the late afternoon, Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to Anuruddha, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6254]="*“Vippasannāni kho te, āvuso anuruddha, indriyāni, parisuddho mukhavaṇṇo pariyodāto.**“Reverend Anuruddha, your faculties are so very clear, and your complexion is pure and bright.*";
P_HTM[6255]="*Katamenāyasmā anuruddho vihārena etarahi bahulaṃ viharatī”ti?**What kind of meditation are you usually practicing these days?”*";
P_HTM[6256]="*“Catūsu khvāhaṃ, āvuso, satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto etarahi bahulaṃ viharāmi.**“These days, reverend, I usually meditate with my mind firmly established in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[6257]="*Katamesu catūsu?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6258]="*Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, kāye kāyānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**I meditate observing an aspect of the body …*";
P_HTM[6259]="*vedanāsu … pe …**feelings …*";
P_HTM[6260]="*citte … pe …**mind …*";
P_HTM[6261]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ—**principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6262]="*imesu khvāhaṃ, āvuso, catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto etarahi bahulaṃ viharāmi.**These days I usually meditate with my mind firmly established in these four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[6263]="*Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, so imesu catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto bahulaṃ viharatī”ti.**A mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment—usually meditates with their mind firmly established in these four kinds of mindfulness meditation.”*";
P_HTM[6264]="*“Lābhā vata no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ vata no, āvuso.**“We’re so fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[6265]="*Ye mayaṃ āyasmato anuruddhassa sammukhāva assumha āsabhiṃ vācaṃ bhāsamānassā”ti.**to have heard such a dramatic statement in the presence of Venerable Anuruddha.”*";
P_HTM[6266]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6267]="*9. Nānādhimuttisuttaṃ**Gravely Ill*";
P_HTM[6268]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā anuruddho sāvatthiyaṃ viharati andhavanasmiṃ ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.**At one time Venerable Anuruddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Dark Forest. And he was sick, suffering, gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[6269]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to Venerable Anuruddha, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6270]="*“Katamenāyasmato anuruddhassa vihārena viharato uppannā sārīrikā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhantī”ti?**“What meditation does Venerable Anuruddha practice so that physical pain doesn’t occupy his mind?”*";
P_HTM[6271]="*“Catūsu kho me, āvuso, satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittassa viharato uppannā sārīrikā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti.**“Reverends, I meditate with my mind firmly established in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation so that physical pain doesn’t occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6272]="*Katamesu catūsu?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6273]="*Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, kāye kāyānupassī viharāmi … pe …**I meditate observing an aspect of the body …*";
P_HTM[6274]="*vedanāsu … pe …**feelings …*";
P_HTM[6275]="*citte … pe …**mind …*";
P_HTM[6276]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ—**principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6277]="*imesu kho me, āvuso, catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittassa viharato uppannā sārīrikā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhantī”ti.**I meditate with my mind firmly established in these four kinds of mindfulness meditation so that physical pain doesn’t occupy my mind.”*";
P_HTM[6278]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6279]="*Rahogatavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[6280]="*Rahogatena dve vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[6281]="*sutanu kaṇḍakī tayo;* **";
P_HTM[6282]="*Taṇhākkhayasalaḷāgāraṃ,* **";
P_HTM[6283]="*ambapāli ca gilānanti.* **";
P_HTM[6284]="*10. Indriyaparopariyattasuttaṃ**A Thousand Eons*";
P_HTM[6285]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā anuruddho sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time Venerable Anuruddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[6286]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā anuruddhena saddhiṃ … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to Venerable Anuruddha, exchanged greetings with him … and said:*";
P_HTM[6287]="*“Katamesaṃ āyasmā anuruddho dhammānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā mahābhiññataṃ patto”ti?**“What things has Venerable Anuruddha developed and cultivated to attain great direct knowledge?”*";
P_HTM[6288]="*“Catunnaṃ khvāhaṃ, āvuso, satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā mahābhiññataṃ patto.**“Reverends, I attained great direct knowledge by developing and cultivating the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[6289]="*Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6290]="*Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, kāye kāyānupassī viharāmi … pe …**I meditate observing an aspect of the body …*";
P_HTM[6291]="*vedanāsu … pe …**feelings …*";
P_HTM[6292]="*citte … pe …**mind …*";
P_HTM[6293]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ—**principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6294]="*imesaṃ khvāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā mahābhiññataṃ patto.**I attained great direct knowledge by developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[6295]="*Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā kappasahassaṃ anussarāmī”ti.**And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I recollect a thousand eons.”*";
P_HTM[6296]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6297]="*11. Jhānādisuttaṃ**Psychic Powers*";
P_HTM[6298]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhomi—ekopi hutvā bahudhā homi … pe … yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vattemī”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I wield the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying myself and becoming one again … controlling the body as far as the Brahmā realm.”*";
P_HTM[6299]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6300]="*12. Pubbenivāsasuttaṃ**Clairaudience*";
P_HTM[6301]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇāmi dibbe ca mānuse ca ye dūre santike cā”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that, with clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, I hear both kinds of sounds, human and divine, whether near or far.”*";
P_HTM[6302]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6303]="*13. Dibbacakkhusuttaṃ**Comprehending the Mind*";
P_HTM[6304]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānāmi … pe … avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘avimuttaṃ cittan’ti pajānāmī”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I understand the minds of other beings and individuals, having comprehended them with my mind. I understand mind with greed as ‘mind with greed’ … I understand unfreed mind as ‘unfreed mind’.”*";
P_HTM[6305]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6306]="*14. Āsavakkhayasuttaṃ**Possible*";
P_HTM[6307]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā ṭhānañca ṭhānato aṭṭhānañca aṭṭhānato yathābhūtaṃ pajānāmī”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I truly understand the possible as possible and the impossible as impossible.”*";
P_HTM[6308]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6309]="*2. Dutiyavaggo**A Thousand*";
P_HTM[6310]="*1-12. Jhānādisuttadvādasakaṃ**The Results of Deeds Undertaken*";
P_HTM[6311]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā atītānāgatapaccuppannānaṃ kammasamādānānaṃ ṭhānaso hetuso vipākaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāmī”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I truly understand the result of deeds undertaken in the past, future, and present in terms of causes and reasons.”*";
P_HTM[6312]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6313]="*1. Veḷudvāravaggo**A Thousand*";
P_HTM[6314]="*1-10. Oghādisuttaṃ**Where All Paths of Practice Lead*";
P_HTM[6315]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā sabbatthagāminippaṭipadaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāmī”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I truly understand where all paths of practice lead.”*";
P_HTM[6316]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6317]="*2. Rājakārāmavaggo**A Thousand*";
P_HTM[6318]="*1. Ekadhammasuttaṃ**Diverse Elements*";
P_HTM[6319]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā anekadhātunānādhātulokaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāmī”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I truly understand the world with its many and diverse elements.”*";
P_HTM[6320]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6321]="*2. Bojjhaṅgasuttaṃ**Diverse Beliefs*";
P_HTM[6322]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā sattānaṃ nānādhimuttikataṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāmī”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I truly understand the diverse beliefs of sentient beings.”*";
P_HTM[6323]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6324]="*3. Suddhikasuttaṃ**Comprehending the Faculties of Others*";
P_HTM[6325]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ indriyaparopariyattaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāmī”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I truly understand the faculties of other sentient beings and other individuals after comprehending them with my mind.”*";
P_HTM[6326]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6327]="*4. Paṭhamaphalasuttaṃ**Absorptions, Etc.*";
P_HTM[6328]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā jhānavimokkhasamādhisamāpattīnaṃ saṃkilesaṃ vodānaṃ vuṭṭhānaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāmī”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I truly understand corruption, cleansing, and emergence regarding the absorptions, liberations, immersions, and attainments.”*";
P_HTM[6329]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6330]="*5. Dutiyaphalasuttaṃ**Past Lives*";
P_HTM[6331]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmī”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I recollect my many kinds of past lives, with features and details.”*";
P_HTM[6332]="*Dvādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6333]="*6. Ariṭṭhasuttaṃ**Clairvoyance*";
P_HTM[6334]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne … pe … iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena yathākammūpage satte pajānāmī”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.”*";
P_HTM[6335]="*Terasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6336]="*7. Mahākappinasuttaṃ**The Ending of Defilements*";
P_HTM[6337]="*“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmī”ti.**“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And I live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending of defilements.”*";
P_HTM[6338]="*Cuddasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6339]="*Dutiyo vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[6340]="*Mahābhiññaṃ iddhi dibbaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[6341]="*Cetopariyaṃ ṭhānaṃ kammaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6342]="*Sabbatthadhātudhimutti,* **";
P_HTM[6343]="*Indriyaṃ jhānaṃ tisso vijjāti.* **";
P_HTM[6344]="*Anuruddhasaṃyuttaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.**The Linked Discourses with Anuruddha are the eighth section.*";
P_HTM[6345]="*53. Jhānasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[6346]="*8. Padīpopamasuttaṃ**1–12. Jhānādisutta*";
P_HTM[6347]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6348]="*Tatra kho … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6349]="*“cattārome, bhikkhave, jhānā.**“Mendicants, there are these four absorptions.*";
P_HTM[6350]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6351]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[6352]="*Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[6353]="*Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[6354]="*Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[6355]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro jhānāti.**These are the four absorptions.*";
P_HTM[6356]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gaṅgā nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā;**The Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines to the east.*";
P_HTM[6357]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro jhāne bhāvento cattāro jhāne bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro.**In the same way, a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four absorptions slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[6358]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro jhāne bhāvento cattāro jhāne bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro?**And how does a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four absorptions slant, slope, and incline to extinguishment?*";
P_HTM[6359]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[6360]="*Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[6361]="*tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[6362]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[6363]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro jhāne bhāvento cattāro jhāne bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro”ti.**That’s how a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four absorptions slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment.”*";
P_HTM[6364]="*Dvādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6365]="*Gaṅgāpeyyālavaggo paṭhamo.**(To be expanded for each of the different rivers as in SN 45.91–102.)*";
P_HTM[6366]="*Cha pācīnato ninnā,**Six on slanting to the east,*";
P_HTM[6367]="*cha ninnā ca samuddato;**and six on slanting to the ocean;*";
P_HTM[6368]="*Dvete cha dvādasa honti,**these two sixes make twelve,*";
P_HTM[6369]="*vaggo tena pavuccatīti.**and that’s how this chapter is recited.*";
P_HTM[6370]="*9. Vesālīsuttaṃ**13. Appamādavagga*";
P_HTM[6371]="*(Appamādavaggo vitthāretabbo.)**(To be expanded as in the chapter on diligence at SN 45.139–148.)*";
P_HTM[6372]="*Tathāgataṃ padaṃ kūṭaṃ,**The Realized One, footprint, roof peak,*";
P_HTM[6373]="*mūlaṃ sāro ca vassikaṃ;**roots, heartwood, jasmine,*";
P_HTM[6374]="*Rājā candimasūriyā,**monarch, sun and moon,*";
P_HTM[6375]="*vatthena dasamaṃ padanti.**and cloth is the tenth.*";
P_HTM[6376]="*10. Kimilasuttaṃ**23. Balakaraṇīyavagga*";
P_HTM[6377]="*(Balakaraṇīyavaggo vitthāretabbo.)**(To be expanded as in the chapter on hard work at SN 45.149–160.)*";
P_HTM[6378]="*Balaṃ bījañca nāgo ca,**Hard work, seeds, and dragons,*";
P_HTM[6379]="*rukkho kumbhena sūkiyā;**a tree, a pot, and a spike,*";
P_HTM[6380]="*Ākāsena ca dve meghā,**the sky, and two on clouds,*";
P_HTM[6381]="*nāvā āgantukā nadīti.**a ship, a guest house, and a river.*";
P_HTM[6382]="*3. Saraṇānivaggo**Esanāvagga*";
P_HTM[6383]="*1. Icchānaṅgalasuttaṃ**35. Esanāvagga*";
P_HTM[6384]="*(Esanāvaggo vitthāretabbo.)**(To be expanded as in the chapter on searches at SN 45.161–170.)*";
P_HTM[6385]="*Esanā vidhā āsavo,**Searches, discriminations, defilements,*";
P_HTM[6386]="*Bhavo ca dukkhatā tisso;**states of existence, three kinds of suffering,*";
P_HTM[6387]="*Khilaṃ malañca nīgho ca,**barrenness, stains, and troubles,*";
P_HTM[6388]="*Vedanā taṇhā tasinā cāti.**feelings, craving, and thirst.*";
P_HTM[6389]="*2. Kaṅkheyyasuttaṃ**45–54. Oghādisutta*";
P_HTM[6390]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, uddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni.**“Mendicants, there are five higher fetters.*";
P_HTM[6391]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[6392]="*Rūparāgo, arūparāgo, māno, uddhaccaṃ, avijjā—**Desire for rebirth in the realm of luminous form, desire for rebirth in the formless realm, conceit, restlessness, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[6393]="*imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañcuddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni.**These are the five higher fetters.*";
P_HTM[6394]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya cattāro jhānā bhāvetabbā.**The four absorptions should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters.*";
P_HTM[6395]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6396]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[6397]="*Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[6398]="*tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[6399]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[6400]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya ime cattāro jhānā bhāvetabbā”ti vitthāretabbaṃ.**These four absorptions should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters.”*";
P_HTM[6401]="*(Yathā maggasaṃyuttaṃ tathā vitthāretabbaṃ.)**(To be expanded as in the Linked Discourses on the Path at SN 45.171–180.)*";
P_HTM[6402]="*Oghavaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[6403]="*Ogho yogo upādānaṃ,**Floods, bonds, grasping,*";
P_HTM[6404]="*ganthā anusayena ca;**ties, and underlying tendencies,*";
P_HTM[6405]="*Kāmaguṇā nīvaraṇā,**kinds of sensual stimulation, hindrances,*";
P_HTM[6406]="*khandhā oruddhambhāgiyāti.**aggregates, and fetters high and low.*";
P_HTM[6407]="*Jhānasaṃyuttaṃ navamaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on Absorption are the ninth section.*";
P_HTM[6408]="*54. Ānāpānasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[6409]="*3. Paṭhamaānandasuttaṃ**One Thing*";
P_HTM[6410]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6411]="*Tatra kho … pe … etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[6412]="*“ekadhammo, bhikkhave, bhāvito bahulīkato mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso.**“Mendicants, when one thing is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[6413]="*Katamo ekadhammo?**What one thing?*";
P_HTM[6414]="*Ānāpānassati.**Mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6415]="*Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassati kathaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā?**And how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated to be very fruitful and beneficial?*";
P_HTM[6416]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut. They sit down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[6417]="*So satova assasati, satova passasati.**Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out.*";
P_HTM[6418]="*Dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, dīghaṃ vā passasanto ‘dīghaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti;**When breathing in heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing in heavily.’ When breathing out heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing out heavily.’*";
P_HTM[6419]="*rassaṃ vā assasanto ‘rassaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā passasanto ‘rassaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti;**When breathing in lightly they know: ‘I’m breathing in lightly.’ When breathing out lightly they know: ‘I’m breathing out lightly.’*";
P_HTM[6420]="*‘sabbakāyappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘sabbakāyappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing the whole body.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out experiencing the whole body.’*";
P_HTM[6421]="*‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in stilling physical processes.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out stilling physical processes.’*";
P_HTM[6422]="*‘Pītippaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘pītippaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing rapture.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out experiencing rapture.’*";
P_HTM[6423]="*‘sukhappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘sukhappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing bliss.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out experiencing bliss.’*";
P_HTM[6424]="*‘cittasaṅkhārappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘cittasaṅkhārappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing mental processes.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out experiencing mental processes.’*";
P_HTM[6425]="*‘passambhayaṃ cittasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘passambhayaṃ cittasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in stilling mental processes.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out stilling mental processes.’*";
P_HTM[6426]="*‘Cittappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘cittappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing the mind.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out experiencing the mind.’*";
P_HTM[6427]="*‘abhippamodayaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘abhippamodayaṃ cittaṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in gladdening the mind.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out gladdening the mind.’*";
P_HTM[6428]="*‘samādahaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘samādahaṃ cittaṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in immersing the mind in samādhi.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out immersing the mind in samādhi.’*";
P_HTM[6429]="*‘vimocayaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘vimocayaṃ cittaṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in freeing the mind.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out freeing the mind.’*";
P_HTM[6430]="*‘aniccānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing impermanence.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing impermanence.’*";
P_HTM[6431]="*‘Aniccānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;* **";
P_HTM[6432]="*‘virāgānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘virāgānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing fading away.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing fading away.’*";
P_HTM[6433]="*‘nirodhānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘nirodhānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing cessation.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing cessation.’*";
P_HTM[6434]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6435]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassati evaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā”ti.**Mindfulness of breathing, when developed and cultivated in this way, is very fruitful and beneficial.”*";
P_HTM[6436]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6437]="*4. Dutiyaānandasuttaṃ**Awakening Factors*";
P_HTM[6438]="*“Ānāpānassati, bhikkhave, bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā.**“Mendicants, when mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[6439]="*Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassati kathaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā?**And how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated to be very fruitful and beneficial?*";
P_HTM[6440]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ānāpānassatisahagataṃ satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ, ānāpānassatisahagataṃ dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pe … ānāpānassatisahagataṃ upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ.**It’s when a mendicant develops mindfulness of breathing together with the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go.*";
P_HTM[6441]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassati evaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā”ti.**Mindfulness of breathing, when developed and cultivated in this way, is very fruitful and beneficial.”*";
P_HTM[6442]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6443]="*5. Paṭhamabhikkhusuttaṃ**Plain Version*";
P_HTM[6444]="*“Ānāpānassati, bhikkhave, bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā.**“Mendicants, when mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[6445]="*Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassati kathaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā?**And how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated to be very fruitful and beneficial?*";
P_HTM[6446]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut. They sit down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[6447]="*So satova assasati, satova passasati … pe …**Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out. …*";
P_HTM[6448]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6449]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassati evaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā”ti.**Mindfulness of breathing, when developed and cultivated in this way, is very fruitful and beneficial.”*";
P_HTM[6450]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6451]="*6. Dutiyabhikkhusuttaṃ**Fruits (1st)*";
P_HTM[6452]="*“Ānāpānassati, bhikkhave, bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā.**“Mendicants, when mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[6453]="*Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassati kathaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā?**And how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated to be very fruitful and beneficial?*";
P_HTM[6454]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut. They sit down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[6455]="*So satova assasati, satova passasati … pe …**Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out. …*";
P_HTM[6456]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6457]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassati evaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā.**Mindfulness of breathing, when developed and cultivated in this way, is very fruitful and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[6458]="*Evaṃ bhāvitāya kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatiyā evaṃ bahulīkatāya dvinnaṃ phalānaṃ aññataraṃ phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—**When mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated in this way you can expect one of two results:*";
P_HTM[6459]="*diṭṭheva dhamme aññā, sati vā upādisese anāgāmitā”ti.**enlightenment in the present life, or if there’s something left over, non-return.”*";
P_HTM[6460]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6461]="*7. Saṃyojanappahānasuttaṃ**Fruits (2nd)*";
P_HTM[6462]="*“Ānāpānassati, bhikkhave, bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā.**“Mendicants, when mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[6463]="*Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassati kathaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā?**And how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated to be very fruitful and beneficial?*";
P_HTM[6464]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut. They sit down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[6465]="*So satova assasati, satova passasati … pe …**Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out. …*";
P_HTM[6466]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6467]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassati evaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā.**Mindfulness of breathing, when developed and cultivated in this way, is very fruitful and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[6468]="*Evaṃ bhāvitāya kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatiyā evaṃ bahulīkatāya satta phalā sattānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā.**When mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated in this way you can expect seven fruits and benefits.*";
P_HTM[6469]="*Katame satta phalā sattānisaṃsā?**What seven?*";
P_HTM[6470]="*Diṭṭheva dhamme paṭikacca aññaṃ ārādheti;**You attain enlightenment early on in this very life.*";
P_HTM[6471]="*no ce diṭṭheva dhamme paṭikacca aññaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[6472]="*Atha maraṇakāle aññaṃ ārādheti;**If not, you attain enlightenment at the time of death.*";
P_HTM[6473]="*no ce diṭṭheva dhamme paṭikacca aññaṃ ārādheti, no ce maraṇakāle aññaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[6474]="*Atha pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā antarāparinibbāyī hoti …**If not, with the ending of the five lower fetters you’re extinguished in between one life and the next …*";
P_HTM[6475]="*upahaccaparinibbāyī hoti …**you’re extinguished upon landing …*";
P_HTM[6476]="*asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti …**you’re extinguished without extra effort …*";
P_HTM[6477]="*sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti …**you’re extinguished with extra effort …*";
P_HTM[6478]="*uddhaṃsoto hoti akaniṭṭhagāmī—**you head upstream, going to the Akaniṭṭha realm …*";
P_HTM[6479]="*evaṃ bhāvitāya kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatiyā evaṃ bahulīkatāya ime satta phalā sattānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā”ti.**When mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated in this way you can expect these seven fruits and benefits.”*";
P_HTM[6480]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6481]="*8. Anusayasamugghātasuttaṃ**With Ariṭṭha*";
P_HTM[6482]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6483]="*Tatra kho bhagavā … pe … etadavoca:**There the Buddha … said:*";
P_HTM[6484]="*“bhāvetha no tumhe bhikkhave, ānāpānassatin”ti?**“Mendicants, do you develop mindfulness of breathing?”*";
P_HTM[6485]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ariṭṭho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Ariṭṭha said to him:*";
P_HTM[6486]="*“ahaṃ kho, bhante, bhāvemi ānāpānassatin”ti.**“Sir, I develop mindfulness of breathing.”*";
P_HTM[6487]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, ariṭṭha, bhāvesi ānāpānassatin”ti?**“But mendicant, how do you develop it?”*";
P_HTM[6488]="*“Atītesu me, bhante, kāmesu kāmacchando pahīno, anāgatesu me kāmesu kāmacchando vigato, ajjhattabahiddhā ca me dhammesu paṭighasaññā suppaṭivinītā.**“Sir, I’ve given up desire for sensual pleasures of the past. I’m rid of desire for sensual pleasures of the future. And I have eliminated perception of repulsion regarding phenomena internally and externally.*";
P_HTM[6489]="*So satova assasissāmi, satova passasissāmi.**Just mindful, I will breathe in. Mindful, I will breathe out.*";
P_HTM[6490]="*Evaṃ khvāhaṃ, bhante, bhāvemi ānāpānassatin”ti.**That’s how I develop mindfulness of breathing.”*";
P_HTM[6491]="*“‘Atthesā, ariṭṭha, ānāpānassati, nesā natthī’ti vadāmi.**“That is mindfulness of breathing, Ariṭṭha; I don’t deny it.*";
P_HTM[6492]="*Api ca, ariṭṭha, yathā ānāpānassati vitthārena paripuṇṇā hoti**But as to how mindfulness of breathing is fulfilled in detail,*";
P_HTM[6493]="*taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[6494]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ariṭṭho bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” Ariṭṭha replied.*";
P_HTM[6495]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[6496]="*“Kathañca, ariṭṭha, ānāpānassati vitthārena paripuṇṇā hoti?**“And how is mindfulness of breathing fulfilled in detail?*";
P_HTM[6497]="*Idha, ariṭṭha, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut. They sit down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[6498]="*So satova assasati, satova passasati.**Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out.*";
P_HTM[6499]="*Dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti … pe …**When breathing in heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing in heavily.’ When breathing out heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing out heavily.’ …*";
P_HTM[6500]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6501]="*Evaṃ kho, ariṭṭha, ānāpānassati vitthārena paripuṇṇā hotī”ti.**This is how mindfulness of breathing is fulfilled in detail.”*";
P_HTM[6502]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6503]="*9. Addhānapariññāsuttaṃ**About Mahākappina*";
P_HTM[6504]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6505]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā mahākappino bhagavato avidūre nisinno hoti pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**Now, at that time Venerable Mahākappina was sitting not far from the Buddha cross-legged, with his body straight, and mindfulness established right there.*";
P_HTM[6506]="*Addasā kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ mahākappinaṃ avidūre nisinnaṃ pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**The Buddha saw him,*";
P_HTM[6507]="*Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi:**and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6508]="*“Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, etassa bhikkhuno kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā phanditattaṃ vā”ti?**“Mendicants, do you see any motion or trembling in that mendicant’s body?”*";
P_HTM[6509]="*“Yadāpi mayaṃ, bhante, taṃ āyasmantaṃ passāma saṅghamajjhe vā nisinnaṃ ekaṃ vā raho nisinnaṃ, tadāpi mayaṃ tassa āyasmato na passāma kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā phanditattaṃ vā”ti.**“Sir, whenever we see that mendicant meditating—whether in the middle of the Saṅgha or alone in private—we never see any motion or trembling in his body.”*";
P_HTM[6510]="*“Yassa, bhikkhave, samādhissa bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā neva kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, tassa so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu samādhissa nikāmalābhī akicchalābhī akasiralābhī.**“Mendicants, when an immersion has been developed and cultivated there’s no motion or trembling of the body or mind. That mendicant gets such immersion when he wants, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[6511]="*Katamassa ca, bhikkhave, samādhissa bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā neva kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā?**And what is that immersion?*";
P_HTM[6512]="*Ānāpānassatisamādhissa, bhikkhave, bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā neva kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā.**When immersion due to mindfulness of breathing has been developed and cultivated there’s no motion or trembling of the body or mind.*";
P_HTM[6513]="*Kathaṃ bhāvite ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhimhi kathaṃ bahulīkate neva kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā?**And how is immersion due to mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated in such a way?*";
P_HTM[6514]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**It’s when a mendicant—gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut—sits down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establishes their mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[6515]="*So satova assasati, satova passasati … pe …**Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out. …*";
P_HTM[6516]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6517]="*Evaṃ bhāvite ca kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhimhi evaṃ bahulīkate neva kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā”ti.**That’s how immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated so that there’s no motion or trembling of the body or mind.”*";
P_HTM[6518]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6519]="*10. Āsavakkhayasuttaṃ**The Simile of the Lamp*";
P_HTM[6520]="*“Ānāpānassatisamādhi, bhikkhave, bhāvito bahulīkato mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso.**“Mendicants, when immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[6521]="*Kathaṃ bhāvito ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi kathaṃ bahulīkato mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso?**How so?*";
P_HTM[6522]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut. They sit down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[6523]="*So satova assasati, satova passasati.**Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out.*";
P_HTM[6524]="*Dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti … pe …**When breathing in heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing in heavily.’ When breathing out heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing out heavily.’ …*";
P_HTM[6525]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6526]="*Evaṃ bhāvito kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi evaṃ bahulīkato mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso.**That’s how immersion due to mindfulness of breathing, when developed and cultivated, is very fruitful and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[6527]="*Ahampi sudaṃ, bhikkhave, pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddho bodhisattova samāno iminā vihārena bahulaṃ viharāmi.**Before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I too usually practiced this kind of meditation.*";
P_HTM[6528]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, iminā vihārena bahulaṃ viharato neva kāyo kilamati na cakkhūni;**And while I was usually practicing this kind of meditation neither my body nor my eyes became fatigued.*";
P_HTM[6529]="*anupādāya ca me āsavehi cittaṃ vimucci.**And my mind was freed from defilements by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[6530]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6531]="*‘neva me kāyo kilameyya na cakkhūni, anupādāya ca me āsavehi cittaṃ vimucceyyā’ti,**‘May neither my body nor my eyes became fatigued. And may my mind be freed from grasping without defilements.’*";
P_HTM[6532]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6533]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6534]="*‘ye me gehasitā sarasaṅkappā te pahīyeyyun’ti,**‘May I give up memories and thoughts of the lay life.’*";
P_HTM[6535]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6536]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6537]="*‘appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti,**‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive.’*";
P_HTM[6538]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6539]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6540]="*‘paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti,**‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive.’*";
P_HTM[6541]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6542]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6543]="*‘paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti,**‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive and the repulsive.’*";
P_HTM[6544]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6545]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6546]="*‘paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti,**‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive and the unrepulsive.’*";
P_HTM[6547]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6548]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6549]="*‘appaṭikūlañca paṭikūlañca tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyyaṃ sato sampajāno’ti,**‘May I meditate staying equanimous, mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive.’*";
P_HTM[6550]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6551]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6552]="*‘vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti,**‘Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, may I enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.’*";
P_HTM[6553]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6554]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6555]="*‘vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti,**‘As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, may I enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.’*";
P_HTM[6556]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6557]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6558]="*‘pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca vihareyyaṃ sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeyyaṃ, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti—upekkhako satimā sukhavihārīti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti,**‘With the fading away of rapture, may I enter and remain in the third absorption, where I will meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, “Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.”’*";
P_HTM[6559]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6560]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6561]="*‘sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti,**‘With the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness and sadness, may I enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.’*";
P_HTM[6562]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6563]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6564]="*‘sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ananto ākāsoti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti,**‘Going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that “space is infinite”, may I enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space.’*";
P_HTM[6565]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6566]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6567]="*‘sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma anantaṃ viññāṇanti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti,**‘Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that “consciousness is infinite”, may I enter and remain in the dimension of infinite consciousness.’*";
P_HTM[6568]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6569]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6570]="*‘sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma natthi kiñcīti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti,**‘Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that “there is nothing at all”, may I enter and remain in the dimension of nothingness.’*";
P_HTM[6571]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6572]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6573]="*‘sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti,**‘Going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, may I enter and remain in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.’*";
P_HTM[6574]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6575]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cepi ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[6576]="*‘sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti,**‘Going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, may I enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling.’*";
P_HTM[6577]="*ayameva ānāpānassatisamādhi sādhukaṃ manasi kātabbo.**So let them closely focus on this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6578]="*Evaṃ bhāvite kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhimhi evaṃ bahulīkate, sukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, sā ‘aniccā’ti pajānāti, ‘anajjhositā’ti pajānāti, ‘anabhinanditā’ti pajānāti;**When mindfulness of breathing has been developed and cultivated in this way, if they feel a pleasant feeling, they understand that it’s impermanent, that they’re not attached to it, and that they don’t take pleasure in it.*";
P_HTM[6579]="*dukkhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, sā ‘aniccā’ti pajānāti, ‘anajjhositā’ti pajānāti, ‘anabhinanditā’ti pajānāti;**If they feel a painful feeling, they understand that it’s impermanent, that they’re not attached to it, and that they don’t take pleasure in it.*";
P_HTM[6580]="*adukkhamasukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, ‘sā aniccā’ti pajānāti, ‘anajjhositā’ti pajānāti, ‘anabhinanditā’ti pajānāti.**If they feel a neutral feeling, they understand that it’s impermanent, that they’re not attached to it, and that they don’t take pleasure in it.*";
P_HTM[6581]="*Sukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, visaṃyutto naṃ vedayati;**If they feel a pleasant feeling, they feel it detached.*";
P_HTM[6582]="*dukkhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, visaṃyutto naṃ vedayati;**If they feel a painful feeling, they feel it detached.*";
P_HTM[6583]="*adukkhamasukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, visaṃyutto naṃ vedayati.**If they feel a neutral feeling, they feel it detached.*";
P_HTM[6584]="*So kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti pajānāti, jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti pajānāti,**Feeling the end of the body approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of the body approaching.’ Feeling the end of life approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of life approaching.’*";
P_HTM[6585]="*‘kāyassa bhedā uddhaṃ jīvitapariyādānā idheva sabbavedayitāni anabhinanditāni sītībhavissantī’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘When my body breaks up and my life has come to an end, everything that’s felt, since I no longer take pleasure in it, will become cool right here.’*";
P_HTM[6586]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, telañca paṭicca, vaṭṭiñca paṭicca telappadīpo jhāyeyya,**Suppose an oil lamp depended on oil and a wick to burn.*";
P_HTM[6587]="*tasseva telassa ca vaṭṭiyā ca pariyādānā anāhāro nibbāyeyya;**As the oil and the wick are used up, it would be extinguished due to lack of fuel.*";
P_HTM[6588]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti pajānāti, jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti pajānāti,**In the same way, feeling the end of the body approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of the body approaching.’ Feeling the end of life approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of life approaching.’*";
P_HTM[6589]="*‘kāyassa bhedā uddhaṃ jīvitapariyādānā idheva sabbavedayitāni anabhinanditāni sītībhavissantī’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘When my body breaks up and my life has come to an end, everything that’s felt, since I no longer take pleasure in it, will become cool right here.’”*";
P_HTM[6590]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6591]="*4. Puññābhisandavaggo**One Thing*";
P_HTM[6592]="*1. Cakkavattirājasuttaṃ**At Vesālī*";
P_HTM[6593]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[6594]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[6595]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ anekapariyāyena asubhakathaṃ katheti, asubhāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, asubhabhāvanāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**Now at that time the Buddha spoke in many ways to the mendicants about the meditation on ugliness. He praised the meditation on ugliness and its development.*";
P_HTM[6596]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[6597]="*“icchāmahaṃ, bhikkhave, aḍḍhamāsaṃ paṭisallīyituṃ.**“Mendicants, I wish to go on retreat for a fortnight.*";
P_HTM[6598]="*Nāmhi kenaci upasaṅkamitabbo, aññatra ekena piṇḍapātanīhārakenā”ti.**No-one should approach me, except for the one who brings my alms-food.”*";
P_HTM[6599]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissutvā nāssudha koci bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamati, aññatra ekena piṇḍapātanīhārakena.**“Yes, sir,” replied those mendicants. And no-one approached him, except for the one who brought the alms-food.*";
P_HTM[6600]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū:**Then those mendicants thought,*";
P_HTM[6601]="*“bhagavā anekapariyāyena asubhakathaṃ katheti, asubhāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, asubhabhāvanāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsatī”ti anekākāravokāraṃ asubhabhāvanānuyogamanuyuttā viharanti.**“The Buddha spoke in many ways about the meditation on ugliness. He praised the meditation on ugliness and its development.” They committed themselves to developing the many different facets of the meditation on ugliness.*";
P_HTM[6602]="*Te iminā kāyena aṭṭīyamānā harāyamānā jigucchamānā satthahārakaṃ pariyesanti.**Becoming horrified, repelled, and disgusted with this body, they looked for someone to slit their wrists.*";
P_HTM[6603]="*Dasapi bhikkhū ekāhena satthaṃ āharanti, vīsampi … pe … tiṃsampi bhikkhū ekāhena satthaṃ āharanti.**Each day ten, twenty, or thirty mendicants slit their wrists.*";
P_HTM[6604]="*Atha kho bhagavā tassa aḍḍhamāsassa accayena paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:**Then after a fortnight had passed, the Buddha came out of retreat and addressed Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[6605]="*“kiṃ nu kho, ānanda, tanubhūto viya bhikkhusaṅgho”ti?**“Ānanda, why does the mendicant Saṅgha seem so diminished?”*";
P_HTM[6606]="*“Tathā hi pana, bhante, ‘bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ anekapariyāyena asubhakathaṃ katheti, asubhāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, asubhabhāvanāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsatī’ti anekākāravokāraṃ asubhabhāvanānuyogamanuyuttā viharanti.**Ānanda told the Buddha all that had happened, and said,*";
P_HTM[6607]="*Te iminā kāyena aṭṭīyamānā harāyamānā jigucchamānā satthahārakaṃ pariyesanti.* **";
P_HTM[6608]="*Dasapi bhikkhū ekāhena satthaṃ āharanti, vīsampi bhikkhū … tiṃsampi bhikkhū ekāhena satthaṃ āharanti.* **";
P_HTM[6609]="*Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā aññaṃ pariyāyaṃ ācikkhatu yathāyaṃ bhikkhusaṅgho aññāya saṇṭhaheyyā”ti.**“Sir, please explain another way for the mendicant Saṅgha to get enlightened.”*";
P_HTM[6610]="*“Tenahānanda, yāvatikā bhikkhū vesāliṃ upanissāya viharanti te sabbe upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ sannipātehī”ti.**“Well then, Ānanda, gather all the mendicants staying in the vicinity of Vesālī together in the assembly hall.”*";
P_HTM[6611]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā yāvatikā bhikkhū vesāliṃ upanissāya viharanti te sabbe upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ sannipātetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” replied Ānanda. He did what the Buddha asked, went up to him, and said,*";
P_HTM[6612]="*“sannipatito, bhante, bhikkhusaṃgho.**“Sir, the mendicant Saṅgha has assembled.*";
P_HTM[6613]="*Yassadāni, bhante, bhagavā kālaṃ maññatī”ti.**Please, sir, come at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[6614]="*Atha kho bhagavā yena upaṭṭhānasālā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Then the Buddha went to the assembly hall, sat down on the seat spread out,*";
P_HTM[6615]="*Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6616]="*“ayampi kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi bhāvito bahulīkato santo ceva paṇīto ca asecanako ca sukho ca vihāro uppannuppanne ca pāpake akusale dhamme ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasameti.**“Mendicants, when this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it’s peaceful and sublime, a deliciously pleasant meditation. And it disperses and settles unskillful qualities on the spot whenever they arise.*";
P_HTM[6617]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gimhānaṃ pacchime māse ūhataṃ rajojallaṃ, tamenaṃ mahāakālamegho ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasameti;**In the last month of summer, when the dust and dirt is stirred up, a large sudden storm disperses and settles it on the spot.*";
P_HTM[6618]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi bhāvito bahulīkato santo ceva paṇīto ca asecanako ca sukho ca vihāro uppannuppanne ca pāpake akusale dhamme ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasameti.**In the same way, when this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it’s peaceful and sublime, a deliciously pleasant meditation. And it disperses and settles unskillful qualities on the spot whenever they arise.*";
P_HTM[6619]="*Kathaṃ bhāvito ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi kathaṃ bahulīkato santo ceva paṇīto ca asecanako ca sukho ca vihāro uppannuppanne ca pāpake akusale dhamme ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasameti?**And how is it so developed and cultivated?*";
P_HTM[6620]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**It’s when a mendicant—gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut—sits down cross-legged, with their body straight, and focuses their mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[6621]="*So satova assasati, satova passasati … pe …**Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out. …*";
P_HTM[6622]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6623]="*Evaṃ bhāvito kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi evaṃ bahulīkato santo ceva paṇīto ca asecanako ca sukho ca vihāro uppannuppanne ca pāpake akusale dhamme ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasametī”ti.**That’s how this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated so that it’s peaceful and sublime, a deliciously pleasant meditation. And it disperses and settles unskillful qualities on the spot whenever they arise.”*";
P_HTM[6624]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6625]="*2. Brahmacariyogadhasuttaṃ**With Kimbila*";
P_HTM[6626]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[6627]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kimilāyaṃ viharati veḷuvane.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Kimbilā in the Freshwater Mangrove Wood.*";
P_HTM[6628]="*Tatra kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ kimilaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to Venerable Kimbila,*";
P_HTM[6629]="*“kathaṃ bhāvito nu kho, kimila, ānāpānassatisamādhi kathaṃ bahulīkato mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso”ti?**“Kimbila, how is immersion due to mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated so that it is very fruitful and beneficial?”*";
P_HTM[6630]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā kimilo tuṇhī ahosi.**When he said this, Kimbila kept silent.*";
P_HTM[6631]="*Dutiyampi kho bhagavā … pe …**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[6632]="*tatiyampi kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ kimilaṃ āmantesi:**And for a third time, the Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[6633]="*“kathaṃ bhāvito nu kho, kimila, ānāpānassatisamādhi kathaṃ bahulīkato mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso”ti?**“How is immersion due to mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated so that it is very fruitful and beneficial?”*";
P_HTM[6634]="*Tatiyampi kho āyasmā kimilo tuṇhī ahosi.**And a second time and a third time Kimbila kept silent.*";
P_HTM[6635]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[6636]="*“etassa, bhagavā, kālo; etassa, sugata, kālo.**“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One!*";
P_HTM[6637]="*Yaṃ bhagavā ānāpānassatisamādhiṃ bhāseyya, bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti.**Let the Buddha speak on immersion due to mindfulness of breathing. The mendicants will listen and remember it.”*";
P_HTM[6638]="*“Tenahānanda, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, Ānanda, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[6639]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied.*";
P_HTM[6640]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[6641]="*“kathaṃ bhāvito ca, ānanda, ānāpānassatisamādhi kathaṃ bahulīkato mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso?**“Ānanda, how is immersion due to mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated so that it is very fruitful and beneficial?*";
P_HTM[6642]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, sits down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establishes mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[6643]="*So satova assasati, satova passasati … pe …**Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out. …*";
P_HTM[6644]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6645]="*Evaṃ bhāvito kho, ānanda, ānāpānassatisamādhi evaṃ bahulīkato mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso.**That’s how immersion due to mindfulness of breathing, when developed and cultivated, is very fruitful and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[6646]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, dīghaṃ vā passasanto ‘dīghaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti;**When a mendicant is breathing in heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing in heavily.’ When breathing out heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing out heavily.’*";
P_HTM[6647]="*rassaṃ vā assasanto ‘rassaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā passasanto ‘rassaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti;**When breathing in lightly they know: ‘I’m breathing in lightly.’ When breathing out lightly they know: ‘I’m breathing out lightly.’*";
P_HTM[6648]="*‘sabbakāyappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘sabbakāyappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing the whole body.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out experiencing the whole body.’*";
P_HTM[6649]="*‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati—**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in stilling the physical process.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out stilling the physical process.’*";
P_HTM[6650]="*kāye kāyānupassī, ānanda, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**At such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6651]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6652]="*Kāyaññatarāhaṃ, ānanda, etaṃ vadāmi yadidaṃ—assāsapassāsaṃ.**Because the breath is a certain aspect of the body, I say.*";
P_HTM[6653]="*Tasmātihānanda, kāye kāyānupassī bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**Therefore, at such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6654]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu ‘pītippaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘pītippaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**There’s a time when a mendicant practices like this: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing rapture.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out experiencing rapture.’*";
P_HTM[6655]="*‘sukhappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘sukhappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing bliss.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out experiencing bliss.’*";
P_HTM[6656]="*‘cittasaṅkhārappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘cittasaṅkhārappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing the mental processes.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out experiencing the mental processes.’*";
P_HTM[6657]="*‘passambhayaṃ cittasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati—**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in stilling the mental processes.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out stilling the mental processes.’*";
P_HTM[6658]="*vedanāsu vedanānupassī, ānanda, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**At such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6659]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6660]="*Vedanāññatarāhaṃ, ānanda, etaṃ vadāmi, yadidaṃ—assāsapassāsānaṃ sādhukaṃ manasikāraṃ.**Because close focus on the breath is a certain aspect of feelings, I say.*";
P_HTM[6661]="*Tasmātihānanda, vedanāsu vedanānupassī bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. (2)**Therefore, at such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6662]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu ‘cittappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘cittappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**There’s a time when a mendicant practices like this: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing the mind.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out experiencing the mind.’*";
P_HTM[6663]="*abhippamodayaṃ cittaṃ … pe …**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in gladdening the mind.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out gladdening the mind.’*";
P_HTM[6664]="*samādahaṃ cittaṃ …**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in immersing the mind in samādhi.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out immersing the mind in samādhi.’*";
P_HTM[6665]="*‘vimocayaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘vimocayaṃ cittaṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati—**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in freeing the mind.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out freeing the mind.’*";
P_HTM[6666]="*citte cittānupassī, ānanda, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**At such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6667]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6668]="*Nāhaṃ, ānanda, muṭṭhassatissa asampajānassa ānāpānassatisamādhibhāvanaṃ vadāmi.**Because there is no development of immersion due to mindfulness of breathing for someone who is unmindful and lacks awareness, I say.*";
P_HTM[6669]="*Tasmātihānanda, citte cittānupassī bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. (3)**Therefore, at such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6670]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu ‘aniccānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati … pe …**There’s a time when a mendicant practices like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing impermanence.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing impermanence.’*";
P_HTM[6671]="*virāgānupassī …**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing fading away.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing fading away.’*";
P_HTM[6672]="*nirodhānupassī …**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing cessation.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing cessation.’*";
P_HTM[6673]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati—**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6674]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī, ānanda, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**At such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6675]="*So yaṃ taṃ hoti abhijjhādomanassānaṃ pahānaṃ taṃ paññāya disvā sādhukaṃ ajjhupekkhitā hoti.**Having seen with wisdom the giving up of desire and aversion, they watch closely over with equanimity.*";
P_HTM[6676]="*Tasmātihānanda, dhammesu dhammānupassī bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. (4)**Therefore, at such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6677]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, catumahāpathe mahāpaṃsupuñjo.**Suppose there was a large heap of sand at the crossroads.*";
P_HTM[6678]="*Puratthimāya cepi disāyaṃ āgaccheyya sakaṭaṃ vā ratho vā, upahanateva taṃ paṃsupuñjaṃ;**And a cart or chariot were to come by from the east,*";
P_HTM[6679]="*pacchimāya cepi disāya āgaccheyya …**west,*";
P_HTM[6680]="*uttarāya cepi disāya …**north,*";
P_HTM[6681]="*dakkhiṇāya cepi disāya āgaccheyya sakaṭaṃ vā ratho vā, upahanateva taṃ paṃsupuñjaṃ.**or south and destroy that heap of sand.*";
P_HTM[6682]="*Evameva kho, ānanda, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharantopi upahanateva pāpake akusale dhamme;**In the same way, when a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of the body,*";
P_HTM[6683]="*vedanāsu … pe …**feelings,*";
P_HTM[6684]="*citte … pe …**mind,*";
P_HTM[6685]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharantopi upahanateva pāpake akusale dhamme”ti.**or principles, they destroy bad, unskillful qualities.”*";
P_HTM[6686]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6687]="*Ekadhammavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[6688]="*Ekadhammo ca bojjhaṅgo,* **";
P_HTM[6689]="*suddhikañca duve phalā;* **";
P_HTM[6690]="*Ariṭṭho kappino dīpo,* **";
P_HTM[6691]="*vesālī kimilena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[6692]="*3. Dīghāvuupāsakasuttaṃ**Icchānaṅgala*";
P_HTM[6693]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā icchānaṅgale viharati icchānaṅgalavanasaṇḍe.**At one time the Buddha was staying in a forest near Icchānaṅgala.*";
P_HTM[6694]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There he addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[6695]="*“icchāmahaṃ, bhikkhave, temāsaṃ paṭisallīyituṃ.**“Mendicants, I wish to go on retreat for three months.*";
P_HTM[6696]="*Nāmhi kenaci upasaṅkamitabbo, aññatra ekena piṇḍapātanīhārakenā”ti.**No-one should approach me, except for the one who brings my alms-food.”*";
P_HTM[6697]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissutvā nāssudha koci bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamati, aññatra ekena piṇḍapātanīhārakena.**“Yes, sir,” replied those mendicants. And no-one approached him, except for the one who brought the alms-food.*";
P_HTM[6698]="*Atha kho bhagavā tassa temāsassa accayena paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then after three months had passed, the Buddha came out of retreat and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6699]="*“sace kho, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**“Mendicants, if wanderers who follow another path were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[6700]="*‘katamenāvuso, vihārena samaṇo gotamo vassāvāsaṃ bahulaṃ vihāsī’ti, evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha:**‘Reverends, what was the ascetic Gotama’s usual meditation during the rainy season residence?’ You should answer them like this.*";
P_HTM[6701]="*‘ānāpānassatisamādhinā kho, āvuso, bhagavā vassāvāsaṃ bahulaṃ vihāsī’ti.**‘Reverends, the ascetic Gotama’s usual meditation during the rainy season residence was immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.’*";
P_HTM[6702]="*Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sato assasāmi, sato passasāmi.**In this regard: mindful, I breathe in. Mindful, I breathe out.*";
P_HTM[6703]="*Dīghaṃ assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāmi, dīghaṃ passasanto ‘dīghaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāmi;**When breathing in heavily I know: ‘I’m breathing in heavily.’ When breathing out heavily I know: ‘I’m breathing out heavily.’*";
P_HTM[6704]="*rassaṃ assasanto ‘rassaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāmi, rassaṃ passasanto ‘rassaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāmi;**When breathing in lightly I know: ‘I’m breathing in lightly.’ When breathing out lightly I know: ‘I’m breathing out lightly.’*";
P_HTM[6705]="*‘sabbakāyappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti pajānāmi … pe …**I know: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing the whole body.’ …*";
P_HTM[6706]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti pajānāmi, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti pajānāmi.**I know: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ I know: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6707]="*Yañhi taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya:**For if anything should be rightly called*";
P_HTM[6708]="*‘ariyavihāro’ itipi, ‘brahmavihāro’ itipi, ‘tathāgatavihāro’ itipi.**‘the meditation of a noble one’, or else ‘the meditation of a Brahmā’, or else ‘the meditation of a realized one’,*";
P_HTM[6709]="*Ānāpānassatisamādhiṃ sammā vadamāno vadeyya:**it’s immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6710]="*‘ariyavihāro’ itipi, ‘brahmavihāro’ itipi, ‘tathāgatavihāro’ itipi.* **";
P_HTM[6711]="*Ye te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū sekhā appattamānasā anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ patthayamānā viharanti tesaṃ ānāpānassatisamādhi bhāvito bahulīkato āsavānaṃ khayāya saṃvattati.**For those mendicants who are trainees—who haven’t achieved their heart’s desire, but live aspiring to the supreme sanctuary—the development and cultivation of immersion due to mindfulness of breathing leads to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[6712]="*Ye ca kho te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū arahanto khīṇāsavā vusitavanto katakaraṇīyā ohitabhārā anuppattasadatthā parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojanā sammadaññāvimuttā, tesaṃ ānāpānassatisamādhi bhāvito bahulīkato diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārāya ceva saṃvattati satisampajaññāya ca.**For those mendicants who are perfected—who have ended the defilements, completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and are rightly freed through enlightenment—the development and cultivation of immersion due to mindfulness of breathing leads to blissful meditation in the present life, and to mindfulness and awareness.*";
P_HTM[6713]="*Yañhi taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya:**For if anything should be rightly called*";
P_HTM[6714]="*‘ariyavihāro’ itipi, ‘brahmavihāro’ itipi, ‘tathāgatavihāro’ itipi.**‘the meditation of a noble one’, or else ‘the meditation of a Brahmā’, or else ‘the meditation of a realized one’,*";
P_HTM[6715]="*Ānāpānassatisamādhiṃ sammā vadamāno vadeyya:**it’s immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.”*";
P_HTM[6716]="*‘ariyavihāro’ itipi, ‘brahmavihāro’ itipi, ‘tathāgatavihāro’ itipī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6717]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6718]="*4. Paṭhamasāriputtasuttaṃ**In Doubt*";
P_HTM[6719]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā lomasakaṃbhiyo sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme.**At one time Venerable Lomasavaṅgīsa was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery.*";
P_HTM[6720]="*Atha kho mahānāmo sakko yenāyasmā lomasakaṃbhiyo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ lomasakaṃbhiyaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahānāmo sakko āyasmantaṃ lomasakaṃbhiyaṃ etadavoca:**Then Mahānāma the Sakyan went up to Venerable Lomasavaṅgīsa, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6721]="*“so eva nu kho, bhante, sekho vihāro so tathāgatavihāro, udāhu aññova sekho vihāro añño tathāgatavihāro”ti?**“Sir, is the meditation of a trainee just the same as the meditation of a Realized One? Or is the meditation of a trainee different from the meditation of a Realized One?”*";
P_HTM[6722]="*“Na kho, āvuso mahānāma, sveva sekho vihāro, so tathāgatavihāro.**“Reverend Mahānāma, the meditation of a trainee and a realized one are not the same;*";
P_HTM[6723]="*Añño kho, āvuso mahānāma, sekho vihāro, añño tathāgatavihāro.**they are different.*";
P_HTM[6724]="*Ye te, āvuso mahānāma, bhikkhū sekhā appattamānasā anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ patthayamānā viharanti, te pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya viharanti.**Those mendicants who are trainees haven’t achieved their heart’s desire, but live aspiring for the supreme sanctuary. They meditate after giving up the five hindrances.*";
P_HTM[6725]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[6726]="*Kāmacchandanīvaraṇaṃ pahāya viharanti, byāpādanīvaraṇaṃ … pe …**The hindrances of sensual desire, ill will,*";
P_HTM[6727]="*thinamiddhanīvaraṇaṃ …**dullness and drowsiness,*";
P_HTM[6728]="*uddhaccakukkuccanīvaraṇaṃ …**restlessness and remorse,*";
P_HTM[6729]="*vicikicchānīvaraṇaṃ pahāya viharanti.**and doubt.*";
P_HTM[6730]="*Yepi te, āvuso mahānāma, bhikkhū sekhā appattamānasā anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ patthayamānā viharanti, te ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya viharanti.**Those who are trainee mendicants … meditate after giving up the five hindrances.*";
P_HTM[6731]="*Ye ca kho te, āvuso mahānāma, bhikkhū arahanto khīṇāsavā vusitavanto katakaraṇīyā ohitabhārā anuppattasadatthā parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojanā sammadaññāvimuttā, tesaṃ pañca nīvaraṇā pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṃkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**Those mendicants who are perfected—who have ended the defilements, completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and are rightly freed through enlightenment—for them, the five hindrances are cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[6732]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[6733]="*Kāmacchandanīvaraṇaṃ pahīnaṃ ucchinnamūlaṃ tālāvatthukataṃ anabhāvaṃkataṃ āyatiṃ anuppādadhammaṃ;**The hindrances of sensual desire,*";
P_HTM[6734]="*byāpādanīvaraṇaṃ pahīnaṃ … pe …**ill will,*";
P_HTM[6735]="*thinamiddhanīvaraṇaṃ …**dullness and drowsiness,*";
P_HTM[6736]="*uddhaccakukkuccanīvaraṇaṃ …**restlessness and remorse,*";
P_HTM[6737]="*vicikicchānīvaraṇaṃ pahīnaṃ ucchinnamūlaṃ tālāvatthukataṃ anabhāvaṃkataṃ āyatiṃ anuppādadhammaṃ.**and doubt.*";
P_HTM[6738]="*Ye te, āvuso mahānāma, bhikkhū arahanto khīṇāsavā vusitavanto katakaraṇīyā ohitabhārā anuppattasadatthā parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojanā sammadaññāvimuttā, tesaṃ ime pañca nīvaraṇā pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**Those mendicants who are perfected—who have ended the defilements … for them, the five hindrances are cut off at the root … and unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[6739]="*Tadamināpetaṃ, āvuso mahānāma, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā—**And here’s another way to understand how*";
P_HTM[6740]="*aññova sekho vihāro, añño tathāgatavihāro.**the meditation of a trainee and a realized one are different.*";
P_HTM[6741]="*Ekamidaṃ, āvuso mahānāma, samayaṃ bhagavā icchānaṅgale viharati icchānaṅgalavanasaṇḍe.**At one time the Buddha was staying in a forest near Icchānaṅgala.*";
P_HTM[6742]="*Tatra kho, āvuso mahānāma, bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There he addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[6743]="*‘icchāmahaṃ, bhikkhave, temāsaṃ paṭisallīyituṃ.**‘Mendicants, I wish to go on retreat for three months.*";
P_HTM[6744]="*Nāmhi kenaci upasaṅkamitabbo, aññatra ekena piṇḍapātanīhārakenā’ti.**No-one should approach me, except for the one who brings my alms-food.’*";
P_HTM[6745]="*‘Evaṃ, bhante’ti kho, āvuso mahānāma, te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissutvā nāssudha koci bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamati, aññatra ekena piṇḍapātanīhārakena.**‘Yes, sir,’ replied those mendicants. And no-one approached him, except for the one who brought the alms-food.*";
P_HTM[6746]="*Atha kho, āvuso, bhagavā tassa temāsassa accayena paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then after three months had passed, the Buddha came out of retreat and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6747]="*‘sace kho, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**‘Mendicants, if wanderers who follow another path were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[6748]="*“katamenāvuso, vihārena samaṇo gotamo vassāvāsaṃ bahulaṃ vihāsī”ti, evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha:**“Reverends, what was the ascetic Gotama’s usual meditation during the rainy season residence?” You should answer them like this:*";
P_HTM[6749]="*“ānāpānassatisamādhinā kho, āvuso, bhagavā vassāvāsaṃ bahulaṃ vihāsī”’ti.**“Reverends, the ascetic Gotama’s usual meditation during the rainy season residence was immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.”*";
P_HTM[6750]="*Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sato assasāmi, sato passasāmi.**In this regard: mindful, I breathe in. Mindful, I breathe out.*";
P_HTM[6751]="*Dīghaṃ assasanto dīghaṃ assasāmīti pajānāmi, dīghaṃ passasanto dīghaṃ passasāmīti pajānāmi … pe …**When breathing in heavily I know: ‘I’m breathing in heavily.’ When breathing out heavily I know: ‘I’m breathing out heavily.’ …*";
P_HTM[6752]="*paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmīti pajānāmi, paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmīti pajānāmi.**I know: “I’ll breathe in observing letting go.” I know: “I’ll breathe out observing letting go.”*";
P_HTM[6753]="*Yañhi taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya—**For if anything should be rightly called*";
P_HTM[6754]="*ariyavihāro itipi, brahmavihāro itipi, tathāgatavihāro itipi.**“the meditation of a noble one”, or else “the meditation of a Brahmā”, or else “the meditation of a realized one”,*";
P_HTM[6755]="*Ānāpānassatisamādhiṃ sammā vadamāno vadeyya—**it’s immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[6756]="*ariyavihāro itipi, brahmavihāro itipi, tathāgatavihāro itipi.* **";
P_HTM[6757]="*Ye te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū sekhā appattamānasā anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ patthayamānā viharanti, tesaṃ ānāpānassatisamādhi bhāvito bahulīkato āsavānaṃ khayāya saṃvattati.**For those mendicants who are trainees—who haven’t achieved their heart’s desire, but live aspiring for the supreme sanctuary—the development and cultivation of immersion due to mindfulness of breathing leads to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[6758]="*Ye ca kho te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū arahanto khīṇāsavā vusitavanto katakaraṇīyā ohitabhārā anuppattasadatthā parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojanā sammadaññāvimuttā, tesaṃ ānāpānassatisamādhi bhāvito bahulīkato diṭṭheva dhamme sukhavihārāya ceva saṃvattati satisampajaññāya ca.**For those mendicants who are perfected—who have ended the defilements, completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and are rightly freed through enlightenment—the development and cultivation of immersion due to mindfulness of breathing leads to blissful meditation in the present life, and to mindfulness and awareness.*";
P_HTM[6759]="*Yañhi taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya—**For if anything should be rightly called*";
P_HTM[6760]="*ariyavihāro itipi, brahmavihāro itipi, tathāgatavihāro itipi.**“the meditation of a noble one”, or else “the meditation of a Brahmā”, or else “the meditation of a realized one”,*";
P_HTM[6761]="*Ānāpānassatisamādhiṃ sammā vadamāno vadeyya—**it’s immersion due to mindfulness of breathing.’*";
P_HTM[6762]="*ariyavihāro itipi, brahmavihāro itipi, tathāgatavihāro itipīti.* **";
P_HTM[6763]="*Iminā kho etaṃ, āvuso mahānāma, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ, yathā—**This is another way to understand how*";
P_HTM[6764]="*aññova sekho vihāro, añño tathāgatavihāro”ti.**the meditation of a trainee and a realized one are different.”*";
P_HTM[6765]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6766]="*5. Dutiyasāriputtasuttaṃ**With Ānanda (1st)*";
P_HTM[6767]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6768]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6769]="*“atthi nu kho, bhante, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro dhamme paripūreti, cattāro dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti, satta dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā dve dhamme paripūrentī”ti?**“Sir, is there one thing that, when developed and cultivated, fulfills four things; and those four things, when developed and cultivated, fulfill seven things; and those seven things, when developed and cultivated, fulfill two things?”*";
P_HTM[6770]="*“Atthi kho, ānanda, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro dhamme paripūreti, cattāro dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti, satta dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā dve dhamme paripūrentī”ti.**“There is, Ānanda.”*";
P_HTM[6771]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro dhamme paripūreti, cattāro dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti, satta dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā dve dhamme paripūrentī”ti?**“Sir, what is that one thing?”*";
P_HTM[6772]="*“Ānāpānassatisamādhi kho, ānanda, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro satipaṭṭhāne paripūreti, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta bojjhaṅge paripūrenti, satta bojjhaṅgā bhāvitā bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ paripūrenti.**“Immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is one thing that, when developed and cultivated, fulfills the four kinds of mindfulness meditation. And the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, when developed and cultivated, fulfill the seven awakening factors. And the seven awakening factors, when developed and cultivated, fulfill knowledge and freedom.*";
P_HTM[6773]="*Kathaṃ bhāvito, ānanda, ānāpānassatisamādhi kathaṃ bahulīkato cattāro satipaṭṭhāne paripūreti?**And how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated so as to fulfill the four kinds of mindfulness meditation?*";
P_HTM[6774]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, sits down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establishes mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[6775]="*So satova assasati, satova passasati.**Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out.*";
P_HTM[6776]="*Dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, dīghaṃ vā passasanto ‘dīghaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti … pe …**When breathing in heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing in heavily.’ When breathing out heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing out heavily.’ …*";
P_HTM[6777]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6778]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, dīghaṃ vā passasanto ‘dīghaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti;**When a mendicant is breathing in heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing in heavily.’ When breathing out heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing out heavily.’*";
P_HTM[6779]="*rassaṃ vā … pe …**…*";
P_HTM[6780]="*‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati—**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in stilling the physical process.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out stilling the physical process.’*";
P_HTM[6781]="*kāye kāyānupassī, ānanda, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**At such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6782]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6783]="*Kāyaññatarāhaṃ, ānanda, etaṃ vadāmi, yadidaṃ—assāsapassāsaṃ.**Because the breath is a certain aspect of the body, I say.*";
P_HTM[6784]="*Tasmātihānanda, kāye kāyānupassī bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**Therefore, at such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6785]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu ‘pītippaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati,**There’s a time when a mendicant practices like this: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing rapture …*";
P_HTM[6786]="*sukhappaṭisaṃvedī … pe …**bliss …*";
P_HTM[6787]="*cittasaṅkhārappaṭisaṃvedī …**mind …’ …*";
P_HTM[6788]="*‘passambhayaṃ cittasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘passambhayaṃ cittasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati—**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in stilling the mental processes.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out stilling the mental processes.’*";
P_HTM[6789]="*vedanāsu vedanānupassī, ānanda, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**At such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6790]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6791]="*Vedanāññatarāhaṃ, ānanda, etaṃ vadāmi, yadidaṃ—assāsapassāsānaṃ sādhukaṃ manasikāraṃ.**Because close focus on the breath is a certain aspect of feelings, I say.*";
P_HTM[6792]="*Tasmātihānanda, vedanāsu vedanānupassī bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. (2)**Therefore, at such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6793]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu ‘cittappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘cittappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**There’s a time when a mendicant practices like this: ‘I’ll breathe in experiencing the mind.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out experiencing the mind.’*";
P_HTM[6794]="*abhippamodayaṃ cittaṃ … pe …**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in gladdening the mind …*";
P_HTM[6795]="*samādahaṃ cittaṃ …**immersing the mind in samādhi …*";
P_HTM[6796]="*‘vimocayaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘vimocayaṃ cittaṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati—**freeing the mind.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out freeing the mind.’*";
P_HTM[6797]="*citte cittānupassī, ānanda, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**At such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6798]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6799]="*Nāhaṃ, ānanda, muṭṭhassatissa asampajānassa ānāpānassatisamādhibhāvanaṃ vadāmi.**Because there is no development of immersion due to mindfulness of breathing for someone who is unmindful and lacks awareness, I say.*";
P_HTM[6800]="*Tasmātihānanda, citte cittānupassī bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. (3)**Therefore, at such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6801]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu aniccānupassī … pe …**There’s a time when a mendicant practices like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing impermanence …*";
P_HTM[6802]="*virāgānupassī …**fading away …*";
P_HTM[6803]="*nirodhānupassī …**cessation …*";
P_HTM[6804]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati—**letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6805]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī, ānanda, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**At such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6806]="*So yaṃ taṃ hoti abhijjhādomanassānaṃ pahānaṃ taṃ paññāya disvā sādhukaṃ ajjhupekkhitā hoti.**Having seen with wisdom the giving up of desire and aversion, they watch closely over with equanimity.*";
P_HTM[6807]="*Tasmātihānanda, dhammesu dhammānupassī bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. (4)**Therefore, at such a time a mendicant is meditating by observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[6808]="*Evaṃ bhāvito kho, ānanda, ānāpānassatisamādhi evaṃ bahulīkato cattāro satipaṭṭhāne paripūreti.**That’s how immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated so as to fulfill the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[6809]="*Kathaṃ bhāvitā cānanda, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā kathaṃ bahulīkatā satta bojjhaṅge paripūrenti?**And how are the four kinds of mindfulness meditation developed and cultivated so as to fulfill the seven awakening factors?*";
P_HTM[6810]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati—**Whenever a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body,*";
P_HTM[6811]="*upaṭṭhitāssa tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno sati hoti asammuṭṭhā.**their mindfulness is established and lucid.*";
P_HTM[6812]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhuno upaṭṭhitā sati hoti asammuṭṭhā—satisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, satisambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, satisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati.**At such a time, a mendicant has activated the awakening factor of mindfulness; they develop it and perfect it.*";
P_HTM[6813]="*So tathā sato viharanto taṃ dhammaṃ paññāya pavicinati pavicarati parivīmaṃsamāpajjati.**As they live mindfully in this way they investigate, explore, and inquire into that principle with wisdom.*";
P_HTM[6814]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu tathā sato viharanto taṃ dhammaṃ paññāya pavicinati pavicarati parivīmaṃsamāpajjati—* **";
P_HTM[6815]="*dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati. (2)**At such a time, a mendicant has activated the awakening factor of investigation of principles; they develop it and perfect it.*";
P_HTM[6816]="*Tassa taṃ dhammaṃ paññāya pavicinato pavicarato parivīmaṃsamāpajjato āraddhaṃ hoti vīriyaṃ asallīnaṃ.**As they investigate principles with wisdom in this way their energy is roused up and unflagging.*";
P_HTM[6817]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhuno taṃ dhammaṃ paññāya pavicinato pavicarato parivīmaṃsamāpajjato āraddhaṃ hoti vīriyaṃ asallīnaṃ—**At such a time, a mendicant has activated the awakening factor of energy; they develop it and perfect it.*";
P_HTM[6818]="*vīriyasambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, vīriyasambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, vīriyasambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati. (3)* **";
P_HTM[6819]="*Āraddhavīriyassa uppajjati pīti nirāmisā.**When you’re energetic, spiritual rapture arises.*";
P_HTM[6820]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhuno āraddhavīriyassa uppajjati pīti nirāmisā—**At such a time, a mendicant has activated the awakening factor of rapture; they develop it and perfect it.*";
P_HTM[6821]="*pītisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, pītisambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, pītisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati. (4)* **";
P_HTM[6822]="*Pītimanassa kāyopi passambhati, cittampi passambhati.**When the mind is full of rapture, the body and mind become tranquil.*";
P_HTM[6823]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhuno pītimanassa kāyopi passambhati, cittampi passambhati—**At such a time, a mendicant has activated the awakening factor of tranquility; they develop it and perfect it.*";
P_HTM[6824]="*passaddhisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, passaddhisambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, passaddhisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati. (5)* **";
P_HTM[6825]="*Passaddhakāyassa sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati.**When the body is tranquil and one feels bliss, the mind becomes immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[6826]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhuno passaddhakāyassa sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati—**At such a time, a mendicant has activated the awakening factor of immersion; they develop it and perfect it.*";
P_HTM[6827]="*samādhisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, samādhisambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, samādhisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati. (6)* **";
P_HTM[6828]="*So tathāsamāhitaṃ cittaṃ sādhukaṃ ajjhupekkhitā hoti.**They closely watch over that mind immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[6829]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu tathāsamāhitaṃ cittaṃ sādhukaṃ ajjhupekkhitā hoti—**At such a time, a mendicant has activated the awakening factor of equanimity; they develop it and perfect it.*";
P_HTM[6830]="*upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati. (7)* **";
P_HTM[6831]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu vedanāsu … pe …**Whenever a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of feelings …*";
P_HTM[6832]="*citte … pe …**mind …*";
P_HTM[6833]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati—**principles,*";
P_HTM[6834]="*upaṭṭhitāssa tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno sati hoti asammuṭṭhā.**their mindfulness is established and lucid.*";
P_HTM[6835]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhuno upaṭṭhitā sati hoti asammuṭṭhā—**At such a time, a mendicant has activated the awakening factor of mindfulness; they develop it and perfect it. …*";
P_HTM[6836]="*satisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, satisambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, satisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[6837]="*(Yathā paṭhamaṃ satipaṭṭhānaṃ, evaṃ vitthāretabbaṃ.)**(This should be told in full as for the first kind of mindfulness meditation.)*";
P_HTM[6838]="*So tathāsamāhitaṃ cittaṃ sādhukaṃ ajjhupekkhitā hoti.**They closely watch over that mind immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[6839]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, ānanda, bhikkhu tathāsamāhitaṃ cittaṃ sādhukaṃ ajjhupekkhitā hoti—**At such a time, a mendicant has activated the awakening factor of equanimity; they develop it and perfect it.*";
P_HTM[6840]="*upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[6841]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, ānanda, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā evaṃ bahulīkatā satta bojjhaṅge paripūrenti.**That’s how the four kinds of mindfulness meditation are developed and cultivated so as to fulfill the seven awakening factors.*";
P_HTM[6842]="*Kathaṃ bhāvitā, ānanda, satta bojjhaṅgā kathaṃ bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ paripūrenti?**And how are the seven awakening factors developed and cultivated so as to fulfill knowledge and freedom?*";
P_HTM[6843]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ, dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pe … upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ.**It’s when a mendicant develops the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go.*";
P_HTM[6844]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, ānanda, satta bojjhaṅgā evaṃ bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ paripūrentī”ti.**That’s how the seven awakening factors are developed and cultivated so as to fulfill knowledge and freedom.”*";
P_HTM[6845]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6846]="*6. Thapatisuttaṃ**With Ānanda (2nd)*";
P_HTM[6847]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[6848]="*“atthi nu kho, ānanda, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro dhamme paripūreti, cattāro dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti, satta dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā dve dhamme paripūrentī”ti.**“Ānanda, is there one thing that, when developed and cultivated, fulfills four things; and those four things, when developed and cultivated, fulfill seven things; and those seven things, when developed and cultivated, fulfill two things?”*";
P_HTM[6849]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[6850]="*“atthānanda, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro dhamme paripūreti, cattāro dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti, satta dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā dve dhamme paripūrenti.**“There is, Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[6851]="*Katamo cānanda, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro dhamme paripūreti, cattāro dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti, satta dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā dve dhamme paripūrenti?**And what is that one thing?*";
P_HTM[6852]="*Ānāpānassatisamādhi, ānanda, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro satipaṭṭhāne paripūreti, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta bojjhaṅge paripūrenti, satta bojjhaṅgā bhāvitā bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ paripūrentīti.**Immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is one thing that, when developed and cultivated, fulfills the four kinds of mindfulness meditation. And the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, when developed and cultivated, fulfill the seven awakening factors. And the seven awakening factors, when developed and cultivated, fulfill knowledge and freedom.*";
P_HTM[6853]="*Kathaṃ bhāvito cānanda, ānāpānassatisamādhi, kathaṃ bahulīkato cattāro satipaṭṭhāne paripūreti?**And how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated so as to fulfill the four kinds of mindfulness meditation? …*";
P_HTM[6854]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu araññagato vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6855]="*evaṃ bhāvitā kho, ānanda, satta bojjhaṅgā evaṃ bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ paripūrentī”ti.**That’s how the seven awakening factors are developed and cultivated so as to fulfill knowledge and freedom.”*";
P_HTM[6856]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6857]="*7. Veḷudvāreyyasuttaṃ**Several Mendicants (1st)*";
P_HTM[6858]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6859]="*“atthi nu kho, bhante, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro dhamme paripūreti, cattāro dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti, satta dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā dve dhamme paripūrentī”ti?**“Sir, is there one thing that, when developed and cultivated, fulfills four things; and those four things, when developed and cultivated, fulfill seven things; and those seven things, when developed and cultivated, fulfill two things?”*";
P_HTM[6860]="*“Atthi kho, bhikkhave, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro dhamme paripūreti, cattāro dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti, satta dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā dve dhamme paripūrentī”ti.**“There is, mendicants.”*";
P_HTM[6861]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro dhamme paripūreti, cattāro dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti, satta dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā dve dhamme paripūrentī”ti?**“Sir, what is that one thing?”*";
P_HTM[6862]="*“Ānāpānassatisamādhi kho, bhikkhave, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro satipaṭṭhāne paripūreti, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta bojjhaṅge paripūrenti, satta bojjhaṅgā bhāvitā bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ paripūrentīti.**“Immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is one thing that, when developed and cultivated, fulfills the four kinds of mindfulness meditation. And the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, when developed and cultivated, fulfill the seven awakening factors. And the seven awakening factors, when developed and cultivated, fulfill knowledge and freedom.*";
P_HTM[6863]="*Kathaṃ bhāvito ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi kathaṃ bahulīkato cattāro satipaṭṭhāne paripūreti?**And how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated so as to fulfill the four kinds of mindfulness meditation? …*";
P_HTM[6864]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6865]="*evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā evaṃ bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ paripūrentī”ti.**That’s how the seven awakening factors are developed and cultivated so as to fulfill knowledge and freedom.”*";
P_HTM[6866]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6867]="*8. Paṭhamagiñjakāvasathasuttaṃ**Several Mendicants (2nd)*";
P_HTM[6868]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca:**Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to them:*";
P_HTM[6869]="*“atthi nu kho, bhikkhave, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro dhamme paripūreti, cattāro dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti, satta dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā dve dhamme paripūrentī”ti?**“Mendicants, is there one thing that, when developed and cultivated, fulfills four things; and those four things, when developed and cultivated, fulfill seven things; and those seven things, when developed and cultivated, fulfill two things?”*";
P_HTM[6870]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe … bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti.**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[6871]="*“Atthi, bhikkhave, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro dhamme paripūreti, cattāro dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti, satta dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā dve dhamme paripūrenti.**“There is, mendicants.*";
P_HTM[6872]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro dhamme paripūreti, cattāro dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti, satta dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā dve dhamme paripūrenti?**And what is that one thing?*";
P_HTM[6873]="*Ānāpānassatisamādhi, bhikkhave, ekadhammo bhāvito bahulīkato cattāro satipaṭṭhāne paripūreti, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta bojjhaṅge paripūrenti, satta bojjhaṅgā bhāvitā bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ paripūrentīti.**Immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is one thing that, when developed and cultivated, fulfills the four kinds of mindfulness meditation. And the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, when developed and cultivated, fulfill the seven awakening factors. And the seven awakening factors, when developed and cultivated, fulfill knowledge and freedom.*";
P_HTM[6874]="*Kathaṃ bhāvito ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi kathaṃ bahulīkato cattāro satipaṭṭhāne paripūreti?**And how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated so as to fulfill the four kinds of mindfulness meditation?*";
P_HTM[6875]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut. They sit down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there. …*";
P_HTM[6876]="*So satova assasati, satova passasati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6877]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.* **";
P_HTM[6878]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, dīghaṃ vā passasanto ‘dīghaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā assasanto ‘rassaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6879]="*sabbakāyappaṭisaṃvedī … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6880]="*‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati—* **";
P_HTM[6881]="*kāye kāyānupassī, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6882]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[6883]="*Kāyaññatarāhaṃ, bhikkhave, etaṃ vadāmi, yadidaṃ—assāsapassāsaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6884]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, kāye kāyānupassī bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6885]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pītippaṭisaṃvedī … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6886]="*sukhappaṭisaṃvedī …* **";
P_HTM[6887]="*cittasaṅkhārappaṭisaṃvedī …* **";
P_HTM[6888]="*‘passambhayaṃ cittasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘passambhayaṃ cittasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati—* **";
P_HTM[6889]="*vedanāsu vedanānupassī, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6890]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[6891]="*Vedanāññatarāhaṃ, bhikkhave, etaṃ vadāmi, yadidaṃ—assāsapassāsānaṃ sādhukaṃ manasikāraṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6892]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, vedanāsu vedanānupassī bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. (2)* **";
P_HTM[6893]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cittappaṭisaṃvedī … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6894]="*abhippamodayaṃ cittaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6895]="*‘samādahaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘samādahaṃ cittaṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;* **";
P_HTM[6896]="*‘vimocayaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘vimocayaṃ cittaṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati—* **";
P_HTM[6897]="*citte cittānupassī, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6898]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[6899]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, muṭṭhassatissa asampajānassa ānāpānassatisamādhibhāvanaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[6900]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, citte cittānupassī bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. (3)* **";
P_HTM[6901]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aniccānupassī … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6902]="*virāgānupassī … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6903]="*nirodhānupassī … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6904]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati—* **";
P_HTM[6905]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6906]="*So yaṃ taṃ hoti abhijjhādomanassānaṃ pahānaṃ taṃ paññāya disvā sādhukaṃ ajjhupekkhitā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[6907]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, dhammesu dhammānupassī bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. (4)* **";
P_HTM[6908]="*Evaṃ bhāvito kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi evaṃ bahulīkato cattāro satipaṭṭhāne paripūreti.* **";
P_HTM[6909]="*Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā kathaṃ bahulīkatā satta bojjhaṅge paripūrenti?* **";
P_HTM[6910]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati—upaṭṭhitāssa tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno sati hoti asammuṭṭhā.* **";
P_HTM[6911]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā—* **";
P_HTM[6912]="*satisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, satisambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, satisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[6913]="*So tathāsato viharanto taṃ dhammaṃ paññāya pavicinati pavicarati parivīmaṃsamāpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[6914]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tathāsato viharanto taṃ dhammaṃ paññāya pavicinati pavicarati parivīmaṃsamāpajjati—* **";
P_HTM[6915]="*dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati. (2)* **";
P_HTM[6916]="*Tassa taṃ dhammaṃ paññāya pavicinato pavicarato parivīmaṃsamāpajjato āraddhaṃ hoti vīriyaṃ asallīnaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6917]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno taṃ dhammaṃ paññāya pavicinato pavicarato parivīmaṃsamāpajjato āraddhaṃ hoti vīriyaṃ asallīnaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[6918]="*vīriyasambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, vīriyasambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, vīriyasambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati. (3)* **";
P_HTM[6919]="*Āraddhavīriyassa uppajjati pīti nirāmisā.* **";
P_HTM[6920]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno āraddhavīriyassa uppajjati pīti nirāmisā—* **";
P_HTM[6921]="*pītisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, pītisambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, pītisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati. (4)* **";
P_HTM[6922]="*Pītimanassa kāyopi passambhati, cittampi passambhati.* **";
P_HTM[6923]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pītimanassa kāyopi passambhati, cittampi passambhati—* **";
P_HTM[6924]="*passaddhisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, passaddhisambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, passaddhisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati. (5)* **";
P_HTM[6925]="*Passaddhakāyassa sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati.* **";
P_HTM[6926]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno passaddhakāyassa sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati—* **";
P_HTM[6927]="*samādhisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, samādhisambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, samādhisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati. (6)* **";
P_HTM[6928]="*So tathāsamāhitaṃ cittaṃ sādhukaṃ ajjhupekkhitā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[6929]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tathāsamāhitaṃ cittaṃ sādhukaṃ ajjhupekkhitā hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6930]="*upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati. (7)* **";
P_HTM[6931]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vedanāsu … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6932]="*citte … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6933]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati—upaṭṭhitāssa tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno sati hoti asammuṭṭhā.* **";
P_HTM[6934]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno upaṭṭhitā sati hoti asammuṭṭhā—* **";
P_HTM[6935]="*satisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, satisambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti—satisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[6936]="*So tathāsamāhitaṃ cittaṃ sādhukaṃ ajjhupekkhitā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[6937]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tathāsamāhitaṃ cittaṃ sādhukaṃ ajjhupekkhitā hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6938]="*upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno āraddho hoti, upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu bhāveti, upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhikkhuno bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[6939]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā evaṃ bahulīkatā satta bojjhaṅge paripūrenti.* **";
P_HTM[6940]="*Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā kathaṃ bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ paripūrenti?* **";
P_HTM[6941]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ; dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ … pe … upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6942]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā evaṃ bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiṃ paripūrentī”ti.**That’s how the seven awakening factors are developed and cultivated so as to fulfill knowledge and freedom.”*";
P_HTM[6943]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6944]="*9. Dutiyagiñjakāvasathasuttaṃ**Giving Up the Fetters*";
P_HTM[6945]="*“Ānāpānassatisamādhi, bhikkhave, bhāvito bahulīkato saṃyojanappahānāya saṃvattati … pe ….**“Mendicants, when immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it leads to giving up the fetters …”*";
P_HTM[6946]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6947]="*10. Tatiyagiñjakāvasathasuttaṃ**Uprooting the Tendencies*";
P_HTM[6948]="*“… Anusayasamugghātāya saṃvattati ….**“Mendicants, when immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it leads to uprooting the underlying tendencies …”*";
P_HTM[6949]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6950]="*5. Sagāthakapuññābhisandavaggo**The Second Chapter*";
P_HTM[6951]="*1. Sahassabhikkhunisaṅghasuttaṃ**Completely Understanding the Course of Time*";
P_HTM[6952]="*“… Addhānapariññāya saṃvattati ….**“Mendicants, when immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it leads to completely understanding the course of time …”*";
P_HTM[6953]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6954]="*2. Brāhmaṇasuttaṃ**The Ending of Defilements*";
P_HTM[6955]="*“… Āsavānaṃ khayāya saṃvattati.**“Mendicants, when immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it leads to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[6956]="*Kathaṃ bhāvito ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi kathaṃ bahulīkato saṃyojanappahānāya saṃvattati …**And how is immersion due to mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated so as to lead to giving up the fetters,*";
P_HTM[6957]="*anusayasamugghātāya saṃvattati …**uprooting the underlying tendencies,*";
P_HTM[6958]="*addhānapariññāya saṃvattati …**completely understanding the course of time,*";
P_HTM[6959]="*āsavānaṃ khayāya saṃvattati?**and ending the defilements?*";
P_HTM[6960]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā … pe …**It’s when a mendicant—gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut—sits down cross-legged, with their body straight, and focuses their mindfulness right there. …*";
P_HTM[6961]="*paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmīti sikkhati, paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmīti sikkhati.**They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’*";
P_HTM[6962]="*Evaṃ bhāvito kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi evaṃ bahulīkato saṃyojanappahānāya saṃvattati … pe …**That’s how immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated so as to lead to giving up the fetters,*";
P_HTM[6963]="*anusayasamugghātāya saṃvattati … pe …**uprooting the underlying tendencies,*";
P_HTM[6964]="*addhānapariññāya saṃvattati … pe …**completely understanding the course of time,*";
P_HTM[6965]="*āsavānaṃ khayāya saṃvattatī”ti.**and ending the defilements.”*";
P_HTM[6966]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6967]="*Dutiyo vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[6968]="*Icchānaṅgalaṃ kaṅkheyyaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[6969]="*ānandā apare duve;* **";
P_HTM[6970]="*Bhikkhū saṃyojanānusayā,* **";
P_HTM[6971]="*addhānaṃ āsavakkhayanti.* **";
P_HTM[6972]="*Ānāpānasaṃyuttaṃ dasamaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on Mindfulness of Breathing is the tenth section.*";
P_HTM[6973]="*55. Sotāpattisaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[6974]="*3. Ānandattherasuttaṃ**A Wheel*";
P_HTM[6975]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6976]="*Tatra kho bhagavā … pe … etadavoca:**There the Buddha … said:*";
P_HTM[6977]="*“kiñcāpi, bhikkhave, rājā cakkavattī catunnaṃ dīpānaṃ issariyādhipaccaṃ rajjaṃ kāretvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyataṃ, so tattha nandane vane accharāsaṅghaparivuto dibbehi ca pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāreti, so catūhi dhammehi asamannāgato, atha kho so aparimuttova nirayā aparimutto tiracchānayoniyā aparimutto pettivisayā aparimutto apāyaduggativinipātā.**“Mendicants, suppose a wheel-turning monarch were to rule as sovereign lord over these four continents. And when his body breaks up, after death, he’s reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm, in the company of the gods of the Thirty-Three. There he entertains himself in the Garden of Delight, escorted by a band of nymphs, and supplied and provided with the five kinds of heavenly sensual stimulation. Still, as he’s lacking four things, he’s not exempt from hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm. He’s not exempt from places of loss, bad places, the underworld.*";
P_HTM[6978]="*Kiñcāpi, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako piṇḍiyālopena yāpeti, nantakāni ca dhāreti, so catūhi dhammehi samannāgato, atha kho so parimutto nirayā parimutto tiracchānayoniyā parimutto pettivisayā parimutto apāyaduggativinipātā.**Now suppose a noble disciple wears rags and feeds on scraps of alms-food. Still, as they have four things, they’re exempt from hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm. They’re exempt from places of loss, bad places, the underworld.*";
P_HTM[6979]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6980]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:**It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6981]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[6982]="*Dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:**They have experiential confidence in the teaching:*";
P_HTM[6983]="*‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī’ti.**‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.’*";
P_HTM[6984]="*Saṅghe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:**They have experiential confidence in the Saṅgha:*";
P_HTM[6985]="*‘suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, ujuppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, ñāyappaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, sāmīcippaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, yadidaṃ—cattāri purisayugāni aṭṭha purisapuggalā, esa bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā’ti.**‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the eight individuals. This is the Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples that is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.’*";
P_HTM[6986]="*Ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi acchiddehi asabalehi akammāsehi bhujissehi viññuppasatthehi aparāmaṭṭhehi samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**Furthermore, a noble disciple’s ethical conduct is loved by the noble ones, unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[6987]="*Imehi catūhi dhammehi samannāgato hoti.**These are the four factors of stream-entry that they have.*";
P_HTM[6988]="*Yo ca, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ dīpānaṃ paṭilābho, yo catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭilābho catunnaṃ dīpānaṃ paṭilābho catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭilābhassa kalaṃ nāgghati soḷasin”ti.**And, mendicants, gaining these four continents is not worth a sixteenth part of gaining these four things.”*";
P_HTM[6989]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6990]="*4. Duggatibhayasuttaṃ**The Culmination of the Spiritual Life*";
P_HTM[6991]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo.**“Mendicants, a noble disciple who has four things is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[6992]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6993]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:**It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[6994]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6995]="*Dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[6996]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[6997]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[6998]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo”ti.**A noble disciple who has these four things is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[6999]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7000]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[7001]="*“Yesaṃ saddhā ca sīlañca,**“Those who have faith and ethics,*";
P_HTM[7002]="*Pasādo dhammadassanaṃ;**confidence, and vision of the truth,*";
P_HTM[7003]="*Te ve kālena paccenti,**in time arrive at happiness,*";
P_HTM[7004]="*Brahmacariyogadhaṃ sukhan”ti.**the culmination of the spiritual life.”*";
P_HTM[7005]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7006]="*5. Duggativinipātabhayasuttaṃ**With Dīghāvu*";
P_HTM[7007]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[7008]="*Tena kho pana samayena dīghāvu upāsako ābādhiko hoti dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.**Now at that time the lay follower Dhīgāvu was sick, suffering, gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[7009]="*Atha kho dīghāvu upāsako pitaraṃ jotikaṃ gahapatiṃ āmantesi:**Then he addressed his father, the householder Jotika,*";
P_HTM[7010]="*“ehi tvaṃ, gahapati, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vanda:**“Please, householder, go to the Buddha, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Say to him:*";
P_HTM[7011]="*‘dīghāvu, bhante, upāsako ābādhiko hoti dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.**‘Sir, the lay follower Dhīgāvu is sick, suffering, gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[7012]="*So bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatī’ti.**He bows with his head to your feet.’*";
P_HTM[7013]="*Evañca vadehi:**And then say:*";
P_HTM[7014]="*‘sādhu kira, bhante, bhagavā yena dīghāvussa upāsakassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti.**‘Sir, please visit him at his home out of compassion.’”*";
P_HTM[7015]="*“Evaṃ, tātā”ti kho jotiko gahapati dīghāvussa upāsakassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho jotiko gahapati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, dear,” replied Jotika. He did as Dīghāvu asked.*";
P_HTM[7016]="*“dīghāvu, bhante, upāsako ābādhiko hoti dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.* **";
P_HTM[7017]="*So bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati.* **";
P_HTM[7018]="*Evañca vadeti:* **";
P_HTM[7019]="*‘sādhu kira, bhante, bhagavā yena dīghāvussa upāsakassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7020]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[7021]="*Atha kho bhagavā nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena dīghāvussa upāsakassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho bhagavā dīghāvuṃ upāsakaṃ etadavoca:**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the home of the lay follower Dīghāvu, sat down on the seat spread out, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[7022]="*“kacci te, dīghāvu, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyaṃ? Kacci dukkhā vedanā paṭikkamanti, no abhikkamanti; paṭikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no abhikkamo”ti?**“I hope you’re coping, Dīghāvu; I hope you’re getting better. I hope that your pain is fading, not growing, that its fading is evident, not its growing.”*";
P_HTM[7023]="*“Na me, bhante, khamanīyaṃ, na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti; abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo”ti.**“Sir, I’m not keeping well, I’m not alright. The pain is terrible and growing, not fading; its growing is evident, not its fading.”*";
P_HTM[7024]="*“Tasmātiha te, dīghāvu, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**“So, Dīghāvu, you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[7025]="*‘buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato bhavissāmi—itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.**‘I will have experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7026]="*Dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7027]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7028]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato bhavissāmi akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi’.**And I will have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.’*";
P_HTM[7029]="*Evañhi te, dīghāvu, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7030]="*“Yānimāni, bhante, bhagavatā cattāri sotāpattiyaṅgāni desitāni, saṃvijjante dhammā mayi, ahañca tesu dhammesu sandissāmi.**“Sir, these four factors of stream-entry that were taught by the Buddha are found in me, and I am seen in them.*";
P_HTM[7031]="*Ahañhi, bhante, buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato—itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.**For I have experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7032]="*Dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7033]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7034]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehī”ti.**And I have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.”*";
P_HTM[7035]="*“Tasmātiha tvaṃ, dīghāvu, imesu catūsu sotāpattiyaṅgesu patiṭṭhāya cha vijjābhāgiye dhamme uttari bhāveyyāsi.**“In that case, Dīghāvu, grounded on these four factors of stream-entry you should further develop these six things that play a part in realization.*";
P_HTM[7036]="*Idha tvaṃ, dīghāvu, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī viharāhi, anicce dukkhasaññī, dukkhe anattasaññī pahānasaññī virāgasaññī nirodhasaññīti.**You should meditate observing the impermanence of all conditions, perceiving suffering in impermanence, perceiving not-self in suffering, perceiving giving up, perceiving fading away, and perceiving cessation.*";
P_HTM[7037]="*Evañhi te, dīghāvu, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7038]="*“Yeme, bhante, bhagavatā cha vijjābhāgiyā dhammā desitā, saṃvijjante dhammā mayi, ahañca tesu dhammesu sandissāmi.**“These six things that play a part in realization that were taught by the Buddha are found in me, and I embody them.*";
P_HTM[7039]="*Ahañhi, bhante, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī viharāmi, anicce dukkhasaññī, dukkhe anattasaññī pahānasaññī virāgasaññī nirodhasaññī.**For I meditate observing the impermanence of all conditions, perceiving suffering in impermanence, perceiving not-self in suffering, perceiving giving up, perceiving fading away, and perceiving cessation.*";
P_HTM[7040]="*Api ca me, bhante, evaṃ hoti:**But still, sir, I think,*";
P_HTM[7041]="*‘mā hevāyaṃ jotiko gahapati mamaccayena vighātaṃ āpajjī’”ti.**‘I hope Jotika doesn’t suffer grief when I’ve gone.’”*";
P_HTM[7042]="*“Mā tvaṃ, tāta dīghāvu, evaṃ manasākāsi.**Jotika said, “Dear Dīghāvu, don’t focus on that.*";
P_HTM[7043]="*Iṅgha tvaṃ, tāta dīghāvu, yadeva te bhagavā āha, tadeva tvaṃ sādhukaṃ manasi karohī”ti.**Come on, dear Dīghāvu, you should closely focus on what the Buddha is saying.”*";
P_HTM[7044]="*Atha kho bhagavā dīghāvuṃ upāsakaṃ iminā ovādena ovaditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had given this advice he got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[7045]="*Atha kho dīghāvu upāsako acirapakkantassa bhagavato kālamakāsi.**Not long after the Buddha left, Dīghāvu passed away.*";
P_HTM[7046]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[7047]="*“yo so, bhante, dīghāvu nāma upāsako bhagavatā saṃkhittena ovādena ovadito so kālaṅkato.**“Sir, the lay follower named Dīghāvu, who was advised in brief by the Buddha, has passed away.*";
P_HTM[7048]="*Tassa kā gati, ko abhisamparāyo”ti?**Where has he been reborn in his next life?”*";
P_HTM[7049]="*“Paṇḍito, bhikkhave, dīghāvu upāsako, paccapādi dhammassānudhammaṃ, na ca maṃ dhammādhikaraṇaṃ vihesesi.**“Mendicants, the lay follower Dīghāvu was astute. He practiced in line with the teachings, and did not trouble me about the teachings.*";
P_HTM[7050]="*Dīghāvu, bhikkhave, upāsako pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā”ti.**With the ending of the five lower fetters, he’s been reborn spontaneously, and will become extinguished there, not liable to return from that world.”*";
P_HTM[7051]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7052]="*6. Paṭhamamittāmaccasuttaṃ**With Sāriputta (1st)*";
P_HTM[7053]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca ānando sāvatthiyaṃ viharanti jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time Venerable Sāriputta was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[7054]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Ānanda came out of retreat … and said to Sāriputta:*";
P_HTM[7055]="*“katinaṃ nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, dhammānaṃ samannāgamanahetu evamayaṃ pajā bhagavatā byākatā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā”ti?**“Reverend, how many things do people have to possess in order for the Buddha to declare that they’re a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening?”*";
P_HTM[7056]="*“Catunnaṃ kho, āvuso, dhammānaṃ samannāgamanahetu evamayaṃ pajā bhagavatā byākatā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā.**“Reverend, people have to possess four things in order for the Buddha to declare that they’re a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[7057]="*Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7058]="*Idhāvuso, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—**It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7059]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.* **";
P_HTM[7060]="*Dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7061]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7062]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7063]="*Imesaṃ kho, āvuso, catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ samannāgamanahetu evamayaṃ pajā bhagavatā byākatā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā”ti.**People have to possess these four things in order for the Buddha to declare that they’re a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[7064]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7065]="*7. Dutiyamittāmaccasuttaṃ**With Sāriputta (2nd)*";
P_HTM[7066]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Sāriputta went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[7067]="*“‘sotāpattiyaṅgaṃ, sotāpattiyaṅgan’ti hidaṃ, sāriputta, vuccati.**“Sāriputta, they speak of a ‘factor of stream-entry’.*";
P_HTM[7068]="*Katamaṃ nu kho, sāriputta, sotāpattiyaṅgan”ti?**What is a factor of stream-entry?”*";
P_HTM[7069]="*“Sappurisasaṃsevo hi, bhante, sotāpattiyaṅgaṃ, saddhammassavanaṃ sotāpattiyaṅgaṃ, yonisomanasikāro sotāpattiyaṅgaṃ, dhammānudhammappaṭipatti sotāpattiyaṅgan”ti.**“Sir, the factors of stream-entry are associating with good people, listening to the true teaching, proper attention, and practicing in line with the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[7070]="*“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta.**“Good, good, Sāriputta!*";
P_HTM[7071]="*Sappurisasaṃsevo hi, sāriputta, sotāpattiyaṅgaṃ, saddhammassavanaṃ sotāpattiyaṅgaṃ, yonisomanasikāro sotāpattiyaṅgaṃ, dhammānudhammappaṭipatti sotāpattiyaṅgaṃ.**For the factors of stream-entry are associating with good people, listening to the true teaching, proper attention, and practicing in line with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[7072]="*‘Soto, soto’ti hidaṃ, sāriputta, vuccati.**Sāriputta, they speak of ‘the stream’.*";
P_HTM[7073]="*Katamo nu kho, sāriputta, soto”ti?**What is the stream?”*";
P_HTM[7074]="*“Ayameva hi, bhante, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo soto, seyyathidaṃ—**“Sir, the stream is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[7075]="*sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhī”ti.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.”*";
P_HTM[7076]="*“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta.**“Good, good, Sāriputta!*";
P_HTM[7077]="*Ayameva hi, sāriputta, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo soto, seyyathidaṃ—**For the stream is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[7078]="*sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[7079]="*‘Sotāpanno, sotāpanno’ti hidaṃ, sāriputta, vuccati.**Sāriputta, they speak of ‘a stream-enterer’.*";
P_HTM[7080]="*Katamo nu kho, sāriputta, sotāpanno”ti?**What is a stream-enterer?”*";
P_HTM[7081]="*“Yo hi, bhante, iminā ariyena aṭṭhaṅgikena maggena samannāgato ayaṃ vuccati sotāpanno, svāyaṃ āyasmā evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto”ti.**“Sir, anyone who possesses this noble eightfold path is called a stream-enterer, the venerable of such and such name and clan.”*";
P_HTM[7082]="*“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta.**“Good, good, Sāriputta!*";
P_HTM[7083]="*Yo hi, sāriputta, iminā ariyena aṭṭhaṅgikena maggena samannāgato ayaṃ vuccati sotāpanno, svāyaṃ āyasmā evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto”ti.**For anyone who possesses this noble eightfold path is called a stream-enterer, the venerable of such and such name and clan.”*";
P_HTM[7084]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7085]="*8. Paṭhamadevacārikasuttaṃ**The Chamberlains*";
P_HTM[7086]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī*";
P_HTM[7087]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū bhagavato cīvarakammaṃ karonti:**At that time several mendicants were making a robe for the Buddha, thinking that*";
P_HTM[7088]="*“niṭṭhitacīvaro bhagavā temāsaccayena cārikaṃ pakkamissatī”ti.**when his robe was finished and the three months of the rains residence had passed the Buddha would set out wandering.*";
P_HTM[7089]="*Tena kho pana samayena isidattapurāṇā thapatayo sādhuke paṭivasanti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Now at that time the chamberlains Isidatta and Purāṇa were residing in Sādhuka on some business.*";
P_HTM[7090]="*Assosuṃ kho isidattapurāṇā thapatayo:**They heard about this.*";
P_HTM[7091]="*“sambahulā kira bhikkhū bhagavato cīvarakammaṃ karonti:* **";
P_HTM[7092]="*‘niṭṭhitacīvaro bhagavā temāsaccayena cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7093]="*Atha kho isidattapurāṇā thapatayo magge purisaṃ ṭhapesuṃ:**So they posted someone on the road, saying:*";
P_HTM[7094]="*“yadā tvaṃ, ambho purisa, passeyyāsi bhagavantaṃ āgacchantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ, atha amhākaṃ āroceyyāsī”ti.**“My good man, let us know when you see the Blessed One coming, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[7095]="*Dvīhatīhaṃ ṭhito kho so puriso addasa bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**And that person stood there for two or three days before they saw the Buddha coming off in the distance.*";
P_HTM[7096]="*Disvāna yena isidattapurāṇā thapatayo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā isidattapurāṇe thapatayo etadavoca:**When they saw him, they went to the chamberlains and said:*";
P_HTM[7097]="*“ayaṃ so, bhante, bhagavā āgacchati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho.**“Sirs, the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha is coming.*";
P_HTM[7098]="*Yassadāni kālaṃ maññathā”ti.**Please come at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[7099]="*Atha kho isidattapurāṇā thapatayo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā bhagavantaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhiṃsu.**Then the chamberlains went up to the Buddha, bowed, and followed behind him.*";
P_HTM[7100]="*Atha kho bhagavā maggā okkamma yena aññataraṃ rukkhamūlaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**And then the Buddha left the road, went to the root of a tree, and sat down on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[7101]="*Isidattapurāṇā thapatayo bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**The chamberlains Isidatta and Purāṇa bowed, sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[7102]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te isidattapurāṇā thapatayo bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7103]="*“Yadā mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:**“Sir, when we hear that*";
P_HTM[7104]="*‘sāvatthiyā kosalesu cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye anattamanatā hoti domanassaṃ:**you will be setting out from Sāvatthī to wander in the Kosalan lands, we’re sad and upset, thinking that*";
P_HTM[7105]="*‘dūre no bhagavā bhavissatī’ti.**you will be far from us.*";
P_HTM[7106]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:**And when we hear that*";
P_HTM[7107]="*‘sāvatthiyā kosalesu cārikaṃ pakkanto’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye anattamanatā hoti domanassaṃ:**you are setting out from Sāvatthī to wander in the Kosalan lands, we’re sad and upset, thinking that*";
P_HTM[7108]="*‘dūre no bhagavā’ti.**you are far from us.*";
P_HTM[7109]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:**And when we hear that*";
P_HTM[7110]="*‘kosalehi mallesu cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye anattamanatā hoti domanassaṃ:**you will be setting out from the Kosalan lands to wander in the Mallian lands, we’re sad and upset, thinking that*";
P_HTM[7111]="*‘dūre no bhagavā bhavissatī’ti.**you will be far from us.*";
P_HTM[7112]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:**And when we hear that*";
P_HTM[7113]="*‘kosalehi mallesu cārikaṃ pakkanto’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye anattamanatā hoti domanassaṃ:**you are setting out from the Kosalan lands to wander in the Mallian lands, we’re sad and upset, thinking that*";
P_HTM[7114]="*‘dūre no bhagavā’ti.**you are far from us.*";
P_HTM[7115]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:**And when we hear that*";
P_HTM[7116]="*‘mallehi vajjīsu cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye anattamanatā hoti domanassaṃ:**you will be setting out from the Mallian lands to wander in the Vajjian lands …*";
P_HTM[7117]="*‘dūre no bhagavā bhavissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7118]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:* **";
P_HTM[7119]="*‘mallehi vajjīsu cārikaṃ pakkanto’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye anattamanatā hoti domanassaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[7120]="*‘dūre no bhagavā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7121]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:* **";
P_HTM[7122]="*‘vajjīhi kāsīsu cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye anattamanatā hoti domanassaṃ:**you will be setting out from the Vajjian lands to wander in the Kāsian lands …*";
P_HTM[7123]="*‘dūre no bhagavā bhavissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7124]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:* **";
P_HTM[7125]="*‘vajjīhi kāsīsu cārikaṃ pakkanto’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye anattamanatā hoti domanassaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[7126]="*‘dūre no bhagavā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7127]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:* **";
P_HTM[7128]="*‘kāsīhi māgadhe cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye anattamanatā hoti domanassaṃ:**you will be setting out from the Kāsian lands to wander in the Māgadhan lands …*";
P_HTM[7129]="*‘dūre no bhagavā bhavissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7130]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:* **";
P_HTM[7131]="*‘kāsīhi māgadhe cārikaṃ pakkanto’ti, hoti anappakā no tasmiṃ samaye anattamanatā hoti anappakaṃ domanassaṃ:**you are setting out from the Kāsian lands to wander in the Māgadhan lands, we’re sad and upset, thinking that*";
P_HTM[7132]="*‘dūre no bhagavā’ti.**you are far from us.*";
P_HTM[7133]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:**But when we hear that*";
P_HTM[7134]="*‘māgadhehi kāsīsu cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye attamanatā hoti somanassaṃ:**you will be setting out from the Māgadhan lands to wander in the Kāsian lands, we’re happy and joyful, thinking that*";
P_HTM[7135]="*‘āsanne no bhagavā bhavissatī’ti.**you will be near to us.*";
P_HTM[7136]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:**And when we hear that*";
P_HTM[7137]="*‘māgadhehi kāsīsu cārikaṃ pakkanto’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye attamanatā hoti somanassaṃ:**you are setting out from the Māgadhan lands to wander in the Kāsian lands …*";
P_HTM[7138]="*‘āsanne no bhagavā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7139]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:* **";
P_HTM[7140]="*‘kāsīhi vajjīsu cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye attamanatā hoti somanassaṃ:**you will be setting out from the Kāsian lands to wander in the Vajjian lands …*";
P_HTM[7141]="*‘āsanne no bhagavā bhavissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7142]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:* **";
P_HTM[7143]="*‘kāsīhi vajjīsu cārikaṃ pakkanto’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye attamanatā hoti somanassaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[7144]="*‘āsanne no bhagavā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7145]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:* **";
P_HTM[7146]="*‘vajjīhi mallesu cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye attamanatā hoti somanassaṃ:**you will be setting out from the Vajjian lands to wander in the Mallian lands …*";
P_HTM[7147]="*‘āsanne no bhagavā bhavissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7148]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:* **";
P_HTM[7149]="*‘vajjīhi mallesu cārikaṃ pakkanto’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye attamanatā hoti somanassaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[7150]="*‘āsanne no bhagavā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7151]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:* **";
P_HTM[7152]="*‘mallehi kosale cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye attamanatā hoti somanassaṃ:**you will be setting out from the Mallian lands to wander in the Kosalan lands …*";
P_HTM[7153]="*‘āsanne no bhagavā bhavissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7154]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:* **";
P_HTM[7155]="*‘mallehi kosale cārikaṃ pakkanto’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye attamanatā hoti somanassaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[7156]="*‘āsanne no bhagavā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7157]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:* **";
P_HTM[7158]="*‘kosalehi sāvatthiṃ cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’ti, hoti no tasmiṃ samaye attamanatā hoti somanassaṃ:**you will be setting out in the Kosalan lands to wander to Sāvatthī, we’re happy and joyful, thinking that*";
P_HTM[7159]="*‘āsanne no bhagavā bhavissatī’ti.**you will be near to us.*";
P_HTM[7160]="*Yadā pana mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ suṇāma:**And when we hear that*";
P_HTM[7161]="*‘sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme’ti, hoti anappakā no tasmiṃ samaye attamanatā hoti anappakaṃ somanassaṃ:**you are staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery we have no little happiness and joy, thinking that*";
P_HTM[7162]="*‘āsanne no bhagavā’”ti.**you are near to us.”*";
P_HTM[7163]="*“Tasmātiha, thapatayo, sambādho gharāvāso rajāpatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā.**“Well then, chamberlains, living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is wide open.*";
P_HTM[7164]="*Alañca pana vo, thapatayo, appamādāyā”ti.**Just this much is enough to be diligent.”*";
P_HTM[7165]="*“Atthi kho no, bhante, etamhā sambādhā añño sambādho sambādhataro ceva sambādhasaṅkhātataro cā”ti.**“Sir, for us there is something that’s even more cramped than that, and is considered as such.”*";
P_HTM[7166]="*“Katamo pana vo, thapatayo, etamhā sambādhā añño sambādho sambādhataro ceva sambādhasaṅkhātataro cā”ti?**“What is that?”*";
P_HTM[7167]="*“Idha mayaṃ, bhante, yadā rājā pasenadi kosalo uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyātukāmo hoti, ye te rañño pasenadissa kosalassa nāgā opavayhā te kappetvā, yā tā rañño pasenadissa kosalassa pajāpatiyo piyā manāpā tā ekaṃ purato ekaṃ pacchato nisīdāpema.**“Sir, it’s when King Pasenadi of Kosala wants to go and visit a park. We have to harness and prepare his royal elephants. Then we have to seat his dear and beloved wives on the elephants, one in front of us, and one behind.*";
P_HTM[7168]="*Tāsaṃ kho pana, bhante, bhaginīnaṃ evarūpo gandho hoti, seyyathāpi nāma gandhakaraṇḍakassa tāvadeva vivariyamānassa, yathā taṃ rājakaññānaṃ gandhena vibhūsitānaṃ.**Those sisters smell like a freshly opened perfume box; that’s how the royal ladies smell with makeup on.*";
P_HTM[7169]="*Tāsaṃ kho pana, bhante, bhaginīnaṃ evarūpo kāyasamphasso hoti, seyyathāpi nāma tūlapicuno vā kappāsapicuno vā, yathā taṃ rājakaññānaṃ sukhedhitānaṃ.**The touch of those sisters is like a tuft of cotton-wool or kapok; that’s how dainty the royal ladies are.*";
P_HTM[7170]="*Tasmiṃ kho pana, bhante, samaye nāgopi rakkhitabbo hoti, tāpi bhaginiyo rakkhitabbā honti, attāpi rakkhitabbo hoti.**Now at that time we must look after the elephants, the sisters, and ourselves.*";
P_HTM[7171]="*Na kho pana mayaṃ, bhante, abhijānāma tāsu bhaginīsu pāpakaṃ cittaṃ uppādetā.**But we don’t recall having a bad thought regarding those sisters.*";
P_HTM[7172]="*Ayaṃ kho no, bhante, etamhā sambādhā añño sambādho sambādhataro ceva sambādhasaṅkhātataro cā”ti.**This is that thing that’s even more cramped than that, and is considered as such.”*";
P_HTM[7173]="*“Tasmātiha, thapatayo, sambādho gharāvāso rajāpatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā.**“Well then, chamberlains, living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is wide open.*";
P_HTM[7174]="*Alañca pana vo, thapatayo, appamādāya.**Just this much is enough to be diligent.*";
P_HTM[7175]="*Catūhi kho, thapatayo, dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo.**A noble disciple who has four things is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[7176]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7177]="*Idha, thapatayo, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—**It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7178]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.* **";
P_HTM[7179]="*Dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7180]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7181]="*vigatamalamaccherena cetasā ajjhāgāraṃ vasati muttacāgo payatapāṇi vossaggarato yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato.**They live at home rid of the stain of stinginess, freely generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to give and to share.*";
P_HTM[7182]="*Imehi kho, thapatayo, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo.**A noble disciple who has these four things is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[7183]="*Tumhe kho, thapatayo, buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgatā—**And you have experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7184]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.* **";
P_HTM[7185]="*Dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7186]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7187]="*yaṃ kho pana kiñci kule deyyadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ appaṭivibhattaṃ sīlavantehi kalyāṇadhammehi.**And whatever there is in your family that’s available to give, you share it all with those who are ethical, of good character.*";
P_HTM[7188]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, thapatayo,**What do you think, chamberlains?*";
P_HTM[7189]="*katividhā te kosalesu manussā ye tumhākaṃ samasamā, yadidaṃ—**How many people among the Kosalans are your equal*";
P_HTM[7190]="*dānasaṃvibhāge”ti?**when it comes to giving and sharing?”*";
P_HTM[7191]="*“Lābhā no, bhante, suladdhaṃ no, bhante.**“We’re fortunate, sir, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[7192]="*Yesaṃ no bhagavā evaṃ pajānātī”ti.**in that the Buddha understands us like this.”*";
P_HTM[7193]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7194]="*9. Dutiyadevacārikasuttaṃ**The People of Bamboo Gate*";
P_HTM[7195]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7196]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena veḷudvāraṃ nāma kosalānaṃ brāhmaṇagāmo tadavasari.**At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a village of the Kosalan brahmins named Bamboo Gate.*";
P_HTM[7197]="*Assosuṃ kho te veḷudvāreyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā:**The brahmins and householders of Bamboo Gate heard:*";
P_HTM[7198]="*“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ veḷudvāraṃ anuppatto.**“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—has arrived at Bamboo Gate, together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[7199]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[7200]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[7201]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[7202]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[7203]="*Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti.**It’s good to see such perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[7204]="*Atha kho te veḷudvāreyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu; sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce bhagavato santike nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te veḷudvāreyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then the brahmins and householders of Bamboo Gate went up to the Buddha. Before sitting down to one side, some bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent. Seated to one side they said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7205]="*“mayaṃ, bho gotama, evaṅkāmā evaṃchandā evaṃadhippāyā—**“Master Gotama, these are our wishes, desires, and hopes.*";
P_HTM[7206]="*puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvaseyyāma, kāsikacandanaṃ paccanubhaveyyāma, mālāgandhavilepanaṃ dhāreyyāma, jātarūparajataṃ sādiyeyyāma, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyyāma.**We wish to live at home with our children; to use sandalwood imported from Kāsi; to wear garlands, perfumes, and makeup; and to accept gold and money. And when our body breaks up, after death, we wish to be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[7207]="*Tesaṃ no bhavaṃ gotamo amhākaṃ evaṅkāmānaṃ evaṃchandānaṃ evaṃadhippāyānaṃ tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā mayaṃ puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvaseyyāma … pe … sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyyāmā”ti.**Given that we have such wishes, may the Buddha teach us the Dhamma so that we may achieve them.”*";
P_HTM[7208]="*“Attupanāyikaṃ vo, gahapatayo, dhammapariyāyaṃ desessāmi.**“Householders, I will teach you an explanation of the Dhamma that’s relevant to oneself.*";
P_HTM[7209]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[7210]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho te veḷudvāreyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[7211]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[7212]="*“Katamo ca, gahapatayo, attupanāyiko dhammapariyāyo?**“And what is the explanation of the Dhamma that’s relevant to oneself?*";
P_HTM[7213]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**It’s when a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[7214]="*‘ahaṃ khosmi jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhappaṭikūlo.**‘I want to live and don’t want to die; I want to be happy and recoil from pain.*";
P_HTM[7215]="*Yo kho maṃ jīvitukāmaṃ amaritukāmaṃ sukhakāmaṃ dukkhappaṭikūlaṃ jīvitā voropeyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ.**Since this is so, if someone were to take my life, I wouldn’t like that.*";
P_HTM[7216]="*Ahañceva kho pana paraṃ jīvitukāmaṃ amaritukāmaṃ sukhakāmaṃ dukkhappaṭikūlaṃ jīvitā voropeyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ assa appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ.**But others also want to live and don’t want to die; they want to be happy and recoil from pain. So if I were to take the life of someone else, they wouldn’t like that either.*";
P_HTM[7217]="*Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, parassa peso dhammo appiyo amanāpo.**The thing that is disliked by me is also disliked by others.*";
P_HTM[7218]="*Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, kathāhaṃ paraṃ tena saṃyojeyyan’ti.**Since I dislike this thing, how can I inflict it on someone else?’*";
P_HTM[7219]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya attanā ca pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, parañca pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**Reflecting in this way, they give up killing living creatures themselves. And they encourage others to give up killing living creatures, praising the giving up of killing living creatures.*";
P_HTM[7220]="*Evamassāyaṃ kāyasamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti.**So their bodily behavior is purified in three points.*";
P_HTM[7221]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[7222]="*‘yo kho me adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyeyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ.**‘If someone were to steal from me, I wouldn’t like that.*";
P_HTM[7223]="*Ahañceva kho pana parassa adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyeyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ assa appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ.**But if I were to steal from someone else, they wouldn’t like that either.*";
P_HTM[7224]="*Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, parassa peso dhammo appiyo amanāpo.**The thing that is disliked by me is also disliked by others.*";
P_HTM[7225]="*Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, kathāhaṃ paraṃ tena saṃyojeyyan’ti.**Since I dislike this thing, how can I inflict it on someone else?’*";
P_HTM[7226]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya attanā ca adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, parañca adinnādānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, adinnādānā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**Reflecting in this way, they give up stealing themselves. And they encourage others to give up stealing, praising the giving up of stealing.*";
P_HTM[7227]="*Evamassāyaṃ kāyasamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti.**So their bodily behavior is purified in three points.*";
P_HTM[7228]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[7229]="*‘yo kho me dāresu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ.**‘If someone were to have sexual relations with my wives, I wouldn’t like it.*";
P_HTM[7230]="*Ahañceva kho pana parassa dāresu cārittaṃ āpajjeyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ assa appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ.**But if I were to have sexual relations with someone else’s wives, he wouldn’t like that either.*";
P_HTM[7231]="*Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, parassa peso dhammo appiyo amanāpo.**The thing that is disliked by me is also disliked by others.*";
P_HTM[7232]="*Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, kathāhaṃ paraṃ tena saṃyojeyyan’ti.**Since I dislike this thing, how can I inflict it on others?’*";
P_HTM[7233]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya attanā ca kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**Reflecting in this way, they give up sexual misconduct themselves. And they encourage others to give up sexual misconduct, praising the giving up of sexual misconduct.*";
P_HTM[7234]="*Evamassāyaṃ kāyasamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti.**So their bodily behavior is purified in three points.*";
P_HTM[7235]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[7236]="*‘yo kho me musāvādena atthaṃ bhañjeyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ.**‘If someone were to distort my meaning by lying, I wouldn’t like it.*";
P_HTM[7237]="*Ahañceva kho pana parassa musāvādena atthaṃ bhañjeyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ assa appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ.**But if I were to distort someone else’s meaning by lying, they wouldn’t like it either.*";
P_HTM[7238]="*Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, parassa peso dhammo appiyo amanāpo.**The thing that is disliked by me is also disliked by someone else.*";
P_HTM[7239]="*Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, kathāhaṃ paraṃ tena saṃyojeyyan’ti.**Since I dislike this thing, how can I inflict it on others?’*";
P_HTM[7240]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya attanā ca musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, parañca musāvādā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, musāvādā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**Reflecting in this way, they give up lying themselves. And they encourage others to give up lying, praising the giving up of lying.*";
P_HTM[7241]="*Evamassāyaṃ vacīsamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti.**So their verbal behavior is purified in three points.*";
P_HTM[7242]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[7243]="*“yo kho maṃ pisuṇāya vācāya mitte bhindeyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ.**‘If someone were to break me up from my friends by divisive speech, I wouldn’t like it.*";
P_HTM[7244]="*Ahañceva kho pana paraṃ pisuṇāya vācāya mitte bhindeyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ assa appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ … pe …**But if I were to break someone else from their friends by divisive speech, they wouldn’t like it either. …’*";
P_HTM[7245]="*evamassāyaṃ vacīsamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti.**So their verbal behavior is purified in three points.*";
P_HTM[7246]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[7247]="*“yo kho maṃ pharusāya vācāya samudācareyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ.**‘If someone were to attack me with harsh speech, I wouldn’t like it.*";
P_HTM[7248]="*Ahañceva kho pana paraṃ pharusāya vācāya samudācareyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ assa appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ.**But if I were to attack someone else with harsh speech, they wouldn’t like it either. …’*";
P_HTM[7249]="*Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7250]="*evamassāyaṃ vacīsamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti.**So their verbal behavior is purified in three points.*";
P_HTM[7251]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[7252]="*‘yo kho maṃ samphabhāsena samphappalāpabhāsena samudācareyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ.**‘If someone were to annoy me by talking silliness and nonsense, I wouldn’t like it.*";
P_HTM[7253]="*Ahañceva kho pana paraṃ samphabhāsena samphappalāpabhāsena samudācareyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ assa appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ.**But if I were to annoy someone else by talking silliness and nonsense, they wouldn’t like it either.’*";
P_HTM[7254]="*Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, parassa peso dhammo appiyo amanāpo.**The thing that is disliked by me is also disliked by another.*";
P_HTM[7255]="*Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, kathāhaṃ paraṃ tena saṃyojeyyan’ti.**Since I dislike this thing, how can I inflict it on another?’*";
P_HTM[7256]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya attanā ca samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, parañca samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**Reflecting in this way, they give up talking nonsense themselves. And they encourage others to give up talking nonsense, praising the giving up of talking nonsense.*";
P_HTM[7257]="*Evamassāyaṃ vacīsamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti.**So their verbal behavior is purified in three points.*";
P_HTM[7258]="*So buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—**And they have experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7259]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti;* **";
P_HTM[7260]="*dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7261]="*saṃghe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṃgho … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassāti.**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7262]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7263]="*Yato kho, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako imehi sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti imehi catūhi ākaṅkhiyehi ṭhānehi, so ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:**When a noble disciple has these seven good qualities and these four desirable states they may, if they wish, declare of themselves:*";
P_HTM[7264]="*‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’”ti.**‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound for awakening.’”*";
P_HTM[7265]="*Evaṃ vutte, veḷudvāreyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When he had spoken, the brahmins and householders of Bamboo Gate said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7266]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**“Excellent, Master Gotama! …*";
P_HTM[7267]="*ete mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca.**We go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[7268]="*Upāsake no bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupete saraṇaṃ gate”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember us as lay followers who have gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[7269]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7270]="*10. Tatiyadevacārikasuttaṃ**In the Brick Hall (1st)*";
P_HTM[7271]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7272]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā ñātike viharati giñjakāvasathe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Nādika in the brick house.*";
P_HTM[7273]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[7274]="*“Sāḷho nāma, bhante, bhikkhu kālaṅkato;**“Sir, the monk named Sāḷha has passed away.*";
P_HTM[7275]="*tassa kā gati ko abhisamparāyo?**Where has he been reborn in his next life?*";
P_HTM[7276]="*Nandā nāma, bhante, bhikkhunī kālaṅkatā;**The nun named Nandā,*";
P_HTM[7277]="*tassā kā gati ko abhisamparāyo?* **";
P_HTM[7278]="*Sudatto nāma, bhante, upāsako kālaṅkato;**the layman named Sudatta,*";
P_HTM[7279]="*tassa kā gati ko abhisamparāyo?* **";
P_HTM[7280]="*Sujātā nāma, bhante, upāsikā kālaṅkatā;**and the laywoman named Sujātā have passed away.*";
P_HTM[7281]="*tassā kā gati, ko abhisamparāyo”ti?**Where have they been reborn in the next life?”*";
P_HTM[7282]="*“Sāḷho, ānanda, bhikkhu kālaṅkato āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi.**“Ānanda, the monk Sāḷha passed away having realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, having realized it with his own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[7283]="*Nandā, ānanda, bhikkhunī kālaṅkatā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyinī anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā.**The nun Nandā passed away having ended the five lower fetters. She’s been reborn spontaneously, and will be extinguished there, not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[7284]="*Sudatto, ānanda, upāsako kālaṅkato tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmī; sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissati.**The layman Sudatta passed away having ended three fetters, and weakened greed, hate, and delusion. He’s a once-returner; he will come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering.*";
P_HTM[7285]="*Sujātā, ānanda, upāsikā kālaṅkatā tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā.**The laywoman Sujātā passed away having ended three fetters. She’s a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[7286]="*Anacchariyaṃ kho panetaṃ, ānanda, yaṃ manussabhūto kālaṃ kareyya;**It’s hardly surprising that a human being should pass away.*";
P_HTM[7287]="*tasmiṃ tasmiñce maṃ kālaṅkate upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipucchissatha. Vihesā pesā, ānanda, assa tathāgatassa.**But if you should come and ask me about it each and every time someone dies that would be a bother for me.*";
P_HTM[7288]="*Tasmātihānanda, dhammādāsaṃ nāma dhammapariyāyaṃ desessāmi; yena samannāgato ariyasāvako ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:**So Ānanda, I will teach you the explanation of the Dhamma called ‘the mirror of the teaching’. A noble disciple who has this may declare of themselves:*";
P_HTM[7289]="*‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’.**‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound for awakening.’*";
P_HTM[7290]="*Katamo ca so, ānanda, dhammādāso dhammapariyāyo; yena samannāgato ariyasāvako ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:**And what is that mirror of the teaching?*";
P_HTM[7291]="*‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’?* **";
P_HTM[7292]="*Idha, ānanda, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.**It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7293]="*Dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7294]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7295]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7296]="*Ayaṃ kho so, ānanda, dhammādāso dhammapariyāyo;**This is that mirror of the teaching.*";
P_HTM[7297]="*yena samannāgato ariyasāvako ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:**A noble disciple who has this may declare of themselves:*";
P_HTM[7298]="*‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’”ti.**‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound for awakening.’”*";
P_HTM[7299]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7300]="*(Tīṇipi suttantāni ekanidānāni.)**(The following two discourses have the same setting.)*";
P_HTM[7301]="*6. Sappaññavaggo**At Bamboo Gate*";
P_HTM[7302]="*1. Paṭhamamahānāmasuttaṃ**At the Brick Hall (2nd)*";
P_HTM[7303]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Ānanda said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7304]="*“asoko nāma, bhante, bhikkhu kālaṅkato;**“Sir, the monk named Asoka has passed away.*";
P_HTM[7305]="*tassa kā gati, ko abhisamparāyo?**Where has he been reborn in his next life?*";
P_HTM[7306]="*Asokā nāma, bhante, bhikkhunī kālaṅkatā … pe …**The nun named Asokā,*";
P_HTM[7307]="*asoko nāma, bhante, upāsako kālaṅkato … pe …**the layman named Asoka,*";
P_HTM[7308]="*asokā nāma, bhante, upāsikā kālaṅkatā;**and the laywoman named Asokā have passed away.*";
P_HTM[7309]="*tassā kā gati, ko abhisamparāyo”ti?**Where have they been reborn in the next life?”*";
P_HTM[7310]="*“Asoko, ānanda, bhikkhu kālaṅkato āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi … pe …**“Ānanda, the monk Asoka passed away having realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life …*";
P_HTM[7311]="*(purimaveyyākaraṇena ekanidānaṃ.)**(And all is explained as in SN 55.8)*";
P_HTM[7312]="*Ayaṃ kho so, ānanda, dhammādāso dhammapariyāyo;**This is that mirror of the teaching.*";
P_HTM[7313]="*yena samannāgato ariyasāvako ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:**A noble disciple who has this may declare of themselves:*";
P_HTM[7314]="*‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’”ti.**‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound for awakening.’”*";
P_HTM[7315]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7316]="*2. Dutiyamahānāmasuttaṃ**At the Brick Hall (3rd)*";
P_HTM[7317]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Ānanda said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7318]="*“kakkaṭo nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako kālaṅkato;**“Sir, the layman named Kakkaṭa has passed away in Nādika.*";
P_HTM[7319]="*tassa kā gati, ko abhisamparāyo?**Where has he been reborn in his next life?*";
P_HTM[7320]="*Kaḷibho nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako … pe …**The laymen named Kaḷibha,*";
P_HTM[7321]="*nikato nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako …**Nikata,*";
P_HTM[7322]="*kaṭissaho nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako …**Kaṭissaha,*";
P_HTM[7323]="*tuṭṭho nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako …**Tuṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[7324]="*santuṭṭho nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako …**Santuṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[7325]="*bhaddo nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako …**Bhadda, and*";
P_HTM[7326]="*subhaddo nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako kālaṅkato;**Subhadda have passed away in Nādika.*";
P_HTM[7327]="*tassa kā gati ko abhisamparāyo”ti?**Where have they been reborn in the next life?”*";
P_HTM[7328]="*“Kakkaṭo, ānanda, upāsako kālaṅkato pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā.**“Ānanda, the laymen Kakkaṭa,*";
P_HTM[7329]="*Kaḷibho, ānanda … pe …**Kaḷibha,*";
P_HTM[7330]="*nikato, ānanda …**Nikata,*";
P_HTM[7331]="*kaṭissaho, ānanda …**Kaṭissaha,*";
P_HTM[7332]="*tuṭṭho, ānanda …**Tuṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[7333]="*santuṭṭho, ānanda …**Santuṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[7334]="*bhaddo, ānanda … pe …**Bhadda,*";
P_HTM[7335]="*subhaddo, ānanda, upāsako kālaṅkato pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā.**and Subhadda passed away having ended the five lower fetters. They’ve been reborn spontaneously, and will be extinguished there, not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[7336]="*(Sabbe ekagatikā kātabbā.)* **";
P_HTM[7337]="*Paropaññāsa, ānanda, ñātike upāsakā kālaṅkatā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyino anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā.**Over fifty laymen in Nādika have passed away having ended the five lower fetters. They’ve been reborn spontaneously, and will be extinguished there, not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[7338]="*Sādhikanavuti, ānanda, ñātike upāsakā kālaṅkatā tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmino; sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissanti.**More than ninety laymen in Nādika have passed away having ended three fetters, and weakened greed, hate, and delusion. They’re once-returners, who will come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering.*";
P_HTM[7339]="*Chātirekāni kho, ānanda, pañcasatāni ñātike upāsakā kālaṅkatā tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā.**In excess of five hundred laymen in Nādika have passed away having ended three fetters. They’re stream-enterers, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[7340]="*Anacchariyaṃ kho panetaṃ, ānanda, yaṃ manussabhūto kālaṃ kareyya;**It’s hardly surprising that a human being should pass away.*";
P_HTM[7341]="*tasmiṃ tasmiñce maṃ kālaṅkate upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipucchissatha. Vihesā pesā, ānanda, assa tathāgatassa.**But if you should come and ask me about it each and every time someone passes away, that would be a bother for me.*";
P_HTM[7342]="*Tasmātihānanda, dhammādāsaṃ nāma dhammapariyāyaṃ desessāmi; yena samannāgato ariyasāvako ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:**So Ānanda, I will teach you the explanation of the Dhamma called ‘the mirror of the teaching’. A noble disciple who has this may declare of themselves:*";
P_HTM[7343]="*‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’.**‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound for awakening.’*";
P_HTM[7344]="*Katamo ca so, ānanda, dhammādāso dhammapariyāyo; yena samannāgato ariyasāvako ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:**And what is that mirror of the teaching?*";
P_HTM[7345]="*‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’.* **";
P_HTM[7346]="*Idhānanda, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.**It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7347]="*Dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7348]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7349]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7350]="*Ayaṃ kho so, ānanda, dhammādāso dhammapariyāyo;**This is that mirror of the teaching.*";
P_HTM[7351]="*yena samannāgato ariyasāvako ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:**A noble disciple who has this may declare of themselves:*";
P_HTM[7352]="*‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’”ti.**‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound for awakening.’”*";
P_HTM[7353]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7354]="*Veḷudvāravaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[7355]="*Rājā ogadhadīghāvu,* **";
P_HTM[7356]="*sāriputtāpare duve;* **";
P_HTM[7357]="*Thapatī veḷudvāreyyā,* **";
P_HTM[7358]="*giñjakāvasathe tayoti.* **";
P_HTM[7359]="*3. Godhasakkasuttaṃ**A Saṅgha of a Thousand Nuns*";
P_HTM[7360]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati rājakārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Royal Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7361]="*Atha kho sahassabhikkhunisaṃgho yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhagavā etadavoca:**Then a Saṅgha of a thousand nuns went up to the Buddha, bowed, and stood to one side. The Buddha said to them:*";
P_HTM[7362]="*“Catūhi kho, bhikkhuniyo, dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo.**“Nuns, a noble disciple who has four things is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[7363]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7364]="*Idha, bhikkhuniyo, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—**It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7365]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.* **";
P_HTM[7366]="*Dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7367]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7368]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti, akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7369]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhuniyo, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo”ti.**A noble disciple who has these four things is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[7370]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7371]="*4. Paṭhamasaraṇānisakkasuttaṃ**The Brahmins*";
P_HTM[7372]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī*";
P_HTM[7373]="*“Brāhmaṇā, bhikkhave, udayagāminiṃ nāma paṭipadaṃ paññapenti.**“Mendicants, the brahmins advocate a practice called ‘get up and go’.*";
P_HTM[7374]="*Te sāvakaṃ evaṃ samādapenti:**They encourage their disciples:*";
P_HTM[7375]="*‘ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, kālasseva uṭṭhāya pācīnamukho yāhi.**‘Please, good people, rising early you should face east and walk.*";
P_HTM[7376]="*So tvaṃ mā sobbhaṃ parivajjehi, mā papātaṃ, mā khāṇuṃ, mā kaṇḍakaṭhānaṃ, mā candaniyaṃ, mā oḷigallaṃ.**Do not avoid a pit, a cliff, a stump, thorny ground, a swamp, or a sewer.*";
P_HTM[7377]="*Yattha papateyyāsi tattheva maraṇaṃ āgameyyāsi.**You should await death in the place that you fall.*";
P_HTM[7378]="*Evaṃ tvaṃ, ambho purisa, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissasī’ti.**And when your body breaks up, after death, you’ll be reborn in a good place, a heaven realm.’*";
P_HTM[7379]="*Taṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇānaṃ bālagamanametaṃ mūḷhagamanametaṃ na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati.**But this practice of the brahmins is a foolish procedure, a stupid procedure. It doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, or extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[7380]="*Ahañca kho, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye udayagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ paññāpemi;**But in the training of the noble one I advocate a ‘get up and go’ practice*";
P_HTM[7381]="*yā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati.**which does lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[7382]="*Katamā ca sā, bhikkhave, udayagāminī paṭipadā;**And what is that ‘get up and go’ practice?*";
P_HTM[7383]="*yā ekantanibbidāya … pe … nibbānāya saṃvattati?* **";
P_HTM[7384]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—**It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7385]="*itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti;* **";
P_HTM[7386]="*dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7387]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7388]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7389]="*Ayaṃ kho sā, bhikkhave, udayagāminī paṭipadā ekantanibbidāya … pe …**This is that ‘get up and go’ practice*";
P_HTM[7390]="*nibbānāya saṃvattatī”ti.**which does lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.”*";
P_HTM[7391]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7392]="*5. Dutiyasaraṇānisakkasuttaṃ**With the Senior Monk Ānanda*";
P_HTM[7393]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca ānando āyasmā ca sāriputto sāvatthiyaṃ viharanti jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the venerables Ānanda and Sāriputta were staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[7394]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to Venerable Ānanda, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[7395]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to him:*";
P_HTM[7396]="*“katinaṃ kho, āvuso ānanda, dhammānaṃ pahānā, katinaṃ dhammānaṃ samannāgamanahetu, evamayaṃ pajā bhagavatā byākatā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā”ti?**“Reverend, how many things do people have to give up and how many do they have to possess in order for the Buddha to declare that they’re a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening?”*";
P_HTM[7397]="*“Catunnaṃ kho, āvuso, dhammānaṃ pahānā, catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ samannāgamanahetu, evamayaṃ pajā bhagavatā byākatā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇāti.**“Reverend, people have to give up four things and possess four things in order for the Buddha to declare that they’re a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[7398]="*Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7399]="*Yathārūpena kho, āvuso, buddhe appasādena samannāgato assutavā puthujjano kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati tathārūpassa buddhe appasādo na hoti.**They don’t have the distrust in the Buddha that causes an uneducated ordinary person to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[7400]="*Yathārūpena ca kho, āvuso, buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato sutavā ariyasāvako kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati tathārūpassa buddhe aveccappasādo hoti—**And they do have the experiential confidence in the Buddha that causes an educated noble disciple to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[7401]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[7402]="*Yathārūpena ca kho, āvuso, dhamme appasādena samannāgato assutavā puthujjano kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati tathārūpassa dhamme appasādo na hoti.**They don’t have the distrust in the teaching that causes an uneducated ordinary person to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[7403]="*Yathārūpena ca kho, āvuso, dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato sutavā ariyasāvako kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati tathārūpassa dhamme aveccappasādo hoti—**And they do have the experiential confidence in the teaching that causes an educated noble disciple to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[7404]="*svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo … pe … viññūhīti.**‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.’*";
P_HTM[7405]="*Yathārūpena ca kho, āvuso, saṅghe appasādena samannāgato assutavā puthujjano kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati tathārūpassa saṅghe appasādo na hoti.**They don’t have the distrust in the Saṅgha that causes an uneducated ordinary person to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[7406]="*Yathārūpena ca kho, āvuso, saṅghe aveccappasādena samannāgato sutavā ariyasāvako kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati tathārūpassa saṅghe aveccappasādo hoti—**And they do have the experiential confidence in the Saṅgha that causes an educated noble disciple to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[7407]="*suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassāti.**‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the eight individuals. This Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, and worthy of veneration with joined palms.’*";
P_HTM[7408]="*Yathārūpena ca kho, āvuso, dussīlyena samannāgato assutavā puthujjano kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati tathārūpassa dussīlyaṃ na hoti.**They don’t have the unethical conduct that causes an uneducated ordinary person to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[7409]="*Yathārūpehi ca kho, āvuso, ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato sutavā ariyasāvako kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati tathārūpāni ariyakantāni sīlāni honti akhaṇḍāni … pe …**And they do have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones that causes an educated noble disciple to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[7410]="*samādhisaṃvattanikāni.**Their ethical conduct is loved by the noble ones, unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7411]="*Imesaṃ kho, āvuso, catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānā imesaṃ catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ samannāgamanahetu evamayaṃ pajā bhagavatā byākatā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā”ti.**People have to give up these four things and possess these four things in order for the Buddha to declare that they’re a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[7412]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7413]="*6. Paṭhamaanāthapiṇḍikasuttaṃ**Fear of the Bad Place*";
P_HTM[7414]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako sabbaduggatibhayaṃ samatikkanto hoti.**“Mendicants, a noble disciple who has four things has gone beyond all fear of being reborn in a bad place.*";
P_HTM[7415]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7416]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—**It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7417]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.* **";
P_HTM[7418]="*Dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7419]="*saṃghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7420]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7421]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako sabbaduggatibhayaṃ samatikkanto hotī”ti.**A noble disciple who has these four things has gone beyond all fear of being reborn in a bad place.”*";
P_HTM[7422]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7423]="*7. Dutiyaanāthapiṇḍikasuttaṃ**Fear of the Bad Place, the Underworld*";
P_HTM[7424]="*“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako sabbaduggativinipātabhayaṃ samatikkanto hoti.**“Mendicants, a noble disciple who has four things has gone beyond all fear of being reborn in a bad place, the underworld.*";
P_HTM[7425]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7426]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—**It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7427]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.* **";
P_HTM[7428]="*Dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7429]="*saṃghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7430]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7431]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako sabbaduggativinipātabhayaṃ samatikkanto hotī”ti.**A noble disciple who has these four things has gone beyond all fear of being reborn in a bad place, the underworld.”*";
P_HTM[7432]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7433]="*8. Paṭhamabhayaverūpasantasuttaṃ**Friends and Colleagues (1st)*";
P_HTM[7434]="*“Ye te, bhikkhave, anukampeyyātha, ye ca sotabbaṃ maññeyyuṃ—mittā vā amaccā vā ñātī vā sālohitā vā—te, bhikkhave, catūsu sotāpattiyaṅgesu samādapetabbā, nivesetabbā, patiṭṭhāpetabbā.**“Mendicants, those who you have sympathy for, and those worth listening to—friends and colleagues, relatives and family—should be encouraged, supported, and established in the four factors of stream-entry.*";
P_HTM[7435]="*Katamesu catūsu?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7436]="*Buddhe aveccappasāde samādapetabbā, nivesetabbā, patiṭṭhāpetabbā—**Experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7437]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.* **";
P_HTM[7438]="*Dhamme … pe …**the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7439]="*saṃghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7440]="*ariyakantesu sīlesu samādapetabbā, nivesetabbā, patiṭṭhāpetabbā akhaṇḍesu … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikesu.**And the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7441]="*Ye te, bhikkhave, anukampeyyātha, ye ca sotabbaṃ maññeyyuṃ—mittā vā amaccā vā ñātī vā sālohitā vā—te, bhikkhave, imesu catūsu sotāpattiyaṅgesu samādapetabbā, nivesetabbā, patiṭṭhāpetabbā”ti.**Those who you have sympathy for, and those worth listening to—friends and colleagues, relatives and family—should be encouraged, supported, and established in these four factors of stream-entry.”*";
P_HTM[7442]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7443]="*9. Dutiyabhayaverūpasantasuttaṃ**Friends and Colleagues (2nd)*";
P_HTM[7444]="*“Ye te, bhikkhave, anukampeyyātha, ye ca sotabbaṃ maññeyyuṃ—mittā vā amaccā vā ñātī vā sālohitā vā—te, bhikkhave, catūsu sotāpattiyaṅgesu samādapetabbā, nivesetabbā, patiṭṭhāpetabbā.**“Mendicants, those who you have sympathy for, and those worth listening to—friends and colleagues, relatives and family—should be encouraged, supported, and established in the four factors of stream-entry.*";
P_HTM[7445]="*Katamesu catūsu?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7446]="*Buddhe aveccappasāde samādapetabbā, nivesetabbā, patiṭṭhāpetabbā—**Experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7447]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.* **";
P_HTM[7448]="*Siyā, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ mahābhūtānaṃ aññathattaṃ—pathavīdhātuyā, āpodhātuyā, tejodhātuyā, vāyodhātuyā—na tveva buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgatassa ariyasāvakassa siyā aññathattaṃ.**There might be change in the four primary elements—earth, water, fire, and air—but a noble disciple with experiential confidence in the Buddha would never change.*";
P_HTM[7449]="*Tatridaṃ aññathattaṃ—so vata buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato ariyasāvako nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā pettivisayaṃ vā upapajjissatī”ti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**In this context, ‘change’ means that such a noble disciple will be reborn in hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm: this is not possible.*";
P_HTM[7450]="*“Dhamme … pe …**Experiential confidence in the teaching …*";
P_HTM[7451]="*saṅghe … pe …**Experiential confidence in the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7452]="*ariyakantesu sīlesu samādapetabbā, nivesetabbā, patiṭṭhāpetabbā akhaṇḍesu … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikesu.**The ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7453]="*Siyā, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ mahābhūtānaṃ aññathattaṃ—pathavīdhātuyā, āpodhātuyā, tejodhātuyā, vāyodhātuyā—na tveva ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgatassa ariyasāvakassa siyā aññathattaṃ.**There might be change in the four primary elements—earth, water, fire, and air—but a noble disciple with the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones would never change.*";
P_HTM[7454]="*Tatridaṃ aññathattaṃ—so vata ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato ariyasāvako nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā pettivisayaṃ vā upapajjissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**In this context, ‘change’ means that such a noble disciple will be reborn in hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm: this is not possible.*";
P_HTM[7455]="*Ye te, bhikkhave, anukampeyyātha, ye ca sotabbaṃ maññeyyuṃ—mittā vā amaccā vā ñātī vā sālohitā vā—te, bhikkhave, imesu catūsu sotāpattiyaṅgesu samādapetabbā, nivesetabbā, patiṭṭhāpetabbā”ti.**Those who you have sympathy for, and those worth listening to—friends and colleagues, relatives and family—should be encouraged, supported, and established in these four factors of stream-entry.”*";
P_HTM[7456]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7457]="*10. Nandakalicchavisuttaṃ**A Visit to the Gods (1st)*";
P_HTM[7458]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī*";
P_HTM[7459]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—jetavane antarahito devesu tāvatiṃsesu pāturahosi.**And then Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, vanished from Jeta’s Grove and reappeared among the gods of the Thirty-Three.*";
P_HTM[7460]="*Atha kho sambahulā tāvatiṃsakāyikā devatāyo yenāyasmā mahāmoggallāno tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho tā devatāyo āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca:**Then several deities of the company of the Thirty-Three went up to Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, bowed, and stood to one side. Moggallāna said to them:*";
P_HTM[7461]="*“Sādhu kho, āvuso, buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgamanaṃ hoti—**“Reverends, it’s good to have experiential confidence in the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[7462]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.* **";
P_HTM[7463]="*Buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgamanahetu kho, āvuso, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti.**It’s the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[7464]="*Sādhu kho, āvuso, dhamme … pe …**It’s good to have experiential confidence in the teaching. …*";
P_HTM[7465]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7466]="*sādhu kho, āvuso, ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgamanaṃ hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**and to have the ethical conduct that’s loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7467]="*Ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgamanahetu kho, āvuso, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti.**It’s the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.”*";
P_HTM[7468]="*“Sādhu kho, mārisa moggallāna, buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgamanaṃ hoti—**“My good Moggallāna, it’s good to have experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7469]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.* **";
P_HTM[7470]="*Buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgamanahetu kho, mārisa moggallāna, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti.**It’s the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[7471]="*Sādhu kho, mārisa moggallāna, dhamme … pe …**It’s good to have experiential confidence in the teaching. …*";
P_HTM[7472]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7473]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgamanaṃ hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**and to have the ethical conduct that’s loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7474]="*Ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgamanahetu kho, mārisa moggallāna, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti.**It’s the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.”*";
P_HTM[7475]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7476]="*7. Mahāpaññavaggo**A Thousand Nuns*";
P_HTM[7477]="*1. Paṭhamapuññābhisandasuttaṃ**A Visit to the Gods (2nd)*";
P_HTM[7478]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7479]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—jetavane antarahito devesu tāvatiṃsesu pāturahosi.**And then Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, vanished from Jeta’s Grove and reappeared among the gods of the Thirty-Three.*";
