P_HTM[7495]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7496]="*2. Dutiyapuññābhisandasuttaṃ**A Visit to the Gods (3rd)*";
P_HTM[7497]="*Atha kho bhagavā—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—jetavane antarahito devesu tāvatiṃsesu pāturahosi.**Then the Buddha, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, vanished from Jeta’s Grove and reappeared among the gods of the Thirty-Three.*";
P_HTM[7498]="*Atha kho sambahulā tāvatiṃsakāyikā devatāyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho tā devatāyo bhagavā etadavoca:**Then several deities of the company of the Thirty-Three went up to the Buddha, bowed, and stood to one side. The Buddha said to them:*";
P_HTM[7499]="*“Sādhu kho, āvuso, buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgamanaṃ hoti—**“Reverends, it’s good to have experiential confidence in the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[7500]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.* **";
P_HTM[7501]="*Buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgamanahetu kho, āvuso, evam’idhekacce sattā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā.**It’s the reason why some sentient beings are stream-enterers, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[7502]="*Sādhu kho, āvuso, dhamme … pe …**It’s good to have experiential confidence in the teaching. …*";
P_HTM[7503]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7504]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgamanaṃ hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**and to have the ethical conduct that’s loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7505]="*Ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgamanahetu kho, āvuso, evam’idhekacce sattā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā”ti.**It’s the reason why some sentient beings are stream-enterers, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[7506]="*“Sādhu kho, mārisa, buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgamanaṃ hoti—**“Good sir, it’s good to have experiential confidence in the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7507]="*itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti.* **";
P_HTM[7508]="*Buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgamanahetu kho, mārisa, evamayaṃ pajā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā.**It’s the reason why some sentient beings are stream-enterers, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[7509]="*Sādhu kho, mārisa, dhamme … pe …**It’s good to have experiential confidence in the teaching. …*";
P_HTM[7510]="*saṅghe … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[7511]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgamanaṃ hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**and to have the ethical conduct that’s loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7512]="*Ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgamanahetu kho, mārisa, evamayaṃ pajā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā”ti.**It’s the reason why some sentient beings are stream-enterers, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
